33def _check_ndim(d3plot, array_dim_names: Dict[str, List[str]]): 

34 """Checks if the specified array is fine in terms of ndim 

35 

36 Parameters 

37 ---------- 

38 d3plot: D3plot 

39 d3plot holding arrays 

40 array_dim_names: Dict[str, List[str]] 

41 """ 

42 

43 for type_name, dim_names in array_dim_names.items(): 

44 if type_name in d3plot.arrays: 

45 array = d3plot.arrays[type_name] 

46 if array.ndim != len(dim_names): 

47 msg = "Array {0} must have {1} instead of {2} dimensions: ({3})" 

48 dim_names_text = ", ".join(dim_names) 

49 raise ValueError(msg.format(type_name, len(dim_names), array.ndim, dim_names_text)) 

50 

51 

52def _check_array_occurrence( 

53 d3plot, array_names: List[str], required_array_names: List[str] 

54) -> bool: 

55 """Check if an array exists, if all depending on it exist too 

56 

57 Parameters 

58 ---------- 

59 array_names: List[str] 

60 list of base arrays 

61 required_array_names: List[str] 

62 list of array names which would be required 

63 

64 Returns 

65 ------- 

66 exists: bool 

67 if the arrays exist or not 

68 

69 Raises 

70 ------ 

71 ValueError 

72 If a required array is not present 

73 """ 

74 

75 if any(name in d3plot.arrays for name in array_names): 

76 if not all(name in d3plot.arrays for name in required_array_names): 

77 msg = "The arrays '{0}' require setting also the arrays '{1}'" 

78 raise ValueError(msg.format(", ".join(array_names), ", ".join(required_array_names))) 

79 return True 

80 return False

83def _negative_to_positive_state_indexes(indexes: Set[int], n_entries) -> Set[int]: 

84 """Convert negative indexes of an iterable to positive ones 

85 

86 Parameters 

87 ---------- 

88 indexes: Set[int] 

89 indexes to check and convert 

90 n_entries: int 

91 total number of entries 

92 

93 Returns 

94 ------- 

95 new_entries: Set[int] 

96 the positive indexes 

97 """ 

98 

99 new_entries: Set[int] = set() 

100 for _, index in enumerate(indexes): 

101 new_index = index + n_entries if index < 0 else index 

102 if new_index >= n_entries: 

103 err_msg = "State '{0}' exceeds the maximum number of states of '{1}'" 

104 raise ValueError(err_msg.format(index, n_entries)) 

105 new_entries.add(new_index) 

106 return new_entries

109# pylint: disable = too-many-instance-attributes 

110class D3plotWriterSettings: 

111 """Settings class for d3plot writing""" 

112 

113 def __init__(self, d3plot: Any, block_size_bytes: int, single_file: bool): 

114 

115 # check the writing types 

116 if d3plot.header.itype == np.int32: 

117 self.itype = "<i" 

118 elif d3plot.header.itype == np.int64: 

119 self.itype = "<q" 

120 else: 

121 msg = "Invalid type for integers: {0}. np.int32 or np.int64 is required." 

122 raise RuntimeError(msg.format(d3plot.itype)) 

123 

124 if d3plot.header.ftype == np.float32: 

125 self.ftype = "<f" 

126 elif d3plot.header.ftype == np.float64: 

127 self.ftype = "<d" 

128 else: 

129 msg = "Invalid type for floats: {0}. np.float32 or np.float64 is required." 

130 raise RuntimeError(msg.format(d3plot.ftype)) 

131 

132 assert isinstance(d3plot, D3plot) 

133 self.d3plot = d3plot 

134 self._header = {} 

135 self.block_size_bytes = block_size_bytes 

136 self.mattyp = 0 

137 self.single_file = single_file 

138 self.mdlopt = 0 

139 self.n_shell_layers = 0 

140 self.n_rigid_shells = 0 

141 self.unique_beam_part_indexes = np.empty(0, dtype=self.itype) 

142 self.unique_shell_part_indexes = np.empty(0, dtype=self.itype) 

143 self.unique_solid_part_indexes = np.empty(0, dtype=self.itype) 

144 self.unique_tshell_part_indexes = np.empty(0, dtype=self.itype) 

145 self._str_codec = "utf-8" 

146 self.has_node_temperature_gradient = False 

147 self.has_node_residual_forces = False 

148 self.has_node_residual_moments = False 

149 self.has_plastic_strain_tensor = False 

150 self.has_thermal_strain_tensor = False 

151 self.n_solid_layers = 1 

152 

153 self._allowed_int_types = (np.int8, np.int16, np.int32, np.int64, int) 

154 self._allowed_float_types = (np.float32, np.float64, float) 

155 

156 @property 

157 def wordsize(self): 

158 """Get the wordsize to use for the d3plot 

159 

160 Returns 

161 ------- 

162 worsize : int 

163 D3plot wordsize 

164 """ 

165 return self.d3plot.header.wordsize 

166 

167 @property 

168 def header(self): 

169 """Dictionary holding all d3plot header information 

170 

171 Notes 

172 ----- 

173 The header is being build from the data stored in the d3plot. 

174 """ 

175 return self._header 

176 

177 @header.setter 

178 def set_header(self, new_header: dict): 

179 assert isinstance(new_header, dict) 

180 self._header = new_header 

181 

182 # pylint: disable = too-many-branches, too-many-statements, too-many-locals 

183 def build_header(self): 

184 """Build the new d3plot header""" 

185 

186 new_header = {} 

187 

188 # TITLE 

189 new_header["title"] = self.d3plot.header.title 

190 # RUNTIME 

191 new_header["runtime"] = self.d3plot.header.runtime 

192 # FILETYPE 

193 new_header["filetype"] = self.d3plot.header.filetype.value 

194 # SOURCE VERSION 

195 new_header["source_version"] = self.d3plot.header.source_version 

196 # RELEASE VERSION 

197 new_header["release_version"] = self.d3plot.header.release_version 

198 # SOURCE VERSION 

199 new_header["version"] = self.d3plot.header.version 

200 

201 # NDIM 

202 

203 # check for rigid body data 

204 has_rigid_body_data = False 

205 has_reduced_rigid_body_data = False 

206 if ( 

207 ArrayType.rigid_body_coordinates in self.d3plot.arrays 

208 or ArrayType.rigid_body_rotation_matrix in self.d3plot.arrays 

209 ): 

210 has_rigid_body_data = True 

211 has_reduced_rigid_body_data = True 

212 if ( 

213 ArrayType.rigid_body_velocity in self.d3plot.arrays 

214 or ArrayType.rigid_body_rot_velocity in self.d3plot.arrays 

215 or ArrayType.rigid_body_acceleration in self.d3plot.arrays 

216 or ArrayType.rigid_body_rot_acceleration in self.d3plot.arrays 

217 ): 

218 has_reduced_rigid_body_data = False 

219 

220 # check for rigid road 

221 required_arrays = [ 

222 ArrayType.rigid_road_node_ids, 

223 ArrayType.rigid_road_node_coordinates, 

224 ArrayType.rigid_road_ids, 

225 ArrayType.rigid_road_segment_node_ids, 

226 ArrayType.rigid_road_segment_road_id, 

227 ] 

228 _check_array_occurrence( 

229 self.d3plot, array_names=required_arrays, required_array_names=required_arrays 

230 ) 

231 has_rigid_road = ArrayType.rigid_road_node_ids in self.d3plot.arrays 

232 

233 # check for mattyp shit 

234 # self.mattyp = 0 

235 # if not is_d3part and ArrayType.part_material_type in self.d3plot.arrays: 

236 # self.mattyp = 1 

237 # elif is_d3part and ArrayType.part_material_type in self.d3plot.arrays: 

238 # # 

239 # self.mattyp = 0 

240 

241 # check for mattyp 

242 is_d3part = self.d3plot.header.filetype == D3plotFiletype.D3PART 

243 

244 self.mattyp = 0 

245 if not is_d3part and ArrayType.part_material_type in self.d3plot.arrays: 

246 self.mattyp = 1 

247 

248 # rigid shells 

249 if ArrayType.element_shell_part_indexes in self.d3plot.arrays: 

250 part_mattyp = self.d3plot.arrays[ArrayType.part_material_type] 

251 shell_part_indexes = self.d3plot.arrays[ArrayType.element_shell_part_indexes] 

252 self.n_rigid_shells = (part_mattyp[shell_part_indexes] == 20).sum() 

253 elif is_d3part: 

254 self.mattyp = 0 

255 

256 # set ndim finally 

257 # 

258 # This also confuses me from the manual ... 

259 # It doesn't specify ndim clearly and only gives ranges. 

260 # 

261 # - has rigid body: rigid body data (movement etc.) 

262 # - rigid road: rigid road data 

263 # - mattyp: array with material types for each part 

264 # 

265 # Table: 

266 # |----------------|--------------------|------------|---------|----------| 

267 # | has_rigid_body | reduced rigid body | rigid road | mattyp | ndim | 

268 # |----------------|--------------------|------------|---------|----------| 

269 # | False | False | False | 0 | 4 | 

270 # | False | False | False | 1 | 5 | 

271 # | False (?) | False | True | 0 | 6 | 

272 # | False | False | True | 1 | 7 | 

273 # | True | False | False | 0 | 8 | 

274 # | True | True | True | 0 | 9 | 

275 # |----------------|--------------------|------------|---------|----------| 

276 # 

277 # uncertainties: mattyp 0 or 1 ?!?!? 

278 if ( 

279 not has_rigid_body_data 

280 and not has_reduced_rigid_body_data 

281 and not has_rigid_road 

282 and self.mattyp == 0 

283 ): 

284 new_header["ndim"] = 4 

285 elif ( 

286 not has_rigid_body_data 

287 and not has_reduced_rigid_body_data 

288 and not has_rigid_road 

289 and self.mattyp == 1 

290 ): 

291 new_header["ndim"] = 5 

292 elif ( 

293 not has_rigid_body_data 

294 and not has_reduced_rigid_body_data 

295 and has_rigid_road 

296 and self.mattyp == 0 

297 ): 

298 new_header["ndim"] = 6 

299 elif ( 

300 not has_rigid_body_data 

301 and not has_reduced_rigid_body_data 

302 and has_rigid_road 

303 and self.mattyp == 1 

304 ): 

305 new_header["ndim"] = 7 

306 elif ( 

307 has_rigid_body_data 

308 and not has_reduced_rigid_body_data 

309 and not has_rigid_road 

310 and self.mattyp == 0 

311 ): 

312 new_header["ndim"] = 8 

313 elif ( 

314 has_rigid_body_data 

315 and has_reduced_rigid_body_data 

316 and has_rigid_road 

317 and self.mattyp == 0 

318 ): 

319 new_header["ndim"] = 9 

320 else: 

321 raise RuntimeError("Cannot determine haeder variable ndim.") 

322 

323 # NUMNP 

324 new_header["numnp"] = ( 

325 self.d3plot.arrays[ArrayType.node_coordinates].shape[0] 

326 if ArrayType.node_coordinates in self.d3plot.arrays 

327 else 0 

328 ) 

329 

330 # ICODE 

331 new_header["icode"] = self.d3plot.header.legacy_code_type 

332 

333 # IT aka temperatures 

334 _check_array_occurrence( 

335 self.d3plot, 

336 array_names=[ArrayType.node_heat_flux], 

337 required_array_names=[ArrayType.node_temperature], 

338 ) 

339 

340 it_temp = 0 

341 if ArrayType.node_mass_scaling in self.d3plot.arrays: 

342 it_temp += 10 

343 

344 if ( 

345 ArrayType.node_temperature in self.d3plot.arrays 

346 and ArrayType.node_heat_flux not in self.d3plot.arrays 

347 ): 

348 it_temp += 1 

349 elif ( 

350 ArrayType.node_temperature in self.d3plot.arrays 

351 and ArrayType.node_heat_flux in self.d3plot.arrays 

352 ): 

353 

354 node_temp_shape = self.d3plot.arrays[ArrayType.node_temperature].shape 

355 if node_temp_shape.ndim == 2: 

356 it_temp += 2 

357 elif node_temp_shape.ndim == 3: 

358 it_temp += 3 

359 else: 

360 msg = "{1} is supposed to have either 2 or 3 dims and not '{0}'" 

361 raise RuntimeError(msg.format(node_temp_shape.ndim, ArrayType.node_temperature)) 

362 else: 

363 # caught by _check_array_occurrence 

364 pass 

365 new_header["it"] = it_temp 

366 

367 # IU - disp field indicator 

368 new_header["iu"] = 1 if ArrayType.node_displacement in self.d3plot.arrays else 0 

369 

370 # IV - velicoty field indicator 

371 new_header["iv"] = 1 if ArrayType.node_velocity in self.d3plot.arrays else 0 

372 

373 # IA - velicoty field indicator 

374 new_header["ia"] = 1 if ArrayType.node_acceleration in self.d3plot.arrays else 0 

375 

376 # NEL8 - solid count 

377 n_solids = ( 

378 self.d3plot.arrays[ArrayType.element_solid_node_indexes].shape[0] 

379 if ArrayType.element_solid_node_indexes in self.d3plot.arrays 

380 else 0 

381 ) 

382 new_header["nel8"] = n_solids 

383 

384 # helper var to track max material index across all element types 

385 # this is required to allocate the part array later 

386 # new_header["nmmat"] = 0 

387 

388 # NUMMAT8 - solid material count 

389 required_arrays = [ 

390 ArrayType.element_solid_node_indexes, 

391 ArrayType.element_solid_part_indexes, 

392 ] 

393 _check_array_occurrence( 

394 self.d3plot, 

395 array_names=required_arrays, 

396 required_array_names=required_arrays, 

397 ) 

398 if ArrayType.element_solid_part_indexes in self.d3plot.arrays: 

399 part_indexes = self.d3plot.arrays[ArrayType.element_solid_part_indexes] 

400 unique_part_indexes = np.unique(part_indexes) 

401 self.unique_solid_part_indexes = unique_part_indexes 

402 new_header["nummat8"] = len(unique_part_indexes) 

403 

404 # max_index = unique_part_indexes.max() + 1 \ 

405 # if len(part_indexes) else 0 

406 # new_header["nmmat"] = max(new_header["nmmat"], 

407 # max_index) 

408 else: 

409 new_header["nummat8"] = 0 

410 

411 # NUMDS 

412 new_header["numds"] = self.d3plot.header.has_shell_four_inplane_gauss_points 

413 

414 # NUMST 

415 new_header["numst"] = self.d3plot.header.unused_numst 

416 

417 # NV3D - number of solid vars 

418 # NEIPH - number of solid history vars 

419 n_solid_layers = self.d3plot.check_array_dims( 

420 { 

421 ArrayType.element_solid_stress: 2, 

422 ArrayType.element_solid_effective_plastic_strain: 2, 

423 ArrayType.element_solid_history_variables: 2, 

424 ArrayType.element_solid_plastic_strain_tensor: 2, 

425 ArrayType.element_solid_thermal_strain_tensor: 2, 

426 }, 

427 "n_solid_layers", 

428 ) 

429 n_solid_layers = 1 if n_solid_layers < 1 else n_solid_layers 

430 self.n_solid_layers = n_solid_layers 

431 if n_solid_layers not in (1, 8): 

432 err_msg = "Solids must have either 1 or 8 integration layers not {0}." 

433 raise ValueError(err_msg.format(self.n_solid_layers)) 

434 

435 n_solid_hist_vars, _ = self.count_array_state_var( 

436 array_type=ArrayType.element_solid_history_variables, 

437 dimension_names=["n_timesteps", "n_solids", "n_solid_layers", "n_history_vars"], 

438 has_layers=True, 

439 n_layers=n_solid_layers, 

440 ) 

441 n_solid_hist_vars = n_solid_hist_vars // n_solid_layers 

442 

443 if ArrayType.element_solid_strain in self.d3plot.arrays: 

444 n_solid_hist_vars += 6 

445 # It is uncertain if this is counted as history var 

446 if ArrayType.element_solid_plastic_strain_tensor in self.d3plot.arrays: 

447 n_solid_hist_vars += 6 

448 # It is uncertain if this is counted as history var 

449 if ArrayType.element_solid_thermal_strain_tensor in self.d3plot.arrays: 

450 n_solid_hist_vars += 6 

451 n_solid_vars = (7 + n_solid_hist_vars) * n_solid_layers 

452 new_header["neiph"] = ( 

453 n_solid_hist_vars if n_solids != 0 else self.d3plot.header.n_solid_history_vars 

454 ) 

455 new_header["nv3d"] = n_solid_vars if n_solids != 0 else self.d3plot.header.n_solid_vars 

456 

457 # NEL2 - beam count 

458 new_header["nel2"] = ( 

459 self.d3plot.arrays[ArrayType.element_beam_node_indexes].shape[0] 

460 if ArrayType.element_beam_node_indexes in self.d3plot.arrays 

461 else 0 

462 ) 

463 

464 # NUMMAT2 - beam material count 

465 required_arrays = [ 

466 ArrayType.element_beam_node_indexes, 

467 ArrayType.element_beam_part_indexes, 

468 ] 

469 _check_array_occurrence( 

470 self.d3plot, 

471 array_names=required_arrays, 

472 required_array_names=required_arrays, 

473 ) 

474 if ArrayType.element_beam_part_indexes in self.d3plot.arrays: 

475 part_indexes = self.d3plot.arrays[ArrayType.element_beam_part_indexes] 

476 unique_part_indexes = np.unique(part_indexes) 

477 new_header["nummat2"] = len(unique_part_indexes) 

478 

479 self.unique_beam_part_indexes = unique_part_indexes 

480 

481 # max_index = unique_part_indexes.max() + 1 \ 

482 # if len(unique_part_indexes) else 0 

483 # new_header["nmmat"] = max(new_header["nmmat"], 

484 # max_index) 

485 else: 

486 new_header["nummat2"] = 0 

487 

488 # NEIPB - beam history vars per integration point 

489 array_dims = { 

490 ArrayType.element_beam_shear_stress: 2, 

491 ArrayType.element_beam_axial_stress: 2, 

492 ArrayType.element_beam_plastic_strain: 2, 

493 ArrayType.element_beam_axial_strain: 2, 

494 ArrayType.element_beam_history_vars: 2, 

495 } 

496 n_beam_layers = self.d3plot.check_array_dims(array_dims, "n_beam_layers") 

497 new_header["beamip"] = n_beam_layers 

498 

499 new_header["neipb"] = 0 

500 if ArrayType.element_beam_history_vars in self.d3plot.arrays: 

501 array = self.d3plot.arrays[ArrayType.element_beam_history_vars] 

502 if array.ndim != 4: 

503 msg = ( 

504 "Array '{0}' was expected to have 4 dimensions " 

505 "(n_timesteps, n_beams, n_modes (3+n_beam_layers), " 

506 "n_beam_history_vars)." 

507 ) 

508 raise ValueError(msg.format(ArrayType.element_beam_history_vars)) 

509 if array.shape[3] < 3: 

510 msg = ( 

511 "Array '{0}' dimension 3 must have have at least three" 

512 " entries (beam layers: average, min, max)" 

513 ) 

514 raise ValueError(msg.format(ArrayType.element_beam_history_vars)) 

515 if array.shape[3] != 3 + n_beam_layers: 

516 msg = "Array '{0}' dimension 3 must have size (3+n_beam_layers). {1} != (3+{2})" 

517 raise ValueError(msg.format(ArrayType.element_beam_history_vars)) 

518 new_header["neipb"] = array.shape[3] 

519 

520 # NV1D - beam variable count 

521 new_header["nv1d"] = ( 

522 6 + 5 * new_header["beamip"] + new_header["neipb"] * (3 + new_header["beamip"]) 

523 ) 

524 

525 # NEL4 - number of shells 

526 n_shells = ( 

527 self.d3plot.arrays[ArrayType.element_shell_node_indexes].shape[0] 

528 if ArrayType.element_shell_node_indexes in self.d3plot.arrays 

529 else 0 

530 ) 

531 new_header["nel4"] = n_shells 

532 

533 # NUMMAT4 - shell material count 

534 required_arrays = [ 

535 ArrayType.element_shell_node_indexes, 

536 ArrayType.element_shell_part_indexes, 

537 ] 

538 _check_array_occurrence( 

539 self.d3plot, 

540 array_names=required_arrays, 

541 required_array_names=required_arrays, 

542 ) 

543 if ArrayType.element_shell_part_indexes in self.d3plot.arrays: 

544 part_indexes = self.d3plot.arrays[ArrayType.element_shell_part_indexes] 

545 unique_part_indexes = np.unique(part_indexes) 

546 new_header["nummat4"] = len(unique_part_indexes) 

547 

548 self.unique_shell_part_indexes = unique_part_indexes 

549 

550 # max_index = unique_part_indexes.max() + 1 \ 

551 # if len(unique_part_indexes) else 0 

552 # new_header["nmmat"] = max(new_header["nmmat"], 

553 # max_index) 

554 else: 

555 new_header["nummat4"] = 0 

556 

557 # NEIPS -shell history variable count 

558 n_shell_layers = 0 

559 if ( 

560 ArrayType.element_shell_history_vars in self.d3plot.arrays 

561 or ArrayType.element_tshell_history_variables in self.d3plot.arrays 

562 ): 

563 

564 n_shell_history_vars, n_shell_layers = self.count_array_state_var( 

565 array_type=ArrayType.element_shell_history_vars, 

566 dimension_names=["n_timesteps", "n_shells", "n_shell_layers", "n_history_vars"], 

567 has_layers=True, 

568 n_layers=n_shell_layers, 

569 ) 

570 n_tshell_history_vars, n_tshell_layers = self.count_array_state_var( 

571 array_type=ArrayType.element_tshell_history_variables, 

572 dimension_names=["n_timesteps", "n_tshells", "n_shell_layers", "n_history_vars"], 

573 has_layers=True, 

574 n_layers=n_shell_layers, 

575 ) 

576 

577 if n_shell_layers != n_tshell_layers: 

578 msg = ( 

579 "Shells and thick shells must have the same amount " 

580 "of integration layers: {0} != {1}" 

581 ) 

582 raise RuntimeError(msg.format(n_shell_layers, n_tshell_layers)) 

583 

584 # we are tolerant here and simply add zero padding for the other 

585 # field later on 

586 new_header["neips"] = max( 

587 n_tshell_history_vars // n_tshell_layers, n_shell_history_vars // n_shell_layers 

588 ) 

589 else: 

590 new_header["neips"] = 0 

591 

592 array_dims = { 

593 ArrayType.element_shell_stress: 2, 

594 ArrayType.element_shell_effective_plastic_strain: 2, 

595 ArrayType.element_shell_history_vars: 2, 

596 ArrayType.element_tshell_stress: 2, 

597 ArrayType.element_tshell_effective_plastic_strain: 2, 

598 ArrayType.element_tshell_history_variables: 2, 

599 } 

600 n_shell_layers = self.d3plot.check_array_dims(array_dims, "n_shell_layers") 

601 self.n_shell_layers = n_shell_layers 

602 

603 # NELTH - number of thick shell elements 

604 n_thick_shells = ( 

605 self.d3plot.arrays[ArrayType.element_tshell_node_indexes].shape[0] 

606 if ArrayType.element_tshell_node_indexes in self.d3plot.arrays 

607 else 0 

608 ) 

609 new_header["nelth"] = n_thick_shells 

610 

611 # IOSHL1 - shell & solid stress flag 

612 if ( 

613 ArrayType.element_shell_stress in self.d3plot.arrays 

614 or ArrayType.element_tshell_stress in self.d3plot.arrays 

615 ): 

616 new_header["ioshl1"] = 1000 

617 else: 

618 # if either stress or pstrain is written for solids 

619 # the whole block of 7 basic variables is always written 

620 # to the file 

621 if ( 

622 ArrayType.element_solid_stress in self.d3plot.arrays 

623 or ArrayType.element_solid_effective_plastic_strain in self.d3plot.arrays 

624 ): 

625 new_header["ioshl1"] = 999 

626 else: 

627 new_header["ioshl1"] = 0 

628 

629 if n_shells == 0 and n_thick_shells == 0 and n_solids == 0: 

630 new_header["ioshl1"] = ( 

631 self.d3plot.header.raw_header["ioshl1"] 

632 if "ioshl1" in self.d3plot.header.raw_header 

633 else 0 

634 ) 

635 

636 if n_shells == 0 and n_thick_shells == 0 and n_solids != 0: 

637 if ( 

638 "ioshl1" in self.d3plot.header.raw_header 

639 and self.d3plot.header.raw_header["ioshl1"] == 1000 

640 ): 

641 new_header["ioshl1"] = 1000 

642 

643 # IOSHL2 - shell & solid pstrain flag 

644 if ( 

645 ArrayType.element_shell_effective_plastic_strain in self.d3plot.arrays 

646 or ArrayType.element_tshell_effective_plastic_strain in self.d3plot.arrays 

647 ): 

648 new_header["ioshl2"] = 1000 

649 else: 

650 if ArrayType.element_solid_effective_plastic_strain in self.d3plot.arrays: 

651 new_header["ioshl2"] = 999 

652 else: 

653 new_header["ioshl2"] = 0 

654 

655 if n_shells == 0 and n_thick_shells == 0 and n_solids == 0: 

656 new_header["ioshl2"] = ( 

657 self.d3plot.header.raw_header["ioshl2"] 

658 if "ioshl2" in self.d3plot.header.raw_header 

659 else 0 

660 ) 

661 

662 if n_shells == 0 and n_thick_shells == 0 and n_solids != 0: 

663 if ( 

664 "ioshl2" in self.d3plot.header.raw_header 

665 and self.d3plot.header.raw_header["ioshl2"] == 1000 

666 ): 

667 new_header["ioshl2"] = 1000 

668 

669 # IOSHL3 - shell forces flag 

670 if ( 

671 ArrayType.element_shell_shear_force in self.d3plot.arrays 

672 or ArrayType.element_shell_bending_moment in self.d3plot.arrays 

673 or ArrayType.element_shell_normal_force in self.d3plot.arrays 

674 ): 

675 new_header["ioshl3"] = 1000 

676 else: 

677 # new_header["ioshl3"] = 999 

678 new_header["ioshl3"] = 0 

679 

680 if n_shells == 0: 

681 new_header["ioshl3"] = ( 

682 self.d3plot.header.raw_header["ioshl3"] 

683 if "ioshl3" in self.d3plot.header.raw_header 

684 else 0 

685 )

688 if (

690 or ArrayType.element_shell_unknown_variables in self.d3plot.arrays 

691 or ArrayType.element_shell_internal_energy in self.d3plot.arrays 

692 ):

694 else:

701 if "ioshl4" in self.d3plot.header.raw_header 

702 else 0

706 new_header["idtdt"] = 0

708 if ( 

709 ArrayType.element_shell_strain in self.d3plot.arrays 

710 or ArrayType.element_solid_strain in self.d3plot.arrays 

711 or ArrayType.element_tshell_strain in self.d3plot.arrays

883 { 

884 ArrayType.part_ids: 0, 

885 ArrayType.part_internal_energy: 1,

888 ArrayType.part_velocity: 1, 

889 }, 

890 "n_parts", 

891 )

895 # FIX

897 if new_header["nmmat"] > tmp_nmmat:

899 new_header["nmmat"] 

900 - new_header["nummat2"] 

901 - new_header["nummat4"] 

902 - new_header["nummat8"] 

903 - new_header["nummatt"] 

904 ) 

905 else:

922 new_header["narbs"] += 10

924 # NGLBV - number of global variables 

925 n_rigid_wall_vars = 0

940 array = self.d3plot.arrays[ArrayType.rigid_wall_position]

942 msg = "Array '{0}' was expected to have {1} dimensions ({2})." 

943 raise ValueError( 

944 msg.format(

946 3, 

947 ",".join(["n_timesteps", "n_rigid_walls", "x_y_z"]), 

948 )

950 n_rigid_walls = array.shape[1] 

951 

952 new_header["n_rigid_walls"] = n_rigid_walls 

953 new_header["n_rigid_wall_vars"] = n_rigid_wall_vars 

954 n_global_variables = 0 

955 if ArrayType.global_kinetic_energy in self.d3plot.arrays: 

956 n_global_variables = 1 

957 if ArrayType.global_internal_energy in self.d3plot.arrays: 

958 n_global_variables = 2 

959 if ArrayType.global_total_energy in self.d3plot.arrays:

965 if ArrayType.part_kinetic_energy in self.d3plot.arrays: 

966 n_global_variables = 6 + 2 * new_header["nmmat"] 

967 if ArrayType.part_velocity in self.d3plot.arrays: 

968 n_global_variables = 6 + 5 * new_header["nmmat"] 

969 if ArrayType.part_mass in self.d3plot.arrays: 

970 n_global_variables = 6 + 6 * new_header["nmmat"] 

971 if ArrayType.part_hourglass_energy in self.d3plot.arrays: 

972 n_global_variables = 6 + 7 * new_header["nmmat"] 

973 if n_rigid_wall_vars * n_rigid_walls != 0: 

974 n_global_variables = 6 + 7 * new_header["nmmat"] + n_rigid_wall_vars * n_rigid_walls 

975 new_header["nglbv"] = n_global_variables 

976 

977 # NUMFLUID - total number of ALE fluid groups 

978 new_header["numfluid"] = 0 

979 

980 # INN - Invariant node numbering fore shell and solid elements 

981 if self.d3plot.header.has_invariant_numbering: 

982 if "inn" in self.d3plot.header.raw_header and self.d3plot.header.raw_header["inn"] != 0: 

983 new_header["inn"] = self.d3plot.header.raw_header["inn"] 

984 else: 

985 new_header["inn"] = int(self.d3plot.header.has_invariant_numbering) 

986 else: 

987 new_header["inn"] = 0 

988 

989 # NPEFG 

990 airbag_arrays = [ 

991 ArrayType.airbags_first_particle_id, 

992 ArrayType.airbags_n_particles, 

993 ArrayType.airbags_ids, 

994 ArrayType.airbags_n_gas_mixtures, 

995 ArrayType.airbags_n_chambers, 

996 ArrayType.airbag_n_active_particles, 

997 ArrayType.airbag_bag_volume, 

998 ArrayType.airbag_particle_gas_id, 

999 ArrayType.airbag_particle_chamber_id, 

1000 ArrayType.airbag_particle_leakage, 

1001 ArrayType.airbag_particle_mass, 

1002 ArrayType.airbag_particle_radius, 

1003 ArrayType.airbag_particle_spin_energy, 

1004 ArrayType.airbag_particle_translation_energy, 

1005 ArrayType.airbag_particle_nearest_segment_distance, 

1006 ArrayType.airbag_particle_position, 

1007 ArrayType.airbag_particle_velocity, 

1008 ] 

1009 subver = 3 if any(name in self.d3plot.arrays for name in airbag_arrays) else 0 

1010 

1011 # subver overwrite 

1012 if self.d3plot.header.n_airbags: 

1013 # pylint: disable = protected-access 

1014 subver = self.d3plot._airbag_info.subver 

1015 

1016 n_partgas = ( 

1017 len(self.d3plot.arrays[ArrayType.airbags_ids]) 

1018 if ArrayType.airbags_ids in self.d3plot.arrays 

1019 else 0 

1020 ) 

1021 

1022 new_header["npefg"] = 1000 * subver + n_partgas 

1023 

1024 # NEL48 - extra nodes for 8 node shell elements 

1025 required_arrays = [ 

1026 ArrayType.element_shell_node8_element_index, 

1027 ArrayType.element_shell_node8_extra_node_indexes, 

1028 ] 

1029 _check_array_occurrence( 

1030 self.d3plot, 

1031 array_names=required_arrays, 

1032 required_array_names=required_arrays, 

1033 ) 

1034 new_header["nel48"] = ( 

1035 len(self.d3plot.arrays[ArrayType.element_shell_node8_element_index]) 

1036 if ArrayType.element_shell_node8_element_index in self.d3plot.arrays 

1037 else 0 

1038 )

1041 required_arrays = [ 

1042 ArrayType.element_solid_node20_element_index, 

1043 ArrayType.element_solid_node20_extra_node_indexes, 

1044 ] 

1045 _check_array_occurrence( 

1046 self.d3plot, 

1047 array_names=required_arrays, 

1048 required_array_names=required_arrays, 

1049 ) 

1050 if ArrayType.element_solid_node20_element_index in self.d3plot.arrays: 

1051 new_header["nel20"] = len( 

1052 self.d3plot.arrays[ArrayType.element_solid_node20_element_index] 

1053 ) 

1054 else: 

1055 new_header["nel20"] = 0

1057 # NT3D - thermal solid data 

1058 if ArrayType.element_solid_thermal_data in self.d3plot.arrays: 

1059 new_header["nt3d"] = len(self.d3plot.arrays[ArrayType.element_solid_thermal_data]) 

1060 else: 

1061 new_header["nt3d"] = 0

1064 required_arrays = [ 

1065 ArrayType.element_solid_node27_element_index, 

1066 ArrayType.element_solid_node27_extra_node_indexes, 

1067 ] 

1068 _check_array_occurrence( 

1069 self.d3plot, 

1070 array_names=required_arrays, 

1071 required_array_names=required_arrays, 

1072 ) 

1073 if ArrayType.element_solid_node27_element_index in self.d3plot.arrays: 

1074 new_header["nel27"] = len( 

1075 self.d3plot.arrays[ArrayType.element_solid_node27_element_index] 

1076 ) 

1077 else: 

1078 new_header["nel27"] = 0

1080 # EXTRA - extra header variables 

1081 # set only if any value is non-zero 

1082 extra_hdr_variables = ["nel20", "nt3d", "nel27", "neipb"] 

1083 if any(new_header[name] for name in extra_hdr_variables): 

1084 new_header["extra"] = 64 

1085 else: 

1086 new_header["extra"] = 0 

1087 

1088 # CHECKS 

1089 

1090 # unique part indexes all ok 

1091 for part_index in self.unique_beam_part_indexes: 

1092 if part_index >= new_header["nmmat"]: 

1093 msg = "{0} part index {1} is larger than number of materials {2}" 

1094 raise ValueError(msg.format("beam", part_index, new_header["nmmat"])) 

1095 for part_index in self.unique_shell_part_indexes: 

1096 if part_index >= new_header["nmmat"]: 

1097 msg = "{0} part index {1} is larger than number of materials {2}" 

1098 raise ValueError(msg.format("shell", part_index, new_header["nmmat"])) 

1099 for part_index in self.unique_solid_part_indexes: 

1100 if part_index >= new_header["nmmat"]: 

1101 msg = "{0} part index {1} is larger than number of materials {2}" 

1102 raise ValueError(msg.format("solid", part_index, new_header["nmmat"])) 

1103 for part_index in self.unique_tshell_part_indexes: 

1104 if part_index >= new_header["nmmat"]: 

1105 msg = "{0} part index {1} is larger than number of materials {2}" 

1106 raise ValueError(msg.format("tshell", part_index, new_header["nmmat"])) 

1107 

1108 # new header 

1109 self._header = new_header 

1110 

1111 # pylint: disable = too-many-return-statements 

1112 def pack(self, value: Any, size=None, dtype_hint=None) -> bytes: 

1113 """Pack a python value according to its settings 

1114 

1115 Parameters 

1116 ---------- 

1117 value: Any 

1118 integer, float or string type value 

1119 size: int 

1120 size in bytes 

1121 dtype_hint: `np.integer` or `np.floating` (default: None) 

1122 dtype hint for numpy arrays (prevens wrong casting) 

1123 

1124 Returns 

1125 ------- 

1126 bytes: bytes 

1127 value packed in bytes 

1128 

1129 Raises 

1130 ------ 

1131 RuntimeError 

1132 If the type cannot be deserialized for being unknown. 

1133 """ 

1134 

1135 assert dtype_hint in (None, np.integer, np.floating) 

1136 

1137 # INT 

1138 if isinstance(value, self._allowed_int_types): 

1139 return struct.pack(self.itype, value) 

1140 # FLOAT 

1141 if isinstance(value, self._allowed_float_types): 

1142 return struct.pack(self.ftype, value) 

1143 # BYTES 

1144 if isinstance(value, bytes): 

1145 if size and len(value) > size: 

1146 return value[:size] 

1147 return value 

1148 # BYTEARRAY 

1149 if isinstance(value, bytearray): 

1150 if size and len(value) > size: 

1151 return bytes(value[:size]) 

1152 return bytes(value) 

1153 # STRING 

1154 if isinstance(value, str): 

1155 if size: 

1156 fmt = "{0:" + str(size) + "}" 

1157 return fmt.format(value).encode(self._str_codec) 

1158 

1159 return value.encode(self._str_codec) 

1160 # ARRAY 

1161 if isinstance(value, np.ndarray): 

1162 

1163 if (value.dtype != self.ftype and dtype_hint == np.floating) or ( 

1164 value.dtype != self.itype and dtype_hint == np.integer 

1165 ): 

1166 

1167 # we need typehint 

1168 if dtype_hint is None: 

1169 msg = "Please specify a dtype_hint (np.floating, np.integer)." 

1170 raise ValueError(msg) 

1171 

1172 # determine new dtype 

1173 new_dtype = self.itype if dtype_hint == np.integer else self.ftype 

1174 

1175 # log conversion 

1176 msg = "Converting array from %s to %s" 

1177 LOGGER.info(msg, value.dtype, new_dtype) 

1178 

1179 # warn if convert between int and float (possible bugs) 

1180 if not np.issubdtype(value.dtype, dtype_hint): 

1181 LOGGER.warning(msg, value.dtype, new_dtype) 

1182 

1183 value = value.astype(new_dtype) 

1184 

1185 return value.tobytes() 

1186 

1187 msg = "Cannot deserialize type '%s' of value '%s' for writing." 

1188 raise RuntimeError(msg, type(value), value) 

1189 

1190 def count_array_state_var( 

1191 self, array_type: str, dimension_names: List[str], has_layers: bool, n_layers: int = 0 

1192 ) -> Tuple[int, int]: 

1193 """This functions checks and updates the variable count for certain types of arrays 

1194 

1195 Parameters 

1196 ---------- 

1197 array_type: str 

1198 name of the shell layer array 

1199 dimension_names: List[str] 

1200 names of the array dimensions 

1201 has_layers: bool 

1202 if the array has integration layers 

1203 n_layers: int 

1204 number of (previous) shell layers, if unknown set to 0 

1205 

1206 Returns 

1207 ------- 

1208 n_vars: int 

1209 variable count 

1210 n_layers: int 

1211 number of layers 

1212 

1213 Raises 

1214 ------ 

1215 ValueError 

1216 If the dimensions of the array were invalid or an inconsistent 

1217 number of integration layers was detected. 

1218 """ 

1219 

1220 n_vars = 0 

1221 

1222 if array_type in self.d3plot.arrays: 

1223 array = self.d3plot.arrays[array_type] 

1224 

1225 if array.ndim != len(dimension_names): 

1226 msg = "Array '{0}' was expected to have {1} dimensions ({2})." 

1227 raise ValueError( 

1228 msg.format(array_type, len(dimension_names), ", ".join(dimension_names)) 

1229 ) 

1230 

1231 if has_layers: 

1232 if n_layers == 0: 

1233 n_layers = array.shape[2] 

1234 else: 

1235 if n_layers != array.shape[2]: 

1236 msg = ( 

1237 "Array '{0}' has '{1}' integration layers" 

1238 " but another array used '{2}'." 

1239 ) 

1240 raise ValueError(msg.format(array_type, array.shape[2], n_layers)) 

1241 

1242 # last dimension is collapsed 

1243 if array.ndim == 3: 

1244 n_vars = 1 * n_layers 

1245 else: 

1246 n_vars = array.shape[3] * n_layers 

1247 

1248 # no layers 

1249 else: 

1250 

1251 # last dimension is collapsed 

1252 if array.ndim == 2: 

1253 n_vars = 1 

1254 else: 

1255 n_vars = array.shape[2] 

1256 

1257 return n_vars, n_layers 

1258

1289 # there is a lot to go wrong

1291 self.buffer_info = self.api.get_buffer_info(filepath) 

1292 # loading femzip api failed

1430 

1431class D3plot: 

1432 """Class used to read LS-Dyna d3plots""" 

1433 

1434 _header: D3plotHeader 

1435 _femzip_info: FemzipInfo 

1436 _material_section_info: MaterialSectionInfo 

1437 _sph_info: SphSectionInfo 

1438 _airbag_info: AirbagInfo 

1439 _numbering_info: NumberingInfo 

1440 _rigid_body_info: RigidBodyInfo 

1441 _rigid_road_info: RigidRoadInfo 

1442 _buffer: Union[BinaryBuffer, None] = None 

1443 

1444 # we all love secret settings 

1445 use_advanced_femzip_api: bool = False 

1446 

1447 # This amount of args is needed 

1448 # pylint: disable = too-many-arguments, too-many-statements, unused-argument 

1449 def __init__( 

1450 self, 

1451 filepath: str = None, 

1452 use_femzip: Union[bool, None] = None, 

1453 n_files_to_load_at_once: Union[int, None] = None, 

1454 state_array_filter: Union[List[str], None] = None, 

1455 state_filter: Union[None, Set[int]] = None, 

1456 buffered_reading: bool = False, 

1457 ): 

1458 """Constructor for a D3plot 

1459 

1460 Parameters 

1461 ---------- 

1462 filepath: str 

1463 path to a d3plot file 

1464 use_femzip: bool 

1465 Not used anymore. 

1466 n_files_to_load_at_once: int 

1467 *DEPRECATED* not used anymore, use `buffered_reading` 

1468 state_array_filter: Union[List[str], None] 

1469 names of arrays which will be the only ones loaded from state data 

1470 state_filter: Union[None, Set[int]] 

1471 which states to load. Negative indexes count backwards. 

1472 buffered_reading: bool 

1473 whether to pull only a single state into memory during reading 

1474 

1475 Examples 

1476 -------- 

1477 >>> from lasso.dyna import D3plot, ArrayType 

1478 >>> # open and read everything 

1479 >>> d3plot = D3plot("path/to/d3plot") 

1480 

1481 >>> # only read node displacement 

1482 >>> d3plot = D3plot("path/to/d3plot", state_array_filter=["node_displacement"]) 

1483 >>> # or with nicer syntax 

1484 >>> d3plot = D3plot("path/to/d3plot", state_array_filter=[ArrayType.node_displacement]) 

1485 

1486 >>> # only load first and last state 

1487 >>> d3plot = D3plot("path/to/d3plot", state_filter={0, -1}) 

1488 

1489 >>> # our computer lacks RAM so lets extract a specific array 

1490 >>> # but only keep one state at a time in memory 

1491 >>> d3plot = D3plot("path/to/d3plot", 

1492 >>> state_array_filter=[ArrayType.node_displacement], 

1493 >>> buffered_reading=True) 

1494 

1495 Notes 

1496 ----- 

1497 If dyna wrote multiple files for several states, 

1498 only give the path to the first file. 

1499 """ 

1500 super().__init__() 

1501 

1502 LOGGER.debug("-------- D 3 P L O T --------") 

1503 

1504 self._arrays = {} 

1505 self._header = D3plotHeader() 

1506 self._femzip_info = FemzipInfo(filepath=filepath if filepath is not None else "") 

1507 self._material_section_info = MaterialSectionInfo() 

1508 self._sph_info = SphSectionInfo() 

1509 self._airbag_info = AirbagInfo() 

1510 self._numbering_info = NumberingInfo() 

1511 self._rigid_body_info = RigidBodyInfo(rigid_body_metadata_list=tuple()) 

1512 self._rigid_road_info = RigidRoadInfo() 

1513 self._state_info = StateInfo() 

1514 

1515 # which states to load 

1516 self.state_filter = state_filter 

1517 

1518 # how many files to load into memory at once 

1519 if n_files_to_load_at_once is not None: 

1520 warn_msg = "D3plot argument '{0}' is deprecated. Please use '{1}=True'." 

1521 raise DeprecationWarning(warn_msg.format("n_files_to_load_at_once", "buffered_reading")) 

1522 self.buffered_reading = buffered_reading or (state_filter is not None and any(state_filter)) 

1523 

1524 # arrays to filter out 

1525 self.state_array_filter = state_array_filter 

1526 

1527 # load memory accordingly 

1528 # no femzip 

1529 if filepath and not self._femzip_info.use_femzip: 

1530 self._buffer = BinaryBuffer(filepath) 

1531 self.bb_states = None 

1532 # femzip 

1533 elif filepath and self._femzip_info.use_femzip: 

1534 self._buffer = self._read_femzip_geometry(filepath) 

1535 # we need to reload the header 

1536 self._header = D3plotHeader().load_file(self._buffer) 

1537 self.bb_states = None 

1538 # no data to load basically 

1539 else: 

1540 self._buffer = None 

1541 self.bb_states = None 

1542 

1543 self.geometry_section_size = 0 

1544 

1545 # read header 

1546 self._read_header() 

1547 

1548 # read geometry 

1549 self._parse_geometry() 

1550 

1551 # read state data 

1552 

1553 # try advanced femzip api 

1554 if ( 

1555 filepath 

1556 and self._femzip_info.use_femzip 

1557 and self.use_advanced_femzip_api 

1558 and self._femzip_info.api.has_femunziplib_license() 

1559 ): 

1560 

1561 LOGGER.debug("Advanced FEMZIP-API used") 

1562 try: 

1563 self._read_states_femzip_advanced( 

1564 filepath, 

1565 ) 

1566 except Exception: 

1567 trace = traceback.format_exc() 

1568 warn_msg = ( 

1569 "Error when using advanced Femzip API, " 

1570 "falling back to normal but slower Femzip API.\n%s" 

1571 ) 

1572 LOGGER.warning(warn_msg, trace) 

1573 

1574 # since we had a crash, we need to reload the file 

1575 # to be sure we don't crash again 

1576 self._femzip_info.api.close_current_file() 

1577 self._femzip_info.api.read_geometry(filepath, self._femzip_info.buffer_info, False) 

1578 # try normal femzip api 

1579 self._read_states(filepath) 

1580 finally: 

1581 self._femzip_info.api.close_current_file() 

1582 

1583 # normal state reading (femzip and non-femzip) 

1584 elif filepath: 

1585 self._read_states(filepath) 

1586 if self._femzip_info.use_femzip: 

1587 self._femzip_info.api.close_current_file() 

1588 else: 

1589 # no filepath = nothing to do 

1590 pass 

1591 

1592 def _read_femzip_geometry(self, filepath: str) -> BinaryBuffer: 

1593 """Read the geometry from femzip 

1594 

1595 Parameters 

1596 ---------- 

1597 filepath: str 

1598 path to the femzpi file 

1599 

1600 Returns 

1601 ------- 

1602 bb: BinaryBuffer 

1603 memory of the geometry section 

1604 """ 

1605 

1606 buffer_geo = self._femzip_info.api.read_geometry( 

1607 filepath, buffer_info=self._femzip_info.buffer_info, close_file=False 

1608 ) 

1609 

1610 # save 

1611 buffer = BinaryBuffer() 

1612 buffer.filepath_ = filepath 

1613 buffer.memoryview = buffer_geo.cast("B") 

1614 

1615 return buffer 

1616 

1617 @property 

1618 def n_timesteps(self) -> int: 

1619 """Number of timesteps loaded""" 

1620 return self._state_info.n_timesteps

1622 @property

1624 """Dictionary holding all d3plot arrays 

1625 

1626 Notes 

1627 ----- 

1628 The corresponding keys of the dictionary can 

1629 also be found in `lasso.dyna.ArrayTypes`, which 

1630 helps with IDE integration and code safety. 

1631 

1632 Examples 

1633 -------- 

1634 >>> d3plot = D3plot("some/path/to/d3plot") 

1635 >>> d3plot.arrays.keys() 

1636 dict_keys(['irbtyp', 'node_coordinates', ...]) 

1637 >>> # The following is good coding practice 

1638 >>> import lasso.dyna.ArrayTypes.ArrayTypes as atypes 

1639 >>> d3plot.arrays[atypes.node_displacmeent].shape 

1640 """ 

1641 return self._arrays 

1642 

1643 @arrays.setter 

1644 def arrays(self, array_dict: dict): 

1645 assert isinstance(array_dict, dict) 

1646 self._arrays = array_dict 

1647 

1648 @property 

1649 def header(self) -> D3plotHeader: 

1650 """Instance holding all d3plot header information 

1651 

1652 Returns 

1653 ------- 

1654 header: D3plotHeader

1657 Notes 

1658 -----

1660 of elements, etc. 

1661 

1662 Examples 

1663 -------- 

1664 >>> d3plot = D3plot("some/path/to/d3plot") 

1665 >>> # number of shells 

1666 >>> d3plot.header.n_shells

1668 """ 

1669 return self._header 

1670 

1671 @staticmethod 

1672 def _is_end_of_file_marker( 

1673 buffer: BinaryBuffer, position: int, ftype: Union[np.float32, np.float64] 

1674 ) -> bool: 

1675 """Check for the dyna eof marker at a certain position 

1676 

1677 Parameters 

1678 ---------- 

1679 bb: BinaryBuffer 

1680 buffer holding memory 

1681 position: int 

1682 position in the buffer 

1683 ftype: Union[np.float32, np.float64] 

1684 floating point type 

1685 

1686 Returns 

1687 ------- 

1688 is_end_marker: bool 

1689 if at the position is an end marker 

1690 

1691 Notes 

1692 ----- 

1693 The end of file marker is represented by a floating point 

1694 number with the value -999999 (single precision hex: F02374C9, 

1695 double precision hex: 000000007E842EC1). 

1696 """ 

1697 

1698 if ftype not in (np.float32, np.float64): 

1699 err_msg = "Floating point type '{0}' is not a floating point type." 

1700 raise ValueError(err_msg.format(ftype)) 

1701 

1702 return buffer.read_number(position, ftype) == ftype(-999999) 

1703 

1704 def _correct_file_offset(self): 

1705 """Correct the position in the bytes 

1706 

1707 Notes 

1708 ----- 

1709 LS-Dyna writes its files zero padded at a size of 

1710 512 words in block size. There might be a lot of 

1711 unused trailing data in the rear we need to skip 

1712 in order to get to the next useful data block. 

1713 """ 

1714 

1715 if not self._buffer: 

1716 return 

1717 

1718 block_count = len(self._buffer) // (512 * self.header.wordsize) 

1719 

1720 # Warning! 

1721 # Resets the block count! 

1722 self.geometry_section_size = (block_count + 1) * 512 * self.header.wordsize 

1723 

1724 @property 

1725 def _n_parts(self) -> int: 

1726 """Get the number of parts contained in the d3plot 

1727 

1728 Returns 

1729 ------- 

1730 n_parts: int 

1731 number of total parts 

1732 """ 

1733 

1734 n_parts = ( 

1735 self.header.n_solid_materials 

1736 + self.header.n_beam_materials 

1737 + self.header.n_shell_materials 

1738 + self.header.n_thick_shell_materials 

1739 + self._numbering_info.n_rigid_bodies 

1740 ) 

1741 

1742 return n_parts 

1743 

1744 @property 

1745 def _n_rigid_walls(self) -> int: 

1746 """Get the number of rigid walls in the d3plot 

1747 

1748 Returns 

1749 ------- 

1750 n_rigid_walls: int 

1751 number of rigid walls 

1752 """ 

1753 

1754 # there have been cases that there are less than in the specs 

1755 # indicated global vars. That breaks this computation, thus we 

1756 # use max at the end. 

1757 previous_global_vars = 6 + 7 * self._n_parts 

1758 n_rigid_wall_vars = self.header.n_rigid_wall_vars 

1759 n_rigid_walls = (self.header.n_global_vars - previous_global_vars) // n_rigid_wall_vars 

1760 

1761 # if n_rigid_walls < 0: 

1762 # err_msg = "The computed number of rigid walls is negative ('{0}')." 

1763 # raise RuntimeError(err_msg.format(n_rigid_walls)) 

1764 

1765 return max(n_rigid_walls, 0) 

1766 

1767 # pylint: disable = unused-argument, too-many-locals 

1768 def _read_d3plot_file_generator( 

1769 self, buffered_reading: bool, state_filter: Union[None, Set[int]] 

1770 ) -> typing.Any: 

1771 """Generator function for reading bare d3plot files 

1772 

1773 Parameters 

1774 ---------- 

1775 buffered_reading: bool 

1776 whether to read one state at a time 

1777 state_filter: Union[None, Set[int]] 

1778 which states to filter out 

1779 

1780 Yields 

1781 ------ 

1782 buffer: BinaryBuffer 

1783 buffer for each file 

1784 n_states: int 

1785 number of states from second yield on 

1786 """ 

1787 

1788 # (1) STATES 

1789 # This is dangerous. The following routine requires data from 

1790 # several sections in the geometry part calling this too early crashes 

1791 bytes_per_state = self._compute_n_bytes_per_state() 

1792 file_infos = self._collect_file_infos(bytes_per_state) 

1793 

1794 # some status 

1795 n_files = len(file_infos) 

1796 n_states = sum(map(lambda file_info: file_info.n_states, file_infos)) 

1797 LOGGER.debug("n_files found: %d", n_files) 

1798 LOGGER.debug("n_states estimated: %d", n_states) 

1799 

1800 # convert negative state indexes into positive ones 

1801 if state_filter is not None: 

1802 state_filter = _negative_to_positive_state_indexes(state_filter, n_states) 

1803 

1804 # if using buffered reading, we load one state at a time 

1805 # into memory 

1806 if buffered_reading: 

1807 file_infos_tmp: List[MemoryInfo] = [] 

1808 n_previous_states = 0 

1809 for minfo in file_infos: 

1810 for i_file_state in range(minfo.n_states): 

1811 i_global_state = n_previous_states + i_file_state 

1812 

1813 # do we need to skip this one 

1814 if state_filter and i_global_state not in state_filter: 

1815 continue 

1816 

1817 file_infos_tmp.append( 

1818 MemoryInfo( 

1819 start=minfo.start + i_file_state * bytes_per_state, 

1820 length=bytes_per_state, 

1821 filepath=minfo.filepath, 

1822 n_states=1, 

1823 filesize=minfo.filesize, 

1824 use_mmap=minfo.n_states != 1, 

1825 ) 

1826 ) 

1827 

1828 n_previous_states += minfo.n_states 

1829 file_infos = file_infos_tmp 

1830 

1831 LOGGER.debug("buffers: %s", pprint.pformat([info.__dict__ for info in file_infos])) 

1832 

1833 # number of states and if buffered reading is used 

1834 n_states_selected = sum(map(lambda file_info: file_info.n_states, file_infos)) 

1835 yield n_states_selected 

1836 

1837 sub_file_infos = [file_infos] if not buffered_reading else [[info] for info in file_infos] 

1838 for sub_file_info_list in sub_file_infos: 

1839 buffer, n_states = D3plot._read_file_from_memory_info(sub_file_info_list) 

1840 yield buffer, n_states 

1841 

1842 def _read_femzip_file_generator( 

1843 self, buffered_reading: bool, state_filter: Union[None, Set[int]] 

1844 ) -> typing.Any: 

1845 """Generator function for reading femzipped d3plot files 

1846 

1847 Parameters 

1848 ---------- 

1849 buffered_reading: bool 

1850 load state by state 

1851 state_filter: Union[None, Set[int]] 

1852 which states to filter out 

1853 

1854 Yields 

1855 ------ 

1856 buffer: BinaryBuffer 

1857 binary buffer of a file 

1858 n_states: int 

1859 from second yield on, number of states for buffers 

1860 """ 

1861 

1862 femzip_api = self._femzip_info.api 

1863 

1864 # (1) STATES 

1865 # number of states and if buffered reading is used 

1866 buffer_info = self._femzip_info.buffer_info 

1867 n_timesteps: int = buffer_info.n_timesteps 

1868 

1869 # convert negative filter indexes 

1870 state_filter_parsed: Set[int] = set() 

1871 if state_filter is not None: 

1872 state_filter_parsed = _negative_to_positive_state_indexes(state_filter, n_timesteps) 

1873 n_states_to_load = len(state_filter) 

1874 else: 

1875 n_states_to_load = n_timesteps 

1876 state_filter_parsed = set(range(n_timesteps)) 

1877 

1878 yield n_states_to_load 

1879 

1880 n_files_to_load_at_once = n_timesteps if not buffered_reading else 1 

1881 # pylint: disable = invalid-name 

1882 BufferStateType = ctypes.c_float * (buffer_info.size_state * n_files_to_load_at_once) 

1883 buffer_state = BufferStateType() 

1884 

1885 buffer = BinaryBuffer() 

1886 buffer.memoryview = memoryview(buffer_state) 

1887 

1888 # do the thing 

1889 i_timesteps_read = 0 

1890 max_timestep = max(state_filter_parsed) if state_filter_parsed else 0 

1891 for i_timestep in range(n_timesteps): 

1892 

1893 # buffer offset 

1894 buffer_current_state = buffer.memoryview[i_timesteps_read * buffer_info.size_state :] 

1895 

1896 # read state 

1897 femzip_api.read_single_state(i_timestep, buffer_info, state_buffer=buffer_current_state) 

1898 

1899 if i_timestep in state_filter_parsed: 

1900 i_timesteps_read += 1 

1901 

1902 # Note: 

1903 # the buffer is re-used here! This saves memory BUT 

1904 # if memory is not copied we overwrite the same again and again 

1905 # This is ok for buffered reading thus indirectly safe 

1906 # since elsewhere the arrays get copied but keep it in mind! 

1907 if i_timesteps_read != 0 and i_timesteps_read % n_files_to_load_at_once == 0: 

1908 yield buffer, i_timesteps_read 

1909 i_timesteps_read = 0 

1910 

1911 # stop in case we have everything we needed 

1912 if i_timestep >= max_timestep: 

1913 if i_timesteps_read != 0: 

1914 yield buffer, i_timesteps_read 

1915 break 

1916 

1917 # do the thing 

1918 femzip_api.close_current_file() 

1919 

1920 def _read_states_femzip_advanced(self, filepath: str) -> None: 

1921 """Read d3plot variables with advanced femzip API 

1922 

1923 Parameters 

1924 ---------- 

1925 filepath: str 

1926 path to the femzipped d3plot 

1927 """ 

1928 

1929 # convert filter 

1930 d3plot_array_filter = set(self.state_array_filter) if self.state_array_filter else None 

1931 

1932 # what vars are inside? 

1933 api = self._femzip_info.api 

1934 file_metadata = api.get_file_metadata(filepath) 

1935 

1936 if file_metadata.number_of_timesteps <= 0: 

1937 return 

1938 

1939 # filter femzip vars according to requested d3plot vars 

1940 file_metadata_filtered = filter_femzip_variables( 

1941 file_metadata, 

1942 d3plot_array_filter, 

1943 ) 

1944 

1945 # read femzip arrays 

1946 result_arrays = api.read_variables( 

1947 file_metadata=file_metadata_filtered, 

1948 n_parts=self.header.n_parts, 

1949 n_rigid_walls=self._n_rigid_walls, 

1950 n_rigid_wall_vars=self.header.n_rigid_wall_vars, 

1951 n_airbag_particles=self._airbag_info.n_particles, 

1952 n_airbags=self._airbag_info.n_airbags, 

1953 state_filter=self.state_filter, 

1954 ) 

1955 

1956 # special case arrays which need extra parsing 

1957 keys_to_remove = [] 

1958 for (fz_index, fz_name, fz_cat), array in result_arrays.items(): 

1959 

1960 # global vars 

1961 if fz_cat == FemzipVariableCategory.GLOBAL: 

1962 keys_to_remove.append((fz_index, fz_name, fz_cat)) 

1963 self._read_states_globals( 

1964 state_data=array, 

1965 var_index=0, 

1966 array_dict=self.arrays, 

1967 ) 

1968 

1969 # parts and rigid walls 

1970 elif fz_cat == FemzipVariableCategory.PART: 

1971 keys_to_remove.append((fz_index, fz_name, fz_cat)) 

1972 

1973 var_index = self._read_states_parts( 

1974 state_data=array, var_index=0, array_dict=self.arrays 

1975 ) 

1976 

1977 self._read_states_rigid_walls( 

1978 state_data=array, var_index=var_index, array_dict=self.arrays 

1979 ) 

1980 

1981 for key in keys_to_remove: 

1982 del result_arrays[key] 

1983 

1984 # transfer arrays 

1985 mapper = FemzipMapper() 

1986 mapper.map(result_arrays) 

1987 

1988 # save arrays 

1989 for plt_name, arr in mapper.d3plot_arrays.items(): 

1990 

1991 # femzip sometimes stores strain in solid history vars 

1992 # but also sometimes separately 

1993 if ( 

1994 plt_name == ArrayType.element_solid_history_variables 

1995 and self.header.has_element_strain 

1996 and ArrayType.element_solid_strain not in mapper.d3plot_arrays 

1997 ): 

1998 self.arrays[ArrayType.element_solid_strain] = arr[:, :, :, :6] 

1999 tmp_array = arr[:, :, :, 6:] 

2000 if all(tmp_array.shape): 

2001 self.arrays[plt_name] = tmp_array 

2002 else: 

2003 self.arrays[plt_name] = arr 

2004 

2005 # ELEMENT DELETION 

2006 # 

2007 # somehow element deletion info is extra ... 

2008 # buffer_info 

2009 buffer_info = self._femzip_info.buffer_info 

2010 deletion_array = api.read_state_deletion_info( 

2011 buffer_info=buffer_info, state_filter=self.state_filter 

2012 ) 

2013 self._read_states_is_alive(state_data=deletion_array, var_index=0, array_dict=self.arrays) 

2014 

2015 # TIMESTEPS 

2016 timestep_array = np.array( 

2017 [buffer_info.timesteps[i_timestep] for i_timestep in range(buffer_info.n_timesteps)], 

2018 dtype=self.header.ftype, 

2019 ) 

2020 self.arrays[ArrayType.global_timesteps] = timestep_array

2089 def _read_material_section(self): 

2090 """This function reads the material type section""" 

2091 

2092 if not self._buffer: 

2093 return 

2094 

2095 if not self.header.has_material_type_section: 

2096 return 

2097 

2098 LOGGER.debug("_read_material_section start at byte %d", self.geometry_section_size) 

2099 

2100 position = self.geometry_section_size 

2101 

2102 # failsafe 

2103 original_position = self.geometry_section_size 

2104 blocksize = (2 + self.header.n_parts) * self.header.wordsize 

2105 

2106 try: 

2107 

2108 # Material Type Data 

2109 # 

2110 # "This data is required because those shell elements 

2111 # that are in a rigid body have no element data output 

2112 # in the state data section." 

2113 # 

2114 # "The normal length of the shell element state data is: 

2115 # NEL4 * NV2D, when the MATTYP flag is set the length is: 

2116 # (NEL4 – NUMRBE) * NV2D. When reading the shell element data, 

2117 # the material number must be checked against IRBRTYP list to 

2118 # find the element’s material type. If the type = 20, then 

2119 # all the values for the element to zero." (Manual 03.2016) 

2120 

2121 self._material_section_info.n_rigid_shells = int( 

2122 self._buffer.read_number(position, self._header.itype) 

2123 ) # type: ignore 

2124 position += self.header.wordsize 

2125 

2126 test_nummat = self._buffer.read_number(position, self._header.itype) 

2127 position += self.header.wordsize 

2128 

2129 if test_nummat != self.header.n_parts: 

2130 raise RuntimeError( 

2131 "nmmat (header) != nmmat (material type data): " 

2132 f"{self.header.n_parts} != {test_nummat}", 

2133 ) 

2134 

2135 self.arrays[ArrayType.part_material_type] = self._buffer.read_ndarray( 

2136 position, self.header.n_parts * self.header.wordsize, 1, self.header.itype 

2137 ) 

2138 position += self.header.n_parts * self.header.wordsize 

2139 

2140 except Exception: 

2141 # print info 

2142 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

2143 LOGGER.warning("A failure in %s was caught:\n%s", "_read_material_section", trb_msg) 

2144 

2145 # fix position 

2146 position = original_position + blocksize 

2147 

2148 self.geometry_section_size = position 

2149 LOGGER.debug("_read_material_section end at byte %d", self.geometry_section_size)

2190 def _read_sph_element_data_flags(self): 

2191 """Read the sph element data flags""" 

2192 

2193 if not self._buffer: 

2194 return 

2195 

2196 if not self.header.n_sph_nodes: 

2197 return 

2198 

2199 LOGGER.debug("_read_sph_element_data_flags start at byte %d", self.geometry_section_size) 

2200 

2201 position = self.geometry_section_size 

2202 

2203 sph_element_data_words = { 

2204 "isphfg1": (position, self._header.itype), 

2205 "isphfg2": (position + 1 * self.header.wordsize, self._header.itype), 

2206 "isphfg3": (position + 2 * self.header.wordsize, self._header.itype), 

2207 "isphfg4": (position + 3 * self.header.wordsize, self._header.itype), 

2208 "isphfg5": (position + 4 * self.header.wordsize, self._header.itype), 

2209 "isphfg6": (position + 5 * self.header.wordsize, self._header.itype), 

2210 "isphfg7": (position + 6 * self.header.wordsize, self._header.itype), 

2211 "isphfg8": (position + 7 * self.header.wordsize, self._header.itype), 

2212 "isphfg9": (position + 8 * self.header.wordsize, self._header.itype), 

2213 "isphfg10": (position + 9 * self.header.wordsize, self._header.itype), 

2214 "isphfg11": (position + 10 * self.header.wordsize, self._header.itype), 

2215 } 

2216 

2217 sph_header_data = self.header.read_words(self._buffer, sph_element_data_words) 

2218 

2219 self._sph_info.n_sph_array_length = sph_header_data["isphfg1"] 

2220 self._sph_info.has_influence_radius = sph_header_data["isphfg2"] != 0 

2221 self._sph_info.has_particle_pressure = sph_header_data["isphfg3"] != 0 

2222 self._sph_info.has_stresses = sph_header_data["isphfg4"] != 0 

2223 self._sph_info.has_plastic_strain = sph_header_data["isphfg5"] != 0 

2224 self._sph_info.has_material_density = sph_header_data["isphfg6"] != 0 

2225 self._sph_info.has_internal_energy = sph_header_data["isphfg7"] != 0 

2226 self._sph_info.has_n_affecting_neighbors = sph_header_data["isphfg8"] != 0 

2227 self._sph_info.has_strain_and_strainrate = sph_header_data["isphfg9"] != 0 

2228 self._sph_info.has_true_strains = sph_header_data["isphfg9"] < 0 

2229 self._sph_info.has_mass = sph_header_data["isphfg10"] != 0 

2230 self._sph_info.n_sph_history_vars = sph_header_data["isphfg11"] 

2231 

2232 if self._sph_info.n_sph_array_length != 11: 

2233 msg = ( 

2234 "Detected inconsistency: " 

2235 f"isphfg = {self._sph_info.n_sph_array_length} but must be 11." 

2236 ) 

2237 raise RuntimeError(msg) 

2238 

2239 self._sph_info.n_sph_vars = ( 

2240 sph_header_data["isphfg2"] 

2241 + sph_header_data["isphfg3"] 

2242 + sph_header_data["isphfg4"] 

2243 + sph_header_data["isphfg5"] 

2244 + sph_header_data["isphfg6"] 

2245 + sph_header_data["isphfg7"] 

2246 + sph_header_data["isphfg8"] 

2247 + abs(sph_header_data["isphfg9"]) 

2248 + sph_header_data["isphfg10"] 

2249 + sph_header_data["isphfg11"] 

2250 + 1 

2251 ) # material number 

2252 

2253 self.geometry_section_size += sph_header_data["isphfg1"] * self.header.wordsize 

2254 LOGGER.debug("_read_sph_element_data_flags end at byte %d", self.geometry_section_size)

2256 def _read_particle_data(self): 

2257 """Read the geometry section for particle data (airbags)""" 

2258 

2259 if not self._buffer: 

2260 return 

2261 

2262 if "npefg" not in self.header.raw_header: 

2263 return 

2264 npefg = self.header.raw_header["npefg"] 

2265 

2266 # let's stick to the manual, too lazy to decypther this test 

2267 if npefg <= 0 or npefg > 10000000: 

2268 return 

2269 

2270 LOGGER.debug("_read_particle_data start at byte %d", self.geometry_section_size) 

2271 

2272 position = self.geometry_section_size 

2273 

2274 airbag_header = { 

2275 # number of airbags 

2276 "npartgas": npefg % 1000, 

2277 # ? 

2278 "subver": npefg // 1000, 

2279 } 

2280 

2281 particle_geometry_data_words = { 

2282 # number of geometry variables 

2283 "ngeom": (position, self._header.itype), 

2284 # number of state variables 

2285 "nvar": (position + 1 * self.header.wordsize, self._header.itype), 

2286 # number of particles 

2287 "npart": (position + 2 * self.header.wordsize, self._header.itype), 

2288 # number of state geometry variables 

2289 "nstgeom": (position + 3 * self.header.wordsize, self._header.itype), 

2290 } 

2291 

2292 self.header.read_words(self._buffer, particle_geometry_data_words, airbag_header) 

2293 position += 4 * self.header.wordsize 

2294 

2295 # transfer to info object 

2296 self._airbag_info.n_airbags = npefg % 1000 

2297 self._airbag_info.subver = npefg // 1000 

2298 self._airbag_info.n_geometric_variables = airbag_header["ngeom"] 

2299 self._airbag_info.n_particle_state_variables = airbag_header["nvar"] 

2300 self._airbag_info.n_particles = airbag_header["npart"] 

2301 self._airbag_info.n_airbag_state_variables = airbag_header["nstgeom"] 

2302 

2303 if self._airbag_info.subver == 4: 

2304 # number of chambers 

2305 self._airbag_info.n_chambers = self._buffer.read_number(position, self._header.itype) 

2306 position += self.header.wordsize 

2307 

2308 n_airbag_variables = self._airbag_info.get_n_variables() 

2309 

2310 # safety 

2311 # from here on the code may fail 

2312 original_position = position 

2313 blocksize = 9 * n_airbag_variables * self.header.wordsize 

2314 

2315 try: 

2316 # variable typecodes 

2317 self.arrays[ArrayType.airbag_variable_types] = self._buffer.read_ndarray( 

2318 position, n_airbag_variables * self.header.wordsize, 1, self._header.itype 

2319 ) 

2320 position += n_airbag_variables * self.header.wordsize 

2321 

2322 # airbag variable names 

2323 # every word is an ascii char 

2324 airbag_variable_names = [] 

2325 var_width = 8 

2326 

2327 for i_variable in range(n_airbag_variables): 

2328 name = self._buffer.read_text( 

2329 position + (i_variable * var_width) * self.header.wordsize, 

2330 var_width * self.header.wordsize, 

2331 ) 

2332 airbag_variable_names.append(name[:: self.header.wordsize]) 

2333 

2334 self.arrays[ArrayType.airbag_variable_names] = airbag_variable_names 

2335 position += n_airbag_variables * var_width * self.header.wordsize 

2336 

2337 except Exception: 

2338 

2339 # print info 

2340 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

2341 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

2342 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_particle_data", trb_msg) 

2343 

2344 # fix position 

2345 position = original_position + blocksize 

2346 

2347 # update position marker 

2348 self.geometry_section_size = position 

2349 LOGGER.debug("_read_particle_data start at byte %d", self.geometry_section_size)
