2351 # pylint: disable = too-many-branches 

2352 def _read_geometry_data(self): 

2353 """Read the data from the geometry section""" 

2354 

2355 if not self._buffer: 

2356 return 

2357 

2358 LOGGER.debug("_read_geometry_data start at byte %d", self.geometry_section_size) 

2359 

2360 # not sure but I think never used by LS-Dyna 

2361 # anyway needs to be detected in the header and not here, 

2362 # though it is mentioned in this section of the database manual 

2363 # 

2364 # is_packed = True if self.header['ndim'] == 3 else False 

2365 # if is_packed: 

2366 # raise RuntimeError("Can not deal with packed "\ 

2367 # "geometry data (ndim == {}).".format(self.header['ndim'])) 

2368 

2369 position = self.geometry_section_size 

2370 

2371 # node coords 

2372 n_nodes = self.header.n_nodes 

2373 n_dimensions = self.header.n_dimensions 

2374 section_word_length = n_dimensions * n_nodes 

2375 try: 

2376 node_coordinates = self._buffer.read_ndarray( 

2377 position, section_word_length * self.header.wordsize, 1, self.header.ftype 

2378 ).reshape((n_nodes, n_dimensions)) 

2379 self.arrays[ArrayType.node_coordinates] = node_coordinates 

2380 except Exception: 

2381 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

2382 msg = "A failure in %d was caught:\n%s" 

2383 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_geometry_data, node_coordinates", trb_msg) 

2384 finally: 

2385 position += section_word_length * self.header.wordsize 

2386 

2387 # solid data 

2388 n_solids = self.header.n_solids 

2389 section_word_length = 9 * n_solids 

2390 try: 

2391 elem_solid_data = self._buffer.read_ndarray( 

2392 position, section_word_length * self.header.wordsize, 1, self._header.itype 

2393 ).reshape((n_solids, 9)) 

2394 solid_connectivity = elem_solid_data[:, :8] 

2395 solid_part_indexes = elem_solid_data[:, 8] 

2396 self.arrays[ArrayType.element_solid_node_indexes] = solid_connectivity - FORTRAN_OFFSET 

2397 self.arrays[ArrayType.element_solid_part_indexes] = solid_part_indexes - FORTRAN_OFFSET 

2398 except Exception: 

2399 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

2400 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

2401 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_geometry_data, solids_geometry", trb_msg) 

2402 finally: 

2403 position += section_word_length * self.header.wordsize 

2404 

2405 # ten node solids extra nodes 

2406 if self.header.has_solid_2_extra_nodes: 

2407 section_word_length = 2 * n_solids 

2408 try: 

2409 self.arrays[ 

2410 ArrayType.element_solid_extra_nodes 

2411 ] = elem_solid_data = self._buffer.read_ndarray( 

2412 position, section_word_length * self.header.wordsize, 1, self._header.itype 

2413 ).reshape( 

2414 (n_solids, 2) 

2415 ) 

2416 except Exception: 

2417 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

2418 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

2419 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_geometry_data, ten_node_solids", trb_msg) 

2420 finally: 

2421 position += section_word_length * self.header.wordsize 

2422 

2423 # 8 node thick shells 

2424 n_thick_shells = self.header.n_thick_shells 

2425 section_word_length = 9 * n_thick_shells 

2426 try: 

2427 elem_tshell_data = self._buffer.read_ndarray( 

2428 position, section_word_length * self.header.wordsize, 1, self._header.itype 

2429 ).reshape((self.header.n_thick_shells, 9)) 

2430 self.arrays[ArrayType.element_tshell_node_indexes] = ( 

2431 elem_tshell_data[:, :8] - FORTRAN_OFFSET 

2432 ) 

2433 self.arrays[ArrayType.element_tshell_part_indexes] = ( 

2434 elem_tshell_data[:, 8] - FORTRAN_OFFSET 

2435 ) 

2436 except Exception: 

2437 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

2438 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

2439 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_geometry_data, tshells_geometry", trb_msg) 

2440 finally: 

2441 position += section_word_length * self.header.wordsize 

2442 

2443 # beams 

2444 n_beams = self.header.n_beams 

2445 section_word_length = 6 * n_beams 

2446 try: 

2447 elem_beam_data = self._buffer.read_ndarray( 

2448 position, section_word_length * self.header.wordsize, 1, self._header.itype 

2449 ).reshape((n_beams, 6)) 

2450 self.arrays[ArrayType.element_beam_part_indexes] = elem_beam_data[:, 5] - FORTRAN_OFFSET 

2451 self.arrays[ArrayType.element_beam_node_indexes] = ( 

2452 elem_beam_data[:, :5] - FORTRAN_OFFSET 

2453 ) 

2454 except Exception: 

2455 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

2456 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

2457 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_geometry_data, beams_geometry", trb_msg) 

2458 finally: 

2459 position += section_word_length * self.header.wordsize 

2460 

2461 # shells 

2462 n_shells = self.header.n_shells 

2463 section_word_length = 5 * n_shells 

2464 try: 

2465 elem_shell_data = self._buffer.read_ndarray( 

2466 position, section_word_length * self.header.wordsize, 1, self._header.itype 

2467 ).reshape((self.header.n_shells, 5)) 

2468 self.arrays[ArrayType.element_shell_node_indexes] = ( 

2469 elem_shell_data[:, :4] - FORTRAN_OFFSET 

2470 ) 

2471 self.arrays[ArrayType.element_shell_part_indexes] = ( 

2472 elem_shell_data[:, 4] - FORTRAN_OFFSET 

2473 ) 

2474 except Exception: 

2475 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

2476 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

2477 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_geometry_data, shells_geometry", trb_msg) 

2478 finally: 

2479 position += section_word_length * self.header.wordsize 

2480 

2481 # update word position 

2482 self.geometry_section_size = position 

2483 

2484 LOGGER.debug("_read_geometry_data end at byte %d", self.geometry_section_size) 

2485 

2486 def _read_user_ids(self): 

2487 

2488 if not self._buffer: 

2489 return 

2490 

2491 if not self.header.has_numbering_section: 

2492 self.arrays[ArrayType.node_ids] = np.arange( 

2493 FORTRAN_OFFSET, self.header.n_nodes + FORTRAN_OFFSET, dtype=self.header.itype 

2494 ) 

2495 self.arrays[ArrayType.element_solid_ids] = np.arange( 

2496 FORTRAN_OFFSET, self.header.n_solids + FORTRAN_OFFSET, dtype=self.header.itype 

2497 ) 

2498 self.arrays[ArrayType.element_beam_ids] = np.arange( 

2499 FORTRAN_OFFSET, self.header.n_beams + FORTRAN_OFFSET, dtype=self.header.itype 

2500 ) 

2501 self.arrays[ArrayType.element_shell_ids] = np.arange( 

2502 FORTRAN_OFFSET, self.header.n_shells + FORTRAN_OFFSET, dtype=self.header.itype 

2503 ) 

2504 self.arrays[ArrayType.element_tshell_ids] = np.arange( 

2505 FORTRAN_OFFSET, self.header.n_thick_shells + FORTRAN_OFFSET, dtype=self.header.itype 

2506 ) 

2507 self.arrays[ArrayType.part_ids] = np.arange( 

2508 FORTRAN_OFFSET, self.header.n_parts + FORTRAN_OFFSET, dtype=self.header.itype 

2509 ) 

2510 return 

2511 

2512 LOGGER.debug("_read_user_ids start at byte %d", self.geometry_section_size) 

2513 

2514 position = self.geometry_section_size 

2515 

2516 # safety 

2517 original_position = position 

2518 blocksize = self.header.raw_header["narbs"] * self.header.wordsize 

2519 

2520 try: 

2521 numbering_words = { 

2522 "nsort": (position, self._header.itype), 

2523 "nsrh": (position + 1 * self.header.wordsize, self._header.itype), 

2524 "nsrb": (position + 2 * self.header.wordsize, self._header.itype), 

2525 "nsrs": (position + 3 * self.header.wordsize, self._header.itype), 

2526 "nsrt": (position + 4 * self.header.wordsize, self._header.itype), 

2527 "nsortd": (position + 5 * self.header.wordsize, self._header.itype), 

2528 "nsrhd": (position + 6 * self.header.wordsize, self._header.itype), 

2529 "nsrbd": (position + 7 * self.header.wordsize, self._header.itype), 

2530 "nsrsd": (position + 8 * self.header.wordsize, self._header.itype), 

2531 "nsrtd": (position + 9 * self.header.wordsize, self._header.itype), 

2532 } 

2533 

2534 extra_numbering_words = { 

2535 "nsrma": (position + 10 * self.header.wordsize, self._header.itype), 

2536 "nsrmu": (position + 11 * self.header.wordsize, self._header.itype), 

2537 "nsrmp": (position + 12 * self.header.wordsize, self._header.itype), 

2538 "nsrtm": (position + 13 * self.header.wordsize, self._header.itype), 

2539 "numrbs": (position + 14 * self.header.wordsize, self._header.itype), 

2540 "nmmat": (position + 15 * self.header.wordsize, self._header.itype), 

2541 } 

2542 

2543 numbering_header = self.header.read_words(self._buffer, numbering_words) 

2544 position += len(numbering_words) * self.header.wordsize 

2545 

2546 # let's make life easier 

2547 info = self._numbering_info 

2548 

2549 # transfer first bunch 

2550 info.ptr_node_ids = abs(numbering_header["nsort"]) 

2551 info.has_material_ids = numbering_header["nsort"] < 0 

2552 info.ptr_solid_ids = numbering_header["nsrh"] 

2553 info.ptr_beam_ids = numbering_header["nsrb"] 

2554 info.ptr_shell_ids = numbering_header["nsrs"] 

2555 info.ptr_thick_shell_ids = numbering_header["nsrt"] 

2556 info.n_nodes = numbering_header["nsortd"] 

2557 info.n_solids = numbering_header["nsrhd"] 

2558 info.n_beams = numbering_header["nsrbd"] 

2559 info.n_shells = numbering_header["nsrsd"] 

2560 info.n_thick_shells = numbering_header["nsrtd"] 

2561 

2562 if info.has_material_ids: 

2563 

2564 # read extra header 

2565 self.header.read_words(self._buffer, extra_numbering_words, numbering_header) 

2566 position += len(extra_numbering_words) * self.header.wordsize 

2567 

2568 # transfer more 

2569 info.ptr_material_ids = numbering_header["nsrma"] 

2570 info.ptr_material_ids_defined_order = numbering_header["nsrmu"] 

2571 info.ptr_material_ids_crossref = numbering_header["nsrmp"] 

2572 info.n_parts = numbering_header["nsrtm"] 

2573 info.n_rigid_bodies = numbering_header["numrbs"] 

2574 info.n_parts2 = numbering_header["nmmat"] 

2575 else: 

2576 info.n_parts = self.header.n_parts 

2577 

2578 # let's do a quick check 

2579 n_words_computed = ( 

2580 len(numbering_header) 

2581 + info.n_nodes 

2582 + info.n_shells 

2583 + info.n_beams 

2584 + info.n_solids 

2585 + info.n_thick_shells 

2586 + info.n_parts * 3 

2587 ) 

2588 if n_words_computed != self.header.n_numbering_section_words: 

2589 warn_msg = ( 

2590 "ID section: The computed word count does " 

2591 "not match the header word count: %d != %d." 

2592 " The ID arrays might contain errors." 

2593 ) 

2594 LOGGER.warning(warn_msg, n_words_computed, self.header.n_numbering_section_words) 

2595 # node ids 

2596 array_length = info.n_nodes * self.header.wordsize 

2597 self.arrays[ArrayType.node_ids] = self._buffer.read_ndarray( 

2598 position, array_length, 1, self._header.itype 

2599 ) 

2600 position += array_length 

2601 # solid ids 

2602 array_length = info.n_solids * self.header.wordsize 

2603 self.arrays[ArrayType.element_solid_ids] = self._buffer.read_ndarray( 

2604 position, array_length, 1, self._header.itype 

2605 ) 

2606 position += array_length 

2607 # beam ids 

2608 array_length = info.n_beams * self.header.wordsize 

2609 self.arrays[ArrayType.element_beam_ids] = self._buffer.read_ndarray( 

2610 position, array_length, 1, self._header.itype 

2611 ) 

2612 position += array_length 

2613 # shell ids 

2614 array_length = info.n_shells * self.header.wordsize 

2615 self.arrays[ArrayType.element_shell_ids] = self._buffer.read_ndarray( 

2616 position, array_length, 1, self._header.itype 

2617 ) 

2618 position += array_length 

2619 # tshell ids 

2620 array_length = info.n_thick_shells * self.header.wordsize 

2621 self.arrays[ArrayType.element_tshell_ids] = self._buffer.read_ndarray( 

2622 position, array_length, 1, self._header.itype 

2623 ) 

2624 position += array_length 

2625 

2626 # part ids 

2627 # 

2628 # this makes no sense but materials are output three times at this section 

2629 # but the length of the array (nmmat) is only output if nsort < 0. In 

2630 # the other case the length is unknown ... 

2631 # 

2632 # Bugfix: 

2633 # The material arrays (three times) are always output, even if nsort < 0 

2634 # which means they are not used. Quite confusing, especially since nmmat 

2635 # is output in the main header and numbering header. 

2636 # 

2637 if "nmmat" in numbering_header: 

2638 

2639 if info.n_parts != self.header.n_parts: 

2640 err_msg = ( 

2641 "nmmat in the file header (%d) and in the " 

2642 "numbering header (%d) are inconsistent." 

2643 ) 

2644 raise RuntimeError(err_msg, self.header.n_parts, info.n_parts) 

2645 

2646 array_length = info.n_parts * self.header.wordsize 

2647 

2648 self.arrays[ArrayType.part_ids] = self._buffer.read_ndarray( 

2649 position, info.n_parts * self.header.wordsize, 1, self._header.itype 

2650 ) 

2651 position += info.n_parts * self.header.wordsize 

2652 

2653 self.arrays[ArrayType.part_ids_unordered] = self._buffer.read_ndarray( 

2654 position, info.n_parts * self.header.wordsize, 1, self._header.itype 

2655 ) 

2656 position += info.n_parts * self.header.wordsize 

2657 

2658 self.arrays[ArrayType.part_ids_cross_references] = self._buffer.read_ndarray( 

2659 position, info.n_parts * self.header.wordsize, 1, self._header.itype 

2660 ) 

2661 position += info.n_parts * self.header.wordsize 

2662 

2663 else: 

2664 position += 3 * self.header.n_parts * self.header.wordsize 

2665 

2666 except Exception: 

2667 # print info 

2668 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

2669 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

2670 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_user_ids", trb_msg) 

2671 

2672 # fix position 

2673 position = original_position + blocksize 

2674 

2675 # update position 

2676 self.geometry_section_size = position 

2677 LOGGER.debug("_read_user_ids end at byte %d", self.geometry_section_size) 

2678 

2679 def _read_rigid_body_description(self): 

2680 """Read the rigid body description section""" 

2681 

2682 if not self._buffer: 

2683 return 

2684 

2685 if not self.header.has_rigid_body_data: 

2686 return 

2687 

2688 LOGGER.debug("_read_rigid_body_description start at byte %d", self.geometry_section_size) 

2689 

2690 position = self.geometry_section_size 

2691 

2692 rigid_body_description_header = { 

2693 "nrigid": self._buffer.read_number(position, self._header.itype) 

2694 } 

2695 position += self.header.wordsize 

2696 

2697 info = self._rigid_body_info 

2698 info.n_rigid_bodies = rigid_body_description_header["nrigid"] 

2699 

2700 rigid_bodies: List[RigidBodyMetadata] = [] 

2701 for _ in range(info.n_rigid_bodies): 

2702 rigid_body_info = { 

2703 # rigid body part internal number 

2704 "mrigid": self._buffer.read_number(position, self._header.itype), 

2705 # number of nodes in rigid body 

2706 "numnodr": self._buffer.read_number( 

2707 position + self.header.wordsize, self._header.itype 

2708 ), 

2709 } 

2710 position += 2 * self.header.wordsize 

2711 

2712 # internal node number of rigid body 

2713 array_length = rigid_body_info["numnodr"] * self.header.wordsize 

2714 rigid_body_info["noder"] = self._buffer.read_ndarray( 

2715 position, array_length, 1, self._header.itype 

2716 ) 

2717 position += array_length 

2718 

2719 # number of active (non-rigid) nodes 

2720 rigid_body_info["numnoda"] = self._buffer.read_number(position, self._header.itype) 

2721 position += self.header.wordsize 

2722 

2723 # internal node numbers of active nodes 

2724 array_length = rigid_body_info["numnoda"] * self.header.wordsize 

2725 rigid_body_info["nodea"] = self._buffer.read_ndarray( 

2726 position, array_length, 1, self._header.itype 

2727 ) 

2728 position += array_length 

2729 

2730 # transfer props 

2731 body_metadata = RigidBodyMetadata( 

2732 internal_number=rigid_body_info["mrigid"], 

2733 n_nodes=rigid_body_info["numnodr"], 

2734 node_indexes=rigid_body_info["noder"], 

2735 n_active_nodes=rigid_body_info["numnoda"], 

2736 active_node_indexes=rigid_body_info["nodea"], 

2737 ) 

2738 

2739 # append to list 

2740 rigid_bodies.append(body_metadata) 

2741 

2742 # save rigid body info to header 

2743 info.rigid_body_metadata_list = rigid_bodies 

2744 

2745 # save arrays 

2746 rigid_body_n_nodes = [] 

2747 rigid_body_part_indexes = [] 

2748 rigid_body_n_active_nodes = [] 

2749 rigid_body_node_indexes_list = [] 

2750 rigid_body_active_node_indexes_list = [] 

2751 for rigid_body_info in rigid_bodies: 

2752 rigid_body_part_indexes.append(rigid_body_info.internal_number) 

2753 rigid_body_n_nodes.append(rigid_body_info.n_nodes) 

2754 rigid_body_node_indexes_list.append(rigid_body_info.node_indexes - FORTRAN_OFFSET) 

2755 rigid_body_n_active_nodes.append(rigid_body_info.n_active_nodes) 

2756 rigid_body_active_node_indexes_list.append( 

2757 rigid_body_info.active_node_indexes - FORTRAN_OFFSET 

2758 ) 

2759 

2760 self.arrays[ArrayType.rigid_body_part_indexes] = ( 

2761 np.array(rigid_body_part_indexes, dtype=self._header.itype) - FORTRAN_OFFSET 

2762 ) 

2763 self.arrays[ArrayType.rigid_body_n_nodes] = np.array( 

2764 rigid_body_n_nodes, dtype=self._header.itype 

2765 ) 

2766 self.arrays[ArrayType.rigid_body_n_active_nodes] = np.array( 

2767 rigid_body_n_active_nodes, dtype=self._header.itype 

2768 ) 

2769 self.arrays[ArrayType.rigid_body_node_indexes_list] = rigid_body_node_indexes_list 

2770 self.arrays[ 

2771 ArrayType.rigid_body_active_node_indexes_list 

2772 ] = rigid_body_active_node_indexes_list 

2773 

2774 # update position 

2775 self.geometry_section_size = position 

2776 LOGGER.debug("_read_rigid_body_description end at byte %d", self.geometry_section_size) 

2777 

2778 def _read_sph_node_and_material_list(self): 

2779 """Read SPH node and material list""" 

2780 

2781 if not self._buffer: 

2782 return 

2783 

2784 if self.header.n_sph_nodes <= 0: 

2785 return 

2786 

2787 LOGGER.debug( 

2788 "_read_sph_node_and_material_list start at byte %d", self.geometry_section_size 

2789 ) 

2790 

2791 position = self.geometry_section_size 

2792 

2793 array_length = self.header.n_sph_nodes * self.header.wordsize * 2 

2794 try: 

2795 # read info array 

2796 sph_node_matlist = self._buffer.read_ndarray( 

2797 position, array_length, 1, self._header.itype 

2798 ).reshape((self.header.n_sph_nodes, 2)) 

2799 

2800 # save array 

2801 self.arrays[ArrayType.sph_node_indexes] = sph_node_matlist[:, 0] - FORTRAN_OFFSET 

2802 self.arrays[ArrayType.sph_node_material_index] = sph_node_matlist[:, 1] - FORTRAN_OFFSET 

2803 

2804 except Exception: 

2805 # print info 

2806 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

2807 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

2808 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_sph_node_and_material_list", trb_msg) 

2809 

2810 finally: 

2811 # update position 

2812 self.geometry_section_size += array_length 

2813 

2814 LOGGER.debug("_read_sph_node_and_material_list end at byte %d", self.geometry_section_size) 

2815 

2816 def _read_particle_geometry_data(self): 

2817 """Read the particle geometry data""" 

2818 

2819 if not self._buffer: 

2820 return 

2821 

2822 if "npefg" not in self.header.raw_header: 

2823 return 

2824 

2825 if self.header.raw_header["npefg"] <= 0: 

2826 return 

2827 

2828 LOGGER.debug("_read_particle_geometry_data start at byte %d", self.geometry_section_size) 

2829 

2830 info = self._airbag_info 

2831 

2832 position = self.geometry_section_size 

2833 

2834 # size of geometry section checking 

2835 ngeom = info.n_geometric_variables 

2836 if ngeom not in [4, 5]: 

2837 raise RuntimeError("variable ngeom in the airbag header must be 4 or 5.") 

2838 

2839 original_position = position 

2840 blocksize = info.n_airbags * ngeom * self.header.wordsize 

2841 try: 

2842 

2843 # extract geometry as a single array 

2844 array_length = blocksize 

2845 particle_geom_data = self._buffer.read_ndarray( 

2846 position, array_length, 1, self._header.itype 

2847 ).reshape((info.n_airbags, ngeom)) 

2848 position += array_length 

2849 

2850 # store arrays 

2851 self.arrays[ArrayType.airbags_first_particle_id] = particle_geom_data[:, 0] 

2852 self.arrays[ArrayType.airbags_n_particles] = particle_geom_data[:, 1] 

2853 self.arrays[ArrayType.airbags_ids] = particle_geom_data[:, 2] 

2854 self.arrays[ArrayType.airbags_n_gas_mixtures] = particle_geom_data[:, 3] 

2855 if ngeom == 5: 

2856 self.arrays[ArrayType.airbags_n_chambers] = particle_geom_data[:, 4] 

2857 

2858 except Exception: 

2859 # print info 

2860 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

2861 msg = "A failure in %d was caught:\n%s" 

2862 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_particle_geometry_data", trb_msg) 

2863 

2864 # fix position 

2865 position = original_position + blocksize 

2866 

2867 # update position 

2868 self.geometry_section_size = position 

2869 

2870 LOGGER.debug("_read_particle_geometry_data end at byte %d", self.geometry_section_size) 

2871 

2872 def _read_rigid_road_surface(self): 

2873 """Read rigid road surface data""" 

2874 

2875 if not self._buffer: 

2876 return 

2877 

2878 if not self.header.has_rigid_road_surface: 

2879 return 

2880 

2881 LOGGER.debug("_read_rigid_road_surface start at byte %d", self.geometry_section_size) 

2882 

2883 position = self.geometry_section_size 

2884 

2885 # read header 

2886 rigid_road_surface_words = { 

2887 "nnode": (position, self._header.itype), 

2888 "nseg": (position + 1 * self.header.wordsize, self._header.itype), 

2889 "nsurf": (position + 2 * self.header.wordsize, self._header.itype), 

2890 "motion": (position + 3 * self.header.wordsize, self._header.itype), 

2891 } 

2892 

2893 rigid_road_header = self.header.read_words(self._buffer, rigid_road_surface_words) 

2894 position += 4 * self.header.wordsize 

2895 

2896 self._rigid_road_info = RigidRoadInfo( 

2897 n_nodes=rigid_road_header["nnode"], 

2898 n_roads=rigid_road_header["nsurf"], 

2899 n_road_segments=rigid_road_header["nseg"], 

2900 motion=rigid_road_header["motion"], 

2901 ) 

2902 info = self._rigid_road_info 

2903 

2904 # node ids 

2905 array_length = info.n_nodes * self.header.wordsize 

2906 rigid_road_node_ids = self._buffer.read_ndarray( 

2907 position, array_length, 1, self._header.itype 

2908 ) 

2909 self.arrays[ArrayType.rigid_road_node_ids] = rigid_road_node_ids 

2910 position += array_length 

2911 

2912 # node xyz 

2913 array_length = info.n_nodes * 3 * self.header.wordsize 

2914 rigid_road_node_coords = self._buffer.read_ndarray( 

2915 position, array_length, 1, self.header.ftype 

2916 ).reshape((info.n_nodes, 3)) 

2917 self.arrays[ArrayType.rigid_road_node_coordinates] = rigid_road_node_coords 

2918 position += array_length 

2919 

2920 # read road segments 

2921 # Warning: must be copied 

2922 rigid_road_ids = np.empty(info.n_roads, dtype=self._header.itype) 

2923 rigid_road_nsegments = np.empty(info.n_roads, dtype=self._header.itype) 

2924 rigid_road_segment_node_ids = [] 

2925 

2926 # this array is created since the array database requires 

2927 # constant sized arrays, and we dump all segments into one 

2928 # array. In order to distinguish which segment 

2929 # belongs to which road, this new array keeps track of it 

2930 rigid_road_segment_road_id = [] 

2931 

2932 # n_total_segments = 0 

2933 for i_surf in range(info.n_roads): 

2934 # surface id 

2935 surf_id = self._buffer.read_number(position, self._header.itype) # type: ignore 

2936 position += self.header.wordsize 

2937 rigid_road_ids[i_surf] = surf_id 

2938 

2939 # number of segments of surface 

2940 surf_nseg = self._buffer.read_number( 

2941 position + 1 * self.header.wordsize, self._header.itype 

2942 ) # type: ignore 

2943 position += self.header.wordsize 

2944 rigid_road_nsegments[i_surf] = surf_nseg 

2945 

2946 # count total segments 

2947 # n_total_segments += surf_nseg 

2948 

2949 # node ids of surface segments 

2950 array_length = 4 * surf_nseg * self.header.wordsize 

2951 surf_segm_node_ids = self._buffer.read_ndarray( 

2952 position, # type: ignore 

2953 array_length, # type: ignore 

2954 1, 

2955 self._header.itype, 

2956 ).reshape((surf_nseg, 4)) 

2957 position += array_length 

2958 rigid_road_segment_node_ids.append(surf_segm_node_ids) 

2959 

2960 # remember road id for segments 

2961 rigid_road_segment_road_id += [surf_id] * surf_nseg 

2962 

2963 # save arrays 

2964 self.arrays[ArrayType.rigid_road_ids] = rigid_road_ids 

2965 self.arrays[ArrayType.rigid_road_n_segments] = rigid_road_nsegments 

2966 self.arrays[ArrayType.rigid_road_segment_node_ids] = np.concatenate( 

2967 rigid_road_segment_node_ids 

2968 ) 

2969 self.arrays[ArrayType.rigid_road_segment_road_id] = np.asarray(rigid_road_segment_road_id) 

2970 

2971 # update position 

2972 self.geometry_section_size = position 

2973 LOGGER.debug("_read_rigid_road_surface end at byte %d", self.geometry_section_size)

2976 def _read_extra_node_connectivity(self): 

2977 """Read the extra node data for creepy elements""" 

2978 

2979 if not self._buffer: 

2980 return 

2981 

2982 LOGGER.debug("_read_extra_node_connectivity start at byte %d", self.geometry_section_size) 

2983

2985 

2986 # extra 2 node connectivity for 10 node tetrahedron elements 

2987 if self.header.has_solid_2_extra_nodes: 

2988 array_length = 2 * self.header.n_solids * self.header.wordsize 

2989 try: 

2990 array = self._buffer.read_ndarray( 

2991 position, array_length, 1, self._header.itype 

2992 ).reshape((self.header.n_solids, 2)) 

2993 self.arrays[ArrayType.element_solid_node10_extra_node_indexes] = ( 

2994 array - FORTRAN_OFFSET 

2995 ) 

2996 except Exception: 

2997 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

2998 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

2999 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_extra_node_connectivity, solid10", trb_msg) 

3000 finally: 

3001 position += array_length 

3002 

3003 # 8 node shell elements 

3004 if self.header.n_shells_8_nodes > 0: 

3005 array_length = 5 * self.header.n_shells_8_nodes * self.header.wordsize

3009 ).reshape((self.header.n_shells_8_nodes, 5))

3011 array[:, 0] - FORTRAN_OFFSET 

3012 ) 

3013 self.arrays[ArrayType.element_shell_node8_extra_node_indexes] = ( 

3014 array[:, 1:] - FORTRAN_OFFSET 

3015 ) 

3016 except Exception:

3178 # pylint: disable = too-many-branches 

3179 @classmethod 

3180 def _read_header_part_contact_interface_titles( 

3181 cls, 

3182 header: D3plotHeader, 

3183 buffer: Union[BinaryBuffer, None], 

3184 geometry_section_size: int, 

3185 arrays: dict, 

3186 ) -> int: 

3187 """Read the header for the parts, contacts and interfaces 

3188 

3189 Parameters 

3190 ---------- 

3191 header: D3plotHeader 

3192 d3plot header 

3193 bb: BinaryBuffer 

3194 buffer holding geometry 

3195 geometry_section_size: int 

3196 size of the geometry section until now 

3197 arrays: dict 

3198 dictionary holding arrays and where arrays will be saved into 

3199 

3200 Returns 

3201 ------- 

3202 geometry_section_size: int 

3203 new size of the geometry section 

3204 """ 

3205 

3206 if not buffer: 

3207 return geometry_section_size 

3208 

3209 if header.filetype not in ( 

3210 D3plotFiletype.D3PLOT, 

3211 D3plotFiletype.D3PART, 

3212 D3plotFiletype.INTFOR, 

3213 ): 

3214 return geometry_section_size 

3215 

3216 LOGGER.debug( 

3217 "_read_header_part_contact_interface_titles start at byte %d", geometry_section_size 

3218 ) 

3219 

3220 position = geometry_section_size 

3221 

3222 # Security 

3223 # 

3224 # we try to read the titles ahead. If dyna writes multiple files 

3225 # then the first file is geometry only thus failing here has no 

3226 # impact on further state reading. 

3227 # If though states are compressed into the first file then we are 

3228 # in trouble here even when catching here. 

3229 try: 

3230 # there is only output if there is an eof marker 

3231 # at least I think I fixed such a bug in the past 

3232 if not cls._is_end_of_file_marker(buffer, position, header.ftype): 

3233 return geometry_section_size 

3234 

3235 position += header.wordsize 

3236 

3237 # section have types here according to what is inside 

3238 ntypes = [] 

3239 

3240 # read first ntype 

3241 current_ntype = buffer.read_number(position, header.itype) 

3242 

3243 while current_ntype in [90000, 90001, 90002, 90020]: 

3244 

3245 # title output 

3246 if current_ntype == 90000: 

3247 

3248 ntypes.append(current_ntype) 

3249 position += header.wordsize 

3250 

3251 # Bugfix: 

3252 # the titles are always 18*4 bytes, even if the wordsize 

3253 # is 8 bytes for the entire file. 

3254 titles_wordsize = 4 

3255 

3256 array_length = 18 * titles_wordsize 

3257 header.title2 = buffer.read_text(position, array_length) 

3258 position += array_length 

3259 

3260 # some title output 

3261 elif current_ntype in [90001, 90002, 90020]: 

3262 

3263 ntypes.append(current_ntype) 

3264 position += header.wordsize 

3265 

3266 # number of parts 

3267 entry_count = buffer.read_number(position, header.itype) 

3268 position += header.wordsize 

3269 

3270 # Bugfix: 

3271 # the titles are always 18*4 bytes, even if the wordsize 

3272 # is 8 bytes for the entire file. 

3273 titles_wordsize = 4 

3274 

3275 # part ids and corresponding titles 

3276 array_type = np.dtype( 

3277 [("ids", header.itype), ("titles", "S" + str(18 * titles_wordsize))] 

3278 ) 

3279 array_length = (header.wordsize + 18 * titles_wordsize) * int(entry_count) 

3280 tmp_arrays = buffer.read_ndarray(position, array_length, 1, array_type) 

3281 position += array_length 

3282 

3283 # save stuff 

3284 if current_ntype == 90001: 

3285 arrays[ArrayType.part_titles_ids] = tmp_arrays["ids"] 

3286 arrays[ArrayType.part_titles] = tmp_arrays["titles"] 

3287 elif current_ntype == 90002: 

3288 arrays[ArrayType.contact_title_ids] = tmp_arrays["ids"] 

3289 arrays[ArrayType.contact_titles] = tmp_arrays["titles"] 

3290 elif current_ntype == 90020: 

3291 arrays["icfd_part_title_ids"] = tmp_arrays["ids"] 

3292 arrays["icfd_part_titles"] = tmp_arrays["titles"] 

3293 

3294 # d3prop 

3295 elif current_ntype == 90100: 

3296 

3297 ntypes.append(current_ntype) 

3298 position += header.wordsize 

3299 

3300 # number of keywords 

3301 nline = buffer.read_number(position, header.itype) 

3302 position += header.wordsize 

3303 

3304 # Bugfix: 

3305 # the titles are always 18*4 bytes, even if the wordsize 

3306 # is 8 bytes for the entire file. 

3307 titles_wordsize = 4 

3308 

3309 # keywords 

3310 array_length = 20 * titles_wordsize * int(nline) 

3311 d3prop_keywords = buffer.read_ndarray( 

3312 position, array_length, 1, np.dtype("S" + str(titles_wordsize * 20)) 

3313 ) 

3314 position += array_length 

3315 

3316 # save 

3317 arrays["d3prop_keywords"] = d3prop_keywords 

3318 

3319 # not sure whether there is an eof file here 

3320 # do not have a test file to check ... 

3321 if cls._is_end_of_file_marker(buffer, position, header.ftype): 

3322 position += header.wordsize 

3323 

3324 # next one 

3325 if buffer.size <= position: 

3326 break 

3327 current_ntype = buffer.read_number(position, header.itype) 

3328 

3329 header.n_types = tuple(ntypes) 

3330 

3331 except Exception: 

3332 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

3333 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

3334 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_header_part_contact_interface_titles", trb_msg) 

3335 

3336 # remember position 

3337 geometry_section_size = position 

3338 LOGGER.debug( 

3339 "_read_header_part_contact_interface_titles end at byte %d", geometry_section_size 

3340 ) 

3341 

3342 return geometry_section_size 

3343 

3344 @staticmethod 

3345 def _read_states_allocate_arrays( 

3346 header: D3plotHeader, 

3347 material_section_info: MaterialSectionInfo, 

3348 airbag_info: AirbagInfo, 

3349 rigid_road_info: RigidRoadInfo, 

3350 rigid_body_info: RigidBodyInfo, 

3351 n_states: int, 

3352 n_rigid_walls: int, 

3353 n_parts: int, 

3354 array_names: Union[Iterable[str], None], 

3355 array_dict: dict, 

3356 ) -> None: 

3357 """Allocate the state arrays 

3358 

3359 Parameters 

3360 ---------- 

3361 header: D3plotHeader 

3362 header of the d3plot 

3363 material_section_info: MaterialSectionInfo 

3364 info about the material section data 

3365 airbag_info: AirbagInfo 

3366 info for airbags 

3367 rigid_road_info: RigidRoadInfo 

3368 info for rigid roads 

3369 rigid_body_info: RigidBodyInfo 

3370 info for rigid bodies 

3371 n_states: int 

3372 number of states to allocate memory for 

3373 n_rigid_walls: int 

3374 number of rigid walls 

3375 n_parts: int 

3376 number of parts 

3377 array_names: Union[Iterable[str], None] 

3378 names of state arrays to allocate (all if None) 

3379 array_dict: dict 

3380 dictionary to allocate arrays into 

3381 """ 

3382 

3383 # (1) ARRAY SHAPES 

3384 # general 

3385 n_dim = header.n_dimensions 

3386 # nodes 

3387 n_nodes = header.n_nodes 

3388 # solids 

3389 n_solids = header.n_solids 

3390 n_solids_thermal_vars = header.n_solid_thermal_vars 

3391 n_solids_strain_vars = 6 * header.has_element_strain * (header.n_solid_history_vars >= 6) 

3392 n_solid_thermal_strain_vars = 6 * header.has_solid_shell_thermal_strain_tensor 

3393 n_solid_plastic_strain_vars = 6 * header.has_solid_shell_plastic_strain_tensor 

3394 n_solid_layers = header.n_solid_layers 

3395 n_solids_history_vars = ( 

3396 header.n_solid_history_vars 

3397 - n_solids_strain_vars 

3398 - n_solid_thermal_strain_vars 

3399 - n_solid_plastic_strain_vars 

3400 ) 

3401 # thick shells 

3402 n_tshells = header.n_thick_shells 

3403 n_tshells_history_vars = header.n_shell_tshell_history_vars 

3404 n_tshells_layers = header.n_shell_tshell_layers 

3405 # beams 

3406 n_beams = header.n_beams 

3407 n_beams_history_vars = header.n_beam_history_vars 

3408 n_beam_vars = header.n_beam_vars 

3409 n_beams_layers = max( 

3410 int((-3 * n_beams_history_vars + n_beam_vars - 6) / (n_beams_history_vars + 5)), 0 

3411 ) 

3412 # shells 

3413 n_shells = header.n_shells 

3414 n_shells_reduced = header.n_shells - material_section_info.n_rigid_shells 

3415 n_shell_layers = header.n_shell_tshell_layers 

3416 n_shell_history_vars = header.n_shell_tshell_history_vars 

3417 # sph 

3418 allocate_sph = header.n_sph_nodes != 0 

3419 n_sph_particles = header.n_sph_nodes if allocate_sph else 0 

3420 # airbags 

3421 allocate_airbags = header.n_airbags != 0 

3422 n_airbags = header.n_airbags if allocate_airbags else 0 

3423 n_airbag_particles = airbag_info.n_particles if allocate_airbags else 0 

3424 # rigid roads 

3425 allocate_rigid_roads = rigid_road_info.n_roads != 0 

3426 n_roads = rigid_road_info.n_roads if allocate_rigid_roads else 0 

3427 # rigid bodies 

3428 n_rigid_bodies = rigid_body_info.n_rigid_bodies 

3429 

3430 # dictionary to lookup array types 

3431 state_array_shapes = { 

3432 # global 

3433 ArrayType.global_timesteps: [n_states], 

3434 ArrayType.global_kinetic_energy: [n_states], 

3435 ArrayType.global_internal_energy: [n_states], 

3436 ArrayType.global_total_energy: [n_states], 

3437 ArrayType.global_velocity: [n_states, 3], 

3438 # parts 

3439 ArrayType.part_internal_energy: [n_states, n_parts], 

3440 ArrayType.part_kinetic_energy: [n_states, n_parts], 

3441 ArrayType.part_velocity: [n_states, n_parts, 3], 

3442 ArrayType.part_mass: [n_states, n_parts], 

3443 ArrayType.part_hourglass_energy: [n_states, n_parts], 

3444 # rigid wall 

3445 ArrayType.rigid_wall_force: [n_states, n_rigid_walls], 

3446 ArrayType.rigid_wall_position: [n_states, n_rigid_walls, 3], 

3447 # nodes 

3448 ArrayType.node_temperature: [n_states, n_nodes, 3] 

3449 if header.has_node_temperature_layers 

3450 else [n_states, n_nodes], 

3451 ArrayType.node_heat_flux: [n_states, n_nodes, 3], 

3452 ArrayType.node_mass_scaling: [n_states, n_nodes], 

3453 ArrayType.node_displacement: [n_states, n_nodes, n_dim], 

3454 ArrayType.node_velocity: [n_states, n_nodes, n_dim], 

3455 ArrayType.node_acceleration: [n_states, n_nodes, n_dim], 

3456 ArrayType.node_temperature_gradient: [n_states, n_nodes], 

3457 ArrayType.node_residual_forces: [n_states, n_nodes, 3], 

3458 ArrayType.node_residual_moments: [n_states, n_nodes, 3], 

3459 # solids 

3460 ArrayType.element_solid_thermal_data: [n_states, n_solids, n_solids_thermal_vars], 

3461 ArrayType.element_solid_stress: [n_states, n_solids, n_solid_layers, 6], 

3462 ArrayType.element_solid_effective_plastic_strain: [n_states, n_solids, n_solid_layers], 

3463 ArrayType.element_solid_history_variables: [ 

3464 n_states, 

3465 n_solids, 

3466 n_solid_layers, 

3467 n_solids_history_vars, 

3468 ], 

3469 ArrayType.element_solid_strain: [n_states, n_solids, n_solid_layers, 6], 

3470 ArrayType.element_solid_is_alive: [n_states, n_solids], 

3471 ArrayType.element_solid_plastic_strain_tensor: [n_states, n_solids, n_solid_layers, 6], 

3472 ArrayType.element_solid_thermal_strain_tensor: [n_states, n_solids, n_solid_layers, 6], 

3473 # thick shells 

3474 ArrayType.element_tshell_stress: [n_states, n_tshells, n_tshells_layers, 6], 

3475 ArrayType.element_tshell_effective_plastic_strain: [ 

3476 n_states, 

3477 n_tshells, 

3478 n_tshells_layers, 

3479 ], 

3480 ArrayType.element_tshell_history_variables: [ 

3481 n_states, 

3482 n_tshells, 

3483 n_tshells_layers, 

3484 n_tshells_history_vars, 

3485 ], 

3486 ArrayType.element_tshell_strain: [n_states, n_tshells, 2, 6], 

3487 ArrayType.element_tshell_is_alive: [n_states, n_tshells], 

3488 # beams 

3489 ArrayType.element_beam_axial_force: [n_states, n_beams], 

3490 ArrayType.element_beam_shear_force: [n_states, n_beams, 2], 

3491 ArrayType.element_beam_bending_moment: [n_states, n_beams, 2], 

3492 ArrayType.element_beam_torsion_moment: [n_states, n_beams], 

3493 ArrayType.element_beam_shear_stress: [n_states, n_beams, n_beams_layers, 2], 

3494 ArrayType.element_beam_axial_stress: [n_states, n_beams, n_beams_layers], 

3495 ArrayType.element_beam_plastic_strain: [n_states, n_beams, n_beams_layers], 

3496 ArrayType.element_beam_axial_strain: [n_states, n_beams, n_beams_layers], 

3497 ArrayType.element_beam_history_vars: [ 

3498 n_states, 

3499 n_beams, 

3500 n_beams_layers + 3, 

3501 n_beams_history_vars, 

3502 ], 

3503 ArrayType.element_beam_is_alive: [n_states, n_beams], 

3504 # shells 

3505 ArrayType.element_shell_stress: [n_states, n_shells_reduced, n_shell_layers, 6], 

3506 ArrayType.element_shell_effective_plastic_strain: [ 

3507 n_states, 

3508 n_shells_reduced, 

3509 n_shell_layers, 

3510 ],

3512 n_states,

3514 n_shell_layers, 

3515 n_shell_history_vars, 

3516 ], 

3517 ArrayType.element_shell_bending_moment: [n_states, n_shells_reduced, 3], 

3518 ArrayType.element_shell_shear_force: [n_states, n_shells_reduced, 2], 

3519 ArrayType.element_shell_normal_force: [n_states, n_shells_reduced, 3], 

3520 ArrayType.element_shell_thickness: [n_states, n_shells_reduced], 

3521 ArrayType.element_shell_unknown_variables: [n_states, n_shells_reduced, 2], 

3522 ArrayType.element_shell_internal_energy: [n_states, n_shells_reduced], 

3523 ArrayType.element_shell_strain: [n_states, n_shells_reduced, 2, 6], 

3524 ArrayType.element_shell_thermal_strain_tensor: [n_states, n_shells_reduced, 6], 

3525 ArrayType.element_shell_plastic_strain_tensor: [ 

3526 n_states, 

3527 n_shells_reduced, 

3528 n_shell_layers, 

3529 6, 

3530 ], 

3531 ArrayType.element_shell_is_alive: [n_states, n_shells], 

3532 # sph 

3533 ArrayType.sph_deletion: [n_states, n_sph_particles], 

3534 ArrayType.sph_radius: [n_states, n_sph_particles], 

3535 ArrayType.sph_pressure: [n_states, n_sph_particles], 

3536 ArrayType.sph_stress: [n_states, n_sph_particles, 6], 

3537 ArrayType.sph_effective_plastic_strain: [n_states, n_sph_particles], 

3538 ArrayType.sph_density: [n_states, n_sph_particles], 

3539 ArrayType.sph_internal_energy: [n_states, n_sph_particles], 

3540 ArrayType.sph_n_neighbors: [n_states, n_sph_particles], 

3541 ArrayType.sph_strain: [n_states, n_sph_particles, 6], 

3542 ArrayType.sph_mass: [n_states, n_sph_particles], 

3543 # airbag 

3544 ArrayType.airbag_n_active_particles: [n_states, n_airbags], 

3545 ArrayType.airbag_bag_volume: [n_states, n_airbags], 

3546 ArrayType.airbag_particle_gas_id: [n_states, n_airbag_particles], 

3547 ArrayType.airbag_particle_chamber_id: [n_states, n_airbag_particles], 

3548 ArrayType.airbag_particle_leakage: [n_states, n_airbag_particles], 

3549 ArrayType.airbag_particle_mass: [n_states, n_airbag_particles], 

3550 ArrayType.airbag_particle_radius: [n_states, n_airbag_particles], 

3551 ArrayType.airbag_particle_spin_energy: [n_states, n_airbag_particles], 

3552 ArrayType.airbag_particle_translation_energy: [n_states, n_airbag_particles], 

3553 ArrayType.airbag_particle_nearest_segment_distance: [n_states, n_airbag_particles], 

3554 ArrayType.airbag_particle_position: [n_states, n_airbag_particles, 3], 

3555 ArrayType.airbag_particle_velocity: [n_states, n_airbag_particles, 3],
