3557 ArrayType.rigid_road_displacement: [n_states, n_roads, 3], 

3558 ArrayType.rigid_road_velocity: [n_states, n_roads, 3], 

3559 # rigid body 

3560 ArrayType.rigid_body_coordinates: [n_states, n_rigid_bodies, 3], 

3561 ArrayType.rigid_body_rotation_matrix: [n_states, n_rigid_bodies, 9], 

3562 ArrayType.rigid_body_velocity: [n_states, n_rigid_bodies, 3], 

3563 ArrayType.rigid_body_rot_velocity: [n_states, n_rigid_bodies, 3], 

3564 ArrayType.rigid_body_acceleration: [n_states, n_rigid_bodies, 3], 

3565 ArrayType.rigid_body_rot_acceleration: [n_states, n_rigid_bodies, 3], 

3566 } 

3567 

3568 # only allocate available arrays 

3569 if array_names is None: 

3570 array_names = ArrayType.get_state_array_names() 

3571 

3572 # BUGFIX 

3573 # These arrays are actually integer types, all other state arrays 

3574 # are floats 

3575 int_state_arrays = [ 

3576 ArrayType.airbag_n_active_particles, 

3577 ArrayType.airbag_particle_gas_id, 

3578 ArrayType.airbag_particle_chamber_id, 

3579 ArrayType.airbag_particle_leakage, 

3580 ] 

3581 

3582 # (2) ALLOCATE ARRAYS 

3583 # this looper allocates the arrays specified by the user. 

3584 for array_name in array_names: 

3585 

3586 array_dtype = header.ftype if array_name not in int_state_arrays else header.itype 

3587 

3588 if array_name in state_array_shapes: 

3589 array_dict[array_name] = np.empty(state_array_shapes[array_name], dtype=array_dtype) 

3590 else: 

3591 raise ValueError( 

3592 f"Array '{array_name}' is not a state array. " 

3593 f"Please try one of: {list(state_array_shapes.keys())}", 

3594 ) 

3595 

3596 @staticmethod 

3597 def _read_states_transfer_memory( 

3598 i_state: int, buffer_array_dict: dict, master_array_dict: dict 

3599 ): 

3600 """Transfers the memory from smaller buffer arrays with only a few 

3601 timesteps into the major one 

3602 

3603 Parameters 

3604 ---------- 

3605 i_state: int 

3606 current state index 

3607 buffer_array_dict: dict 

3608 dict with arrays of only a few timesteps 

3609 master_array_dict: dict 

3610 dict with the parent master arrays 

3611 

3612 Notes 

3613 ----- 

3614 If an array in the master dict is not found in the buffer dict 

3615 then this array is set to `None`. 

3616 """ 

3617 

3618 state_array_names = ArrayType.get_state_array_names() 

3619 

3620 arrays_to_delete = [] 

3621 for array_name, array in master_array_dict.items(): 

3622 

3623 # copy memory to big array 

3624 if array_name in buffer_array_dict: 

3625 buffer_array = buffer_array_dict[array_name] 

3626 n_states_buffer_array = buffer_array.shape[0] 

3627 array[i_state : i_state + n_states_buffer_array] = buffer_array 

3628 else: 

3629 # remove unnecesary state arrays (not geometry arrays!) 

3630 # we "could" deal with this in the allocate function 

3631 # by not allocating them but this would replicate code 

3632 # in the reading functions 

3633 if array_name in state_array_names: 

3634 arrays_to_delete.append(array_name) 

3635 

3636 for array_name in arrays_to_delete: 

3637 del master_array_dict[array_name] 

3638 

3639 def _compute_n_bytes_per_state(self) -> int: 

3640 """Computes the number of bytes for every state 

3641 

3642 Returns 

3643 ------- 

3644 n_bytes_per_state: int 

3645 number of bytes of every state 

3646 """ 

3647 

3648 if not self.header: 

3649 return 0 

3650 

3651 # timestep 

3652 timestep_offset = 1 * self.header.wordsize 

3653 # global vars 

3654 global_vars_offset = self.header.n_global_vars * self.header.wordsize 

3655 # node vars 

3656 n_node_vars = ( 

3657 self.header.has_node_displacement 

3658 + self.header.has_node_velocity 

3659 + self.header.has_node_acceleration 

3660 ) * self.header.n_dimensions 

3661 

3662 if self.header.has_node_temperatures: 

3663 n_node_vars += 1 

3664 if self.header.has_node_temperature_layers: 

3665 n_node_vars += 2 

3666 if self.header.has_node_heat_flux: 

3667 n_node_vars += 3 

3668 if self.header.has_node_mass_scaling: 

3669 n_node_vars += 1 

3670 if self.header.has_node_temperature_gradient: 

3671 n_node_vars += 1 

3672 if self.header.has_node_residual_forces: 

3673 n_node_vars += 3 

3674 if self.header.has_node_residual_moments: 

3675 n_node_vars += 3 

3676 

3677 node_data_offset = n_node_vars * self.header.n_nodes * self.header.wordsize 

3678 # thermal shit 

3679 therm_data_offset = ( 

3680 self.header.n_solid_thermal_vars * self.header.n_solids * self.header.wordsize 

3681 ) 

3682 # solids 

3683 solid_offset = self.header.n_solids * self.header.n_solid_vars * self.header.wordsize 

3684 # tshells 

3685 tshell_offset = ( 

3686 self.header.n_thick_shells * self.header.n_thick_shell_vars * self.header.wordsize 

3687 ) 

3688 # beams 

3689 beam_offset = self.header.n_beams * self.header.n_beam_vars * self.header.wordsize 

3690 # shells 

3691 shell_offset = ( 

3692 (self.header.n_shells - self._material_section_info.n_rigid_shells) 

3693 * self.header.n_shell_vars 

3694 * self.header.wordsize 

3695 ) 

3696 # Manual 

3697 # "NOTE: This CFDDATA is no longer output by ls-dyna." 

3698 cfd_data_offset = 0 

3699 # sph 

3700 sph_offset = self.header.n_sph_nodes * self._sph_info.n_sph_vars * self.header.wordsize 

3701 # deleted nodes and elems ... or nothing 

3702 elem_deletion_offset = 0 

3703 if self.header.has_node_deletion_data: 

3704 elem_deletion_offset = self.header.n_nodes * self.header.wordsize 

3705 elif self.header.has_element_deletion_data: 

3706 elem_deletion_offset = ( 

3707 self.header.n_beams 

3708 + self.header.n_shells 

3709 + self.header.n_solids 

3710 + self.header.n_thick_shells 

3711 ) * self.header.wordsize 

3712 # airbag particle offset 

3713 if self._airbag_info.n_airbags: 

3714 particle_state_offset = ( 

3715 self._airbag_info.n_airbags * self._airbag_info.n_airbag_state_variables 

3716 + self._airbag_info.n_particles * self._airbag_info.n_particle_state_variables 

3717 ) * self.header.wordsize 

3718 else: 

3719 particle_state_offset = 0 

3720 # rigid road stuff whoever uses this 

3721 road_surface_offset = self._rigid_road_info.n_roads * 6 * self.header.wordsize 

3722 # rigid body motion data 

3723 if self.header.has_rigid_body_data: 

3724 n_rigids = self._rigid_body_info.n_rigid_bodies 

3725 n_rigid_vars = 12 if self.header.has_reduced_rigid_body_data else 24 

3726 rigid_body_motion_offset = n_rigids * n_rigid_vars * self.header.wordsize 

3727 else: 

3728 rigid_body_motion_offset = 0 

3729 # ... not supported 

3730 extra_data_offset = 0 

3731 

3732 n_bytes_per_state = ( 

3733 timestep_offset 

3734 + global_vars_offset 

3735 + node_data_offset 

3736 + therm_data_offset 

3737 + solid_offset 

3738 + tshell_offset 

3739 + beam_offset 

3740 + shell_offset 

3741 + cfd_data_offset 

3742 + sph_offset 

3743 + elem_deletion_offset 

3744 + particle_state_offset 

3745 + road_surface_offset 

3746 + rigid_body_motion_offset 

3747 + extra_data_offset 

3748 ) 

3749 return n_bytes_per_state 

3750 

3751 def _read_states(self, filepath: str): 

3752 """Read the states from the d3plot 

3753 

3754 Parameters 

3755 ---------- 

3756 filepath: str 

3757 path to the d3plot 

3758 """ 

3759 

3760 if not self._buffer or not filepath: 

3761 self._state_info.n_timesteps = 0 

3762 return 

3763 

3764 LOGGER.debug("-------- S T A T E S --------") 

3765 LOGGER.debug("_read_states with geom offset %d", self.geometry_section_size) 

3766 

3767 # (0) OFFSETS 

3768 bytes_per_state = self._compute_n_bytes_per_state() 

3769 LOGGER.debug("bytes_per_state: %d", bytes_per_state) 

3770 

3771 # load the memory from the files 

3772 if self._femzip_info.use_femzip: 

3773 bytes_per_state += 1 * self.header.wordsize 

3774 self.bb_generator = self._read_femzip_file_generator( 

3775 self.buffered_reading, self.state_filter 

3776 ) 

3777 else: 

3778 self.bb_generator = self._read_d3plot_file_generator( 

3779 self.buffered_reading, self.state_filter 

3780 ) 

3781 

3782 # (1) READ STATE DATA 

3783 n_states = next(self.bb_generator) 

3784 

3785 # determine whether to transfer arrays 

3786 if not self.buffered_reading: 

3787 transfer_arrays = False 

3788 else: 

3789 transfer_arrays = True 

3790 if self.state_filter is not None and any(self.state_filter): 

3791 transfer_arrays = True 

3792 if self.state_array_filter: 

3793 transfer_arrays = True 

3794 

3795 # arrays need to be preallocated if we transfer them 

3796 if transfer_arrays: 

3797 self._read_states_allocate_arrays( 

3798 self.header, 

3799 self._material_section_info, 

3800 self._airbag_info, 

3801 self._rigid_road_info, 

3802 self._rigid_body_info, 

3803 n_states, 

3804 self._n_rigid_walls, 

3805 self._n_parts, 

3806 self.state_array_filter, 

3807 self.arrays, 

3808 ) 

3809 

3810 i_state = 0 

3811 for bb_states, n_states in self.bb_generator: 

3812 

3813 # dictionary to store the temporary, partial arrays 

3814 # if we do not transfer any arrays we store them directly 

3815 # in the classes main dict 

3816 array_dict = {} if transfer_arrays else self.arrays 

3817 

3818 # sometimes there is just a geometry in the file 

3819 if n_states == 0: 

3820 continue 

3821 

3822 # state data as array 

3823 array_length = int(n_states) * int(bytes_per_state) 

3824 state_data = bb_states.read_ndarray(0, array_length, 1, self.header.ftype) 

3825 state_data = state_data.reshape((n_states, -1)) 

3826 

3827 var_index = 0 

3828 

3829 # global state header 

3830 var_index = self._read_states_global_section(state_data, var_index, array_dict) 

3831 

3832 # node data 

3833 var_index = self._read_states_nodes(state_data, var_index, array_dict) 

3834 

3835 # thermal solid data 

3836 var_index = self._read_states_solids_thermal(state_data, var_index, array_dict) 

3837 

3838 # cfddata was originally here 

3839 

3840 # solids 

3841 var_index = self._read_states_solids(state_data, var_index, array_dict) 

3842 

3843 # tshells 

3844 var_index = self._read_states_tshell(state_data, var_index, array_dict) 

3845 

3846 # beams 

3847 var_index = self._read_states_beams(state_data, var_index, array_dict) 

3848 

3849 # shells 

3850 var_index = self._read_states_shell(state_data, var_index, array_dict) 

3851 

3852 # element and node deletion info 

3853 var_index = self._read_states_is_alive(state_data, var_index, array_dict) 

3854 

3855 # sph 

3856 var_index = self._read_states_sph(state_data, var_index, array_dict) 

3857 

3858 # airbag particle data 

3859 var_index = self._read_states_airbags(state_data, var_index, array_dict) 

3860 

3861 # road surface data 

3862 var_index = self._read_states_road_surfaces(state_data, var_index, array_dict) 

3863 

3864 # rigid body motion 

3865 var_index = self._read_states_rigid_body_motion(state_data, var_index, array_dict) 

3866 

3867 # transfer memory 

3868 if transfer_arrays: 

3869 self._read_states_transfer_memory(i_state, array_dict, self.arrays) 

3870 

3871 # increment state counter 

3872 i_state += n_states 

3873 self._state_info.n_timesteps = i_state 

3874 

3875 if transfer_arrays: 

3876 self._buffer = None 

3877 self.bb_states = None 

3878 

3879 def _read_states_global_section( 

3880 self, state_data: np.ndarray, var_index: int, array_dict: dict 

3881 ) -> int: 

3882 """Read the global vars for the state 

3883 

3884 Parameters 

3885 ---------- 

3886 state_data: np.ndarray 

3887 array with entire state data 

3888 var_index: int 

3889 variable index in the state data array 

3890 array_dict: dict 

3891 dictionary to store the loaded arrays in 

3892 

3893 Returns 

3894 ------- 

3895 var_index: int 

3896 updated variable index after reading the section 

3897 """ 

3898 

3899 LOGGER.debug("_read_states_global_section start at var_index %d", var_index) 

3900 

3901 # we wrap globals, parts and rigid walls into a single try 

3902 # catch block since in the header the global section is 

3903 # defined by those three. If we fail in any of those we can 

3904 # only heal by skipping all together and jumping forward 

3905 original_var_index = var_index 

3906 try: 

3907 # timestep 

3908 array_dict[ArrayType.global_timesteps] = state_data[:, var_index] 

3909 var_index += 1 

3910 

3911 # global stuff 

3912 var_index = self._read_states_globals(state_data, var_index, array_dict) 

3913 

3914 # parts 

3915 var_index = self._read_states_parts(state_data, var_index, array_dict) 

3916 

3917 # rigid walls 

3918 var_index = self._read_states_rigid_walls(state_data, var_index, array_dict) 

3919 

3920 except Exception: 

3921 # print 

3922 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

3923 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

3924 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_global_section", trb_msg) 

3925 finally: 

3926 timestep_var_size = 1 

3927 var_index = original_var_index + self.header.n_global_vars + timestep_var_size 

3928 

3929 LOGGER.debug("_read_states_global_section end at var_index %d", var_index) 

3930 

3931 return var_index 

3932 

3933 def _read_states_globals(self, state_data: np.ndarray, var_index: int, array_dict: dict) -> int: 

3934 """Read the part data in the state section 

3935 

3936 Parameters 

3937 ---------- 

3938 state_data: np.ndarray 

3939 array with entire state data 

3940 var_index: int 

3941 variable index in the state data array 

3942 array_dict: dict 

3943 dictionary to store the loaded arrays in 

3944 

3945 Returns 

3946 ------- 

3947 var_index: int 

3948 updated variable index after reading the section 

3949 """ 

3950 

3951 n_global_vars = self.header.n_global_vars 

3952 

3953 # global stuff 

3954 i_global_var = 0 

3955 if i_global_var < n_global_vars: 

3956 array_dict[ArrayType.global_kinetic_energy] = state_data[:, var_index + i_global_var] 

3957 i_global_var += 1 

3958 if i_global_var < n_global_vars: 

3959 array_dict[ArrayType.global_internal_energy] = state_data[:, var_index + i_global_var] 

3960 i_global_var += 1 

3961 if i_global_var < n_global_vars: 

3962 array_dict[ArrayType.global_total_energy] = state_data[:, var_index + i_global_var] 

3963 i_global_var += 1 

3964 if i_global_var + 3 <= n_global_vars: 

3965 array_dict[ArrayType.global_velocity] = state_data[ 

3966 :, var_index + i_global_var : var_index + i_global_var + 3 

3967 ] 

3968 i_global_var += 3 

3969 

3970 return var_index + i_global_var 

3971 

3972 def _read_states_parts(self, state_data: np.ndarray, var_index: int, array_dict: dict) -> int: 

3973 """Read the part data in the state section 

3974 

3975 Parameters 

3976 ---------- 

3977 state_data: np.ndarray 

3978 array with entire state data 

3979 var_index: int 

3980 variable index in the state data array 

3981 array_dict: dict 

3982 dictionary to store the loaded arrays in 

3983 

3984 Returns 

3985 ------- 

3986 var_index: int 

3987 updated variable index after reading the section 

3988 """ 

3989 

3990 n_states = state_data.shape[0] 

3991 timestep_word = 1 

3992 n_global_vars = self.header.n_global_vars + timestep_word 

3993 

3994 # part infos 

3995 # n_parts = self._n_parts 

3996 n_parts = self.header.n_parts 

3997 

3998 # part internal energy 

3999 if var_index + n_parts <= n_global_vars: 

4000 array_dict[ArrayType.part_internal_energy] = state_data[ 

4001 :, var_index : var_index + n_parts 

4002 ] 

4003 var_index += n_parts 

4004 

4005 # part kinetic energy 

4006 if var_index + n_parts <= n_global_vars: 

4007 array_dict[ArrayType.part_kinetic_energy] = state_data[ 

4008 :, var_index : var_index + n_parts 

4009 ] 

4010 var_index += n_parts 

4011 

4012 # part velocity 

4013 if var_index + 3 * n_parts <= n_global_vars: 

4014 array_dict[ArrayType.part_velocity] = state_data[ 

4015 :, var_index : var_index + 3 * n_parts 

4016 ].reshape((n_states, n_parts, 3)) 

4017 var_index += 3 * n_parts 

4018 

4019 # part mass 

4020 if var_index + n_parts <= n_global_vars: 

4021 array_dict[ArrayType.part_mass] = state_data[:, var_index : var_index + n_parts] 

4022 var_index += n_parts 

4023 

4024 # part hourglass energy 

4025 if var_index + n_parts <= n_global_vars: 

4026 array_dict[ArrayType.part_hourglass_energy] = state_data[ 

4027 :, var_index : var_index + n_parts 

4028 ] 

4029 var_index += n_parts 

4030 

4031 return var_index 

4032 

4033 def _read_states_rigid_walls( 

4034 self, state_data: np.ndarray, var_index: int, array_dict: dict 

4035 ) -> int: 

4036 """Read the rigid wall data in the state section 

4037 

4038 Parameters 

4039 ---------- 

4040 state_data: np.ndarray 

4041 array with entire state data 

4042 var_index: int 

4043 variable index in the state data array 

4044 array_dict: dict 

4045 dictionary to store the loaded arrays in 

4046 

4047 Returns 

4048 ------- 

4049 var_index: int 

4050 updated variable index after reading the section 

4051 """ 

4052 

4053 n_states = state_data.shape[0] 

4054 

4055 i_global_var = 6 + 7 * self.header.n_parts 

4056 n_global_vars = self.header.n_global_vars 

4057 

4058 # rigid walls 

4059 previous_global_vars = i_global_var 

4060 n_rigid_wall_vars = 4 if self.header.version >= 971 else 1 

4061 # +1 is timestep which is not considered a global var ... seriously 

4062 n_rigid_walls = self._n_rigid_walls 

4063 if n_global_vars >= previous_global_vars + n_rigid_walls * n_rigid_wall_vars: 

4064 if ( 

4065 previous_global_vars + n_rigid_walls * n_rigid_wall_vars 

4066 != self.header.n_global_vars 

4067 ): 

4068 LOGGER.warning("Bug while reading global data for rigid walls. Skipping this data.") 

4069 var_index += self.header.n_global_vars - previous_global_vars 

4070 else: 

4071 

4072 # rigid wall force 

4073 if n_rigid_walls * n_rigid_wall_vars != 0: 

4074 array_dict[ArrayType.rigid_wall_force] = state_data[ 

4075 :, var_index : var_index + n_rigid_walls 

4076 ] 

4077 var_index += n_rigid_walls 

4078 

4079 # rigid wall position 

4080 if n_rigid_wall_vars > 1: 

4081 array_dict[ArrayType.rigid_wall_position] = state_data[ 

4082 :, var_index : var_index + 3 * n_rigid_walls 

4083 ].reshape(n_states, n_rigid_walls, 3) 

4084 var_index += 3 * n_rigid_walls 

4085 

4086 return var_index 

4087 

4088 def _read_states_nodes(self, state_data: np.ndarray, var_index: int, array_dict: dict) -> int: 

4089 """Read the node data in the state section 

4090 

4091 Parameters 

4092 ---------- 

4093 state_data: np.ndarray 

4094 array with entire state data 

4095 var_index: int 

4096 variable index in the state data array 

4097 array_dict: dict 

4098 dictionary to store the loaded arrays in 

4099 

4100 Returns 

4101 ------- 

4102 var_index: int 

4103 updated variable index after reading the section 

4104 """ 

4105 

4106 if self.header.n_nodes <= 0: 

4107 return var_index 

4108 

4109 LOGGER.debug("_read_states_nodes start at var_index %d", var_index) 

4110 

4111 n_dim = self.header.n_dimensions 

4112 n_states = state_data.shape[0] 

4113 n_nodes = self.header.n_nodes 

4114 

4115 # displacement 

4116 if self.header.has_node_displacement: 

4117 try: 

4118 tmp_array = state_data[:, var_index : var_index + n_dim * n_nodes].reshape( 

4119 (n_states, n_nodes, n_dim) 

4120 ) 

4121 array_dict[ArrayType.node_displacement] = tmp_array 

4122 except Exception: 

4123 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

4124 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

4125 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_nodes, node_displacement", trb_msg) 

4126 finally: 

4127 var_index += n_dim * n_nodes 

4128 

4129 # temperatures 

4130 if self.header.has_node_temperatures: 

4131 

4132 # only node temperatures 

4133 if not self.header.has_node_temperature_layers: 

4134 try: 

4135 array_dict[ArrayType.node_temperature] = state_data[ 

4136 :, var_index : var_index + n_nodes 

4137 ] 

4138 except Exception: 

4139 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

4140 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

4141 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_nodes, node_temperatures", trb_msg) 

4142 finally: 

4143 var_index += n_nodes 

4144 # node temperature layers 

4145 else: 

4146 try: 

4147 tmp_array = state_data[:, var_index : var_index + 3 * n_nodes].reshape( 

4148 (n_states, n_nodes, 3) 

4149 ) 

4150 array_dict[ArrayType.node_temperature] = tmp_array 

4151 except Exception: 

4152 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

4153 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

4154 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_nodes, node_temperatures_layers", trb_msg) 

4155 finally: 

4156 var_index += 3 * n_nodes 

4157 

4158 # node heat flux 

4159 if self.header.has_node_heat_flux: 

4160 try: 

4161 tmp_array = state_data[:, var_index : var_index + 3 * n_nodes].reshape( 

4162 (n_states, n_nodes, 3) 

4163 ) 

4164 array_dict[ArrayType.node_heat_flux] = tmp_array 

4165 except Exception: 

4166 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

4167 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

4168 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_nodes, node_heat_flux", trb_msg) 

4169 finally: 

4170 var_index += 3 * n_nodes 

4171 

4172 # mass scaling 

4173 if self.header.has_node_mass_scaling: 

4174 try: 

4175 array_dict[ArrayType.node_mass_scaling] = state_data[ 

4176 :, var_index : var_index + n_nodes 

4177 ] 

4178 except Exception: 

4179 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

4180 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

4181 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_nodes, node_mass_scaling", trb_msg) 

4182 finally: 

4183 var_index += n_nodes 

4184 

4185 # node temperature gradient 

4186 # Unclear: verify (could also be between temperature and node heat flux) 

4187 if self.header.has_node_temperature_gradient: 

4188 try: 

4189 array_dict[ArrayType.node_temperature_gradient] = state_data[ 

4190 :, var_index : var_index + n_nodes 

4191 ] 

4192 except Exception: 

4193 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

4194 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

4195 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_nodes, node_temperature_gradient", trb_msg) 

4196 finally: 

4197 var_index += n_nodes 

4198 

4199 # node residual forces and moments 

4200 # Unclear: verify (see before, according to docs this is after previous) 

4201 if self.header.has_node_residual_forces: 

4202 try: 

4203 array_dict[ArrayType.node_residual_forces] = state_data[ 

4204 :, var_index : var_index + 3 * n_nodes 

4205 ].reshape((n_states, n_nodes, 3)) 

4206 except Exception: 

4207 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

4208 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

4209 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_nodes, node_residual_forces", trb_msg) 

4210 finally: 

4211 var_index += n_nodes * 3 

4212 

4213 if self.header.has_node_residual_moments: 

4214 try: 

4215 array_dict[ArrayType.node_residual_moments] = state_data[ 

4216 :, var_index : var_index + 3 * n_nodes 

4217 ].reshape((n_states, n_nodes, 3)) 

4218 except Exception: 

4219 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

4220 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

4221 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_nodes, node_residual_moments", trb_msg) 

4222 finally: 

4223 var_index += n_nodes * 3 

4224 

4225 # velocity 

4226 if self.header.has_node_velocity: 

4227 try: 

4228 tmp_array = state_data[:, var_index : var_index + n_dim * n_nodes].reshape( 

4229 (n_states, n_nodes, n_dim) 

4230 ) 

4231 array_dict[ArrayType.node_velocity] = tmp_array 

4232 except Exception: 

4233 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

4234 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

4235 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_nodes, node_velocity", trb_msg) 

4236 finally: 

4237 var_index += n_dim * n_nodes 

4238 

4239 # acceleration 

4240 if self.header.has_node_acceleration: 

4241 try: 

4242 tmp_array = state_data[:, var_index : var_index + n_dim * n_nodes].reshape( 

4243 (n_states, n_nodes, n_dim) 

4244 ) 

4245 array_dict[ArrayType.node_acceleration] = tmp_array 

4246 except Exception: 

4247 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

4248 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

4249 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_nodes, node_acceleration", trb_msg) 

4250 finally: 

4251 var_index += n_dim * n_nodes 

4252 

4253 LOGGER.debug("_read_states_nodes end at var_index %d", var_index) 

4254 

4255 return var_index 

4256 

4257 def _read_states_solids_thermal( 

4258 self, state_data: np.ndarray, var_index: int, array_dict: dict 

4259 ) -> int: 

4260 """Read the thermal data for solids 

4261 

4262 Parameters 

4263 ---------- 

4264 state_data: np.ndarray 

4265 array with entire state data 

4266 var_index: int 

4267 variable index in the state data array 

4268 array_dict: dict 

4269 dictionary to store the loaded arrays in 

4270 

4271 Returns 

4272 ------- 

4273 var_index: int 

4274 updated variable index after reading the section 

4275 """ 

4276 

4277 if self.header.n_solid_thermal_vars <= 0: 

4278 return var_index 

4279 

4280 LOGGER.debug("_read_states_solids_thermal start at var_index %d", var_index) 

4281 

4282 n_states = state_data.shape[0] 

4283 n_solids = self.header.n_solids 

4284 n_thermal_vars = self.header.n_solid_thermal_vars 

4285 

4286 try: 

4287 tmp_array = state_data[:, var_index : var_index + n_solids * n_thermal_vars] 

4288 array_dict[ArrayType.element_solid_thermal_data] = tmp_array.reshape( 

4289 (n_states, n_solids, n_thermal_vars) 

4290 ) 

4291 except Exception: 

4292 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

4293 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

4294 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_solids_thermal", trb_msg) 

4295 finally: 

4296 var_index += n_thermal_vars * n_solids 

4297 

4298 LOGGER.debug("_read_states_solids_thermal end at var_index %d", var_index) 

4299 

4300 return var_index 

4301 

4302 def _read_states_solids(self, state_data: np.ndarray, var_index: int, array_dict: dict) -> int: 

4303 """Read the state data of the solid elements 

4304 

4305 Parameters 

4306 ---------- 

4307 state_data: np.ndarray 

4308 array with entire state data 

4309 var_index: int 

4310 variable index in the state data array 

4311 array_dict: dict 

4312 dictionary to store the loaded arrays in 

4313 

4314 Returns 

4315 ------- 

4316 var_index: int 

4317 updated variable index after reading the section 

4318 """ 

4319 

4320 if self.header.n_solids <= 0 or self.header.n_solid_vars <= 0: 

4321 return var_index 

4322 

4323 LOGGER.debug("_read_states_solids start at var_index %d", var_index) 

4324 

4325 n_solid_vars = self.header.n_solid_vars 

4326 n_solids = self.header.n_solids 

4327 n_states = state_data.shape[0] 

4328 n_strain_vars = 6 * self.header.has_element_strain 

4329 n_history_vars = self.header.n_solid_history_vars 

4330 n_solid_layers = self.header.n_solid_layers 

4331 

4332 # double safety here, if either the formatting of the solid state data 

4333 # or individual arrays fails then we catch it 

4334 try: 

4335 # this is a sanity check if the manual was understood correctly 

4336 # 

4337 # NOTE due to plotcompress we disable this check, it can delete 

4338 # variables so that stress or pstrain might be missing despite 

4339 # being always present in the file spec 

4340 # 

4341 # n_solid_vars2 = (7 + 

4342 # n_history_vars) 

4343 

4344 # if n_solid_vars2 != n_solid_vars: 

4345 # msg = "n_solid_vars != n_solid_vars_computed: {} != {}."\ 

4346 # + " Solid variables might be wrong." 

4347 # LOGGER.warning(msg.format(n_solid_vars, n_solid_vars2)) 

4348 

4349 solid_state_data = state_data[ 

4350 :, var_index : var_index + n_solid_vars * n_solids 

4351 ].reshape((n_states, n_solids, n_solid_layers, n_solid_vars // n_solid_layers)) 

4352 

4353 i_solid_var = 0 

4354 

4355 # stress 

4356 try: 

4357 if self.header.has_solid_stress: 

4358 array_dict[ArrayType.element_solid_stress] = solid_state_data[:, :, :, :6] 

4359 except Exception: 

4360 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

4361 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

4362 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_solids, stress", trb_msg) 

4363 finally: 

4364 i_solid_var += 6 * self.header.has_solid_stress 

4365 

4366 # effective plastic strain 

4367 try: 

4368 # in case plotcompress deleted stresses but pstrain exists 

4369 if self.header.has_solid_pstrain: 

4370 array_dict[ArrayType.element_solid_effective_plastic_strain] = solid_state_data[ 

4371 :, :, :, i_solid_var 

4372 ].reshape((n_states, n_solids, n_solid_layers)) 

4373 except Exception: 

4374 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

4375 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

4376 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_solids, eff_plastic_strain", trb_msg) 

4377 finally: 

4378 i_solid_var += 1 * self.header.has_solid_pstrain 

4379 

4380 # history vars 

4381 if n_history_vars: 

4382 try: 

4383 array_dict[ArrayType.element_solid_history_variables] = solid_state_data[ 

4384 :, :, :, i_solid_var : i_solid_var + n_history_vars 

4385 ] 

4386 except Exception: 

4387 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

4388 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

4389 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_solids, history_variables", trb_msg) 

4390 finally: 

4391 i_solid_var += n_history_vars 

4392 

4393 # strain 

4394 # they are the last 6 entries of the history vars 

4395 if n_strain_vars: 

4396 try: 

4397 array_dict[ArrayType.element_solid_strain] = array_dict[ 

4398 ArrayType.element_solid_history_variables 

4399 ][:, :, :, -n_strain_vars:] 

4400 

4401 array_dict[ArrayType.element_solid_history_variables] = array_dict[ 

4402 ArrayType.element_solid_history_variables 

4403 ][:, :, :, :-n_strain_vars] 

4404 

4405 if not all(array_dict[ArrayType.element_solid_history_variables].shape): 

4406 del array_dict[ArrayType.element_solid_history_variables] 

4407 except Exception: 

4408 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

4409 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

4410 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_solids, strain", trb_msg) 

4411 

4412 # plastic strain tensor 

4413 if self.header.has_solid_shell_plastic_strain_tensor: 

4414 try: 

4415 array_dict[ArrayType.element_solid_plastic_strain_tensor] = solid_state_data[ 

4416 :, :, :, i_solid_var : i_solid_var + 6 

4417 ] 

4418 except Exception: 

4419 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

4420 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

4421 LOGGER.warning( 

4422 msg, "_read_states_solids, element_solid_plastic_strain_tensor", trb_msg 

4423 ) 

4424 finally: 

4425 i_solid_var += 6 

4426 

4427 # thermal strain tensor 

4428 if self.header.has_solid_shell_thermal_strain_tensor: 

4429 try: 

4430 array_dict[ArrayType.element_solid_thermal_strain_tensor] = solid_state_data[ 

4431 :, :, i_solid_var : i_solid_var + 6 

4432 ] 

4433 except Exception: 

4434 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

4435 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

4436 LOGGER.warning( 

4437 msg, "_read_states_solids, element_solid_thermal_strain_tensor", trb_msg 

4438 ) 

4439 finally: 

4440 i_solid_var += 6 

4441 

4442 # catch formatting in solid_state_datra 

4443 except Exception: 

4444 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

4445 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

4446 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_solids, solid_state_data", trb_msg) 

4447 # always increment variable count 

4448 finally: 

4449 var_index += n_solids * n_solid_vars 

4450 

4451 LOGGER.debug("_read_states_solids end at var_index %d", var_index) 

4452 

4453 return var_index 

4454 

4455 def _read_states_tshell(self, state_data: np.ndarray, var_index: int, array_dict: dict) -> int: 

4456 """Read the state data for thick shell elements 

4457 

4458 Parameters 

4459 ---------- 

4460 state_data: np.ndarray 

4461 array with entire state data 

4462 var_index: int 

4463 variable index in the state data array 

4464 array_dict: dict 

4465 dictionary to store the loaded arrays in 

4466 

4467 Returns 

4468 ------- 

4469 var_index: int 

4470 updated variable index after reading the section 

4471 """ 

4472 

4473 if self.header.n_thick_shells <= 0 or self.header.n_thick_shell_vars <= 0: 

4474 return var_index 

4475 

4476 LOGGER.debug("_read_states_tshell start at var_index %d", var_index) 

4477 

4478 n_states = state_data.shape[0] 

4479 n_tshells = self.header.n_thick_shells 

4480 n_history_vars = self.header.n_shell_tshell_history_vars 

4481 n_layers = self.header.n_shell_tshell_layers 

4482 n_layer_vars = n_layers * ( 

4483 6 * self.header.has_shell_tshell_stress 

4484 + self.header.has_shell_tshell_pstrain 

4485 + n_history_vars 

4486 ) 

4487 n_strain_vars = 12 * self.header.has_element_strain 

4488 n_thsell_vars = self.header.n_thick_shell_vars 

4489 has_stress = self.header.has_shell_tshell_stress 

4490 has_pstrain = self.header.has_shell_tshell_pstrain 

4491 

4492 try: 

4493 # this is a sanity check if the manual was understood correctly 

4494 n_tshell_vars2 = n_layer_vars + n_strain_vars 

4495 

4496 if n_tshell_vars2 != n_thsell_vars: 

4497 msg = ( 

4498 "n_tshell_vars != n_tshell_vars_computed: %d != %d." 

4499 " Thick shell variables might be wrong." 

4500 ) 

4501 LOGGER.warning(msg, n_thsell_vars, n_tshell_vars2) 

4502 

4503 # thick shell element data 

4504 tshell_data = state_data[:, var_index : var_index + n_thsell_vars * n_tshells] 

4505 tshell_data = tshell_data.reshape((n_states, n_tshells, n_thsell_vars)) 

4506 

4507 # extract layer data 

4508 tshell_layer_data = tshell_data[:, :, slice(0, n_layer_vars)] 

4509 tshell_layer_data = tshell_layer_data.reshape((n_states, n_tshells, n_layers, -1)) 

4510 tshell_nonlayer_data = tshell_data[:, :, n_layer_vars:] 

4511 

4512 # STRESS 

4513 i_tshell_layer_var = 0 

4514 if has_stress: 

4515 try: 

4516 array_dict[ArrayType.element_tshell_stress] = tshell_layer_data[ 

4517 :, :, :, i_tshell_layer_var : i_tshell_layer_var + 6 

4518 ].reshape((n_states, n_tshells, n_layers, 6)) 

4519 except Exception: 

4520 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

4521 msg = "A failure in %d was caught:\n%s" 

4522 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_tshell, stress", trb_msg) 

4523 finally: 

4524 i_tshell_layer_var += 6 

4525 

4526 # PSTRAIN 

4527 if has_pstrain: 

4528 try: 

4529 array_dict[ 

4530 ArrayType.element_tshell_effective_plastic_strain 

4531 ] = tshell_layer_data[:, :, :, i_tshell_layer_var].reshape( 

4532 (n_states, n_tshells, n_layers) 

4533 ) 

4534 except Exception: 

4535 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

4536 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

4537 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_tshell, eff_plastic_strain", trb_msg) 

4538 finally: 

4539 i_tshell_layer_var += 1 

4540 

4541 # HISTORY VARS 

4542 if n_history_vars: 

4543 try: 

4544 array_dict[ArrayType.element_tshell_history_variables] = tshell_layer_data[ 

4545 :, :, :, i_tshell_layer_var : i_tshell_layer_var + n_history_vars 

4546 ].reshape((n_states, n_tshells, n_layers, n_history_vars)) 

4547 except Exception: 

4548 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

4549 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

4550 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_tshell, history_variables", trb_msg) 

4551 

4552 # STRAIN (only non layer data for tshells) 

4553 if n_strain_vars: 

4554 try: 

4555 tshell_nonlayer_data = tshell_nonlayer_data[:, :, :n_strain_vars] 

4556 array_dict[ArrayType.element_tshell_strain] = tshell_nonlayer_data.reshape( 

4557 (n_states, n_tshells, 2, 6) 

4558 ) 

4559 except Exception: 

4560 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

4561 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

4562 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_tshell, strain", trb_msg) 

4563 

4564 except Exception: 

4565 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

4566 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

4567 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_tshell, tshell_data", trb_msg) 

4568 finally: 

4569 var_index += n_thsell_vars * n_tshells 

4570 

4571 LOGGER.debug("_read_states_tshell end at var_index %d", var_index) 

4572 

4573 return var_index 

4574 

4575 def _read_states_beams(self, state_data: np.ndarray, var_index: int, array_dict: dict) -> int: 

4576 """Read the state data for beams 

4577 

4578 Parameters 

4579 ---------- 

4580 state_data: np.ndarray 

4581 array with entire state data 

4582 var_index: int 

4583 variable index in the state data array 

4584 array_dict: dict 

4585 dictionary to store the loaded arrays in 

4586 

4587 Returns 

4588 ------- 

4589 var_index: int 

4590 updated variable index after reading the section 

4591 """ 

4592 

4593 if self.header.n_beams <= 0 or self.header.n_beam_vars <= 0: 

4594 return var_index 

4595 

4596 LOGGER.debug("_read_states_beams start at var_index %d", var_index) 

4597 

4598 # usual beam vars 

4599 # pylint: disable = invalid-name 

4600 N_BEAM_BASIC_VARS = 6 

4601 # beam intergration point vars 

4602 # pylint: disable = invalid-name 

4603 N_BEAM_IP_VARS = 5 

4604 

4605 n_states = state_data.shape[0] 

4606 n_beams = self.header.n_beams 

4607 n_history_vars = self.header.n_beam_history_vars 

4608 n_beam_vars = self.header.n_beam_vars 

4609 n_layers = int( 

4610 (-3 * n_history_vars + n_beam_vars - N_BEAM_BASIC_VARS) 

4611 / (n_history_vars + N_BEAM_IP_VARS) 

4612 ) 

4613 # n_layer_vars = 6 + N_BEAM_IP_VARS * n_layers 

4614 n_layer_vars = N_BEAM_IP_VARS * n_layers 

4615 

4616 try: 

4617 # beam element data 

4618 beam_data = state_data[:, var_index : var_index + n_beam_vars * n_beams] 

4619 beam_data = beam_data.reshape((n_states, n_beams, n_beam_vars)) 

4620 

4621 # extract layer data 

4622 beam_nonlayer_data = beam_data[:, :, :N_BEAM_BASIC_VARS] 

4623 beam_layer_data = beam_data[:, :, N_BEAM_BASIC_VARS : N_BEAM_BASIC_VARS + n_layer_vars] 

4624 beam_layer_data = beam_layer_data.reshape((n_states, n_beams, n_layers, N_BEAM_IP_VARS)) 

4625 

4626 # axial force 

4627 try: 

4628 array_dict[ArrayType.element_beam_axial_force] = beam_nonlayer_data[ 

4629 :, :, 0 

4630 ].reshape((n_states, n_beams)) 

4631 except Exception: 

4632 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

4633 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

4634 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_beams, axial_force", trb_msg) 

4635 

4636 # shear force 

4637 try: 

4638 array_dict[ArrayType.element_beam_shear_force] = beam_nonlayer_data[ 

4639 :, :, 1:3 

4640 ].reshape((n_states, n_beams, 2)) 

4641 except Exception: 

4642 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

4643 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

4644 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_beams, shear_force", trb_msg) 

4645 

4646 # bending moment 

4647 try: 

4648 array_dict[ArrayType.element_beam_bending_moment] = beam_nonlayer_data[ 

4649 :, :, 3:5 

4650 ].reshape((n_states, n_beams, 2)) 

4651 except Exception: 

4652 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

4653 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

4654 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_beams, bending_moment", trb_msg) 

4655 

4656 # torsion moment 

4657 try: 

4658 array_dict[ArrayType.element_beam_torsion_moment] = beam_nonlayer_data[ 

4659 :, :, 5 

4660 ].reshape((n_states, n_beams)) 

4661 except Exception: 

4662 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

4663 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

4664 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_beams, torsion_moment", trb_msg) 

4665 

4666 if n_layers: 

4667 

4668 # BUGFIX? 

4669 # According to the database manual the first 

4670 # two layer vars are the shear stress and then 

4671 # axial stress. Tests with FEMZIP and META though 

4672 # suggests that axial stress comes first. 

4673 

4674 # axial stress 

4675 try: 

4676 array_dict[ArrayType.element_beam_axial_stress] = beam_layer_data[:, :, :, 0] 

4677 except Exception: 

4678 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

4679 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

4680 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_beams, axial_stress", trb_msg) 

4681 

4682 # shear stress 

4683 try: 

4684 array_dict[ArrayType.element_beam_shear_stress] = beam_layer_data[:, :, :, 1:3] 

4685 except Exception: 

4686 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

4687 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

4688 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_beams, shear_stress", trb_msg) 

4689 

4690 # eff. plastic strain 

4691 try: 

4692 array_dict[ArrayType.element_beam_plastic_strain] = beam_layer_data[:, :, :, 3] 

4693 except Exception: 

4694 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

4695 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

4696 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_beams, eff_plastic_strain", trb_msg) 

4697 

4698 # axial strain 

4699 try: 

4700 array_dict[ArrayType.element_beam_axial_strain] = beam_layer_data[:, :, :, 4] 

4701 except Exception: 

4702 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

4703 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

4704 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_beams, axial_strain", trb_msg) 

4705 

4706 # history vars 

4707 if n_history_vars: 

4708 try: 

4709 array_dict[ArrayType.element_beam_history_vars] = beam_data[ 

4710 :, :, 6 + n_layer_vars : 

4711 ].reshape((n_states, n_beams, 3 + n_layers, n_history_vars)) 

4712 except Exception: 

4713 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

4714 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

4715 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_beams, history_variables", trb_msg) 

4716 

4717 # failure of formatting beam state data 

4718 except Exception: 

4719 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

4720 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

4721 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_beams, beam_state_data", trb_msg) 

4722 # always increment variable index 

4723 finally: 

4724 var_index += n_beams * n_beam_vars 

4725 

4726 LOGGER.debug("_read_states_beams end at var_index %d", var_index) 

4727 

4728 return var_index 

4729 

4730 def _read_states_shell(self, state_data: np.ndarray, var_index: int, array_dict: dict) -> int: 

4731 """Read the state data for shell elements 

4732 

4733 Parameters 

4734 ---------- 

4735 state_data: np.ndarray 

4736 array with entire state data 

4737 var_index: int 

4738 variable index in the state data array 

4739 array_dict: dict 

4740 dictionary to store the loaded arrays in 

4741 

4742 Returns 

4743 ------- 

4744 var_index: int 

4745 updated variable index after reading the section 

4746 """ 

4747 

4748 # bugfix 

4749 # 

4750 # Interestingly, dyna seems to write result values for rigid shells in 

4751 # the d3part file, but not in the d3plot. Of course this is not 

4752 # documented ... 

4753 n_reduced_shells = ( 

4754 self.header.n_shells 

4755 if self.header.filetype == D3plotFiletype.D3PART 

4756 else self.header.n_shells - self._material_section_info.n_rigid_shells 

4757 ) 

4758 

4759 if self.header.n_shell_vars <= 0 or n_reduced_shells <= 0: 

4760 return var_index 

4761 

4762 LOGGER.debug("_read_states_shell start at var_index %d", var_index) 

4763 

4764 n_states = state_data.shape[0] 

4765 n_shells = n_reduced_shells 

4766 n_shell_vars = self.header.n_shell_vars 

4767 

4768 # what is in the file? 

4769 n_layers = self.header.n_shell_tshell_layers 

4770 n_history_vars = self.header.n_shell_tshell_history_vars 

4771 n_stress_vars = 6 * self.header.has_shell_tshell_stress 

4772 n_pstrain_vars = 1 * self.header.has_shell_tshell_pstrain 

4773 n_force_variables = 8 * self.header.has_shell_forces 

4774 n_extra_variables = 4 * self.header.has_shell_extra_variables 

4775 n_strain_vars = 12 * self.header.has_element_strain 

4776 n_plastic_strain_tensor = 6 * n_layers * self.header.has_solid_shell_plastic_strain_tensor 

4777 n_thermal_strain_tensor = 6 * self.header.has_solid_shell_thermal_strain_tensor 

4778 

4779 try: 

4780 # this is a sanity check if the manual was understood correctly 

4781 n_shell_vars2 = ( 

4782 n_layers * (n_stress_vars + n_pstrain_vars + n_history_vars) 

4783 + n_force_variables 

4784 + n_extra_variables 

4785 + n_strain_vars 

4786 + n_plastic_strain_tensor 

4787 + n_thermal_strain_tensor 

4788 ) 

4789 

4790 if n_shell_vars != n_shell_vars2: 

4791 msg = ( 

4792 "n_shell_vars != n_shell_vars_computed: %d != %d." 

4793 " Shell variables might be wrong." 

4794 ) 

4795 LOGGER.warning(msg, n_shell_vars, n_shell_vars2) 

4796 

4797 n_layer_vars = n_layers * (n_stress_vars + n_pstrain_vars + n_history_vars) 

4798 

4799 # shell element data 

4800 shell_data = state_data[:, var_index : var_index + n_shell_vars * n_shells] 

4801 shell_data = shell_data.reshape((n_states, n_shells, n_shell_vars)) 

4802 

4803 # extract layer data 

4804 shell_layer_data = shell_data[:, :, :n_layer_vars] 

4805 shell_layer_data = shell_layer_data.reshape((n_states, n_shells, n_layers, -1)) 

4806 shell_nonlayer_data = shell_data[:, :, n_layer_vars:] 

4807 

4808 # save layer stuff 

4809 # STRESS 

4810 layer_var_index = 0 

4811 if n_stress_vars: 

4812 try: 

4813 array_dict[ArrayType.element_shell_stress] = shell_layer_data[ 

4814 :, :, :, :n_stress_vars 

4815 ].reshape((n_states, n_shells, n_layers, n_stress_vars)) 

4816 except Exception: 

4817 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

4818 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

4819 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_shells, stress", trb_msg) 

4820 finally: 

4821 layer_var_index += n_stress_vars 

4822 

4823 # PSTRAIN 

4824 if n_pstrain_vars: 

4825 try: 

4826 array_dict[ArrayType.element_shell_effective_plastic_strain] = shell_layer_data[ 

4827 :, :, :, layer_var_index 

4828 ].reshape((n_states, n_shells, n_layers)) 

4829 except Exception: 

4830 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

4831 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

4832 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_shells, stress", trb_msg) 

4833 finally: 

4834 layer_var_index += 1 

4835 

4836 # HISTORY VARIABLES 

4837 if n_history_vars: 

4838 try: 

4839 array_dict[ArrayType.element_shell_history_vars] = shell_layer_data[ 

4840 :, :, :, layer_var_index : layer_var_index + n_history_vars 

4841 ].reshape((n_states, n_shells, n_layers, n_history_vars)) 

4842 except Exception: 

4843 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

4844 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

4845 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_shells, history_variables", trb_msg) 

4846 finally: 

4847 layer_var_index += n_history_vars 

4848 

4849 # save nonlayer stuff 

4850 # forces 

4851 nonlayer_var_index = 0 

4852 if n_force_variables: 

4853 try: 

4854 array_dict[ArrayType.element_shell_bending_moment] = shell_nonlayer_data[ 

4855 :, :, 0:3 

4856 ].reshape((n_states, n_shells, 3)) 

4857 array_dict[ArrayType.element_shell_shear_force] = shell_nonlayer_data[ 

4858 :, :, 3:5 

4859 ].reshape((n_states, n_shells, 2)) 

4860 array_dict[ArrayType.element_shell_normal_force] = shell_nonlayer_data[ 

4861 :, :, 5:8 

4862 ].reshape((n_states, n_shells, 3)) 

4863 except Exception: 

4864 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

4865 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

4866 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_shells, forces", trb_msg) 

4867 finally: 

4868 nonlayer_var_index += n_force_variables 

4869 

4870 # weird stuff 

4871 if n_extra_variables: 

4872 try: 

4873 array_dict[ArrayType.element_shell_thickness] = shell_nonlayer_data[ 

4874 :, :, nonlayer_var_index 

4875 ].reshape((n_states, n_shells)) 

4876 array_dict[ArrayType.element_shell_unknown_variables] = shell_nonlayer_data[ 

4877 :, :, nonlayer_var_index + 1 : nonlayer_var_index + 3 

4878 ].reshape((n_states, n_shells, 2)) 

4879 except Exception: 

4880 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

4881 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

4882 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_shells, history_variables", trb_msg) 

4883 finally: 

4884 nonlayer_var_index += 3 

4885 

4886 # strain present 

4887 if n_strain_vars: 

4888 try: 

4889 shell_strain = shell_nonlayer_data[ 

4890 :, :, nonlayer_var_index : nonlayer_var_index + n_strain_vars 

4891 ] 

4892 array_dict[ArrayType.element_shell_strain] = shell_strain.reshape( 

4893 (n_states, n_shells, 2, 6) 

4894 ) 

4895 except Exception: 

4896 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

4897 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

4898 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_shells, strain", trb_msg) 

4899 finally: 

4900 nonlayer_var_index += n_strain_vars 

4901 

4902 # internal energy is behind strain if strain is written 

4903 if self.header.has_shell_extra_variables: 

4904 try: 

4905 array_dict[ArrayType.element_shell_internal_energy] = shell_nonlayer_data[ 

4906 :, :, nonlayer_var_index 

4907 ].reshape((n_states, n_shells)) 

4908 except Exception: 

4909 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

4910 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

4911 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_shells, internal_energy", trb_msg) 

4912 

4913 # PLASTIC STRAIN TENSOR 

4914 if n_plastic_strain_tensor: 

4915 try: 

4916 pstrain_tensor = shell_nonlayer_data[ 

4917 :, :, nonlayer_var_index : nonlayer_var_index + n_plastic_strain_tensor 

4918 ] 

4919 array_dict[ 

4920 ArrayType.element_shell_plastic_strain_tensor 

4921 ] = pstrain_tensor.reshape((n_states, n_shells, n_layers, 6)) 

4922 except Exception: 

4923 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

4924 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

4925 LOGGER.warning( 

4926 msg, "_read_states_shells, element_shell_plastic_strain_tensor", trb_msg 

4927 ) 

4928 finally: 

4929 nonlayer_var_index += n_plastic_strain_tensor 

4930 

4931 # THERMAL STRAIN TENSOR 

4932 if n_thermal_strain_tensor: 

4933 try: 

4934 thermal_tensor = shell_nonlayer_data[ 

4935 :, :, nonlayer_var_index : nonlayer_var_index + n_thermal_strain_tensor 

4936 ] 

4937 array_dict[ 

4938 ArrayType.element_shell_thermal_strain_tensor 

4939 ] = thermal_tensor.reshape((n_states, n_shells, 6)) 

4940 except Exception: 

4941 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

4942 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

4943 LOGGER.warning( 

4944 msg, "_read_states_shells, element_shell_thermal_strain_tensor", trb_msg 

4945 ) 

4946 finally: 

4947 nonlayer_var_index += n_thermal_strain_tensor 

4948 

4949 # error in formatting shell state data 

4950 except Exception: 

4951 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

4952 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

4953 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_shell, shell_state_data", trb_msg) 

4954 

4955 # always increment variable index 

4956 finally: 

4957 var_index += n_shell_vars * n_shells 

4958 

4959 LOGGER.debug("_read_states_shell end at var_index %d", var_index) 

4960 

4961 return var_index 

4962 

4963 def _read_states_is_alive( 

4964 self, state_data: np.ndarray, var_index: int, array_dict: dict 

4965 ) -> int: 

4966 """Read deletion info for nodes, elements, etc 

4967 

4968 Parameters 

4969 ---------- 

4970 state_data: np.ndarray 

4971 array with entire state data 

4972 var_index: int 

4973 variable index in the state data array 

4974 array_dict: dict 

4975 dictionary to store the loaded arrays in 

4976 

4977 Returns 

4978 ------- 

4979 var_index: int 

4980 updated variable index after reading the section 

4981 """ 

4982 

4983 if not self.header.has_node_deletion_data and not self.header.has_element_deletion_data: 

4984 return var_index 

4985 

4986 LOGGER.debug("_read_states_is_alive start at var_index %s", var_index) 

4987 

4988 n_states = state_data.shape[0] 

4989 

4990 # NODES 

4991 if self.header.has_node_deletion_data: 

4992 n_nodes = self.header.n_nodes 

4993 

4994 if n_nodes > 0: 

4995 try: 

4996 array_dict[ArrayType.node_is_alive] = state_data[ 

4997 :, var_index : var_index + n_nodes 

4998 ] 

4999 except Exception: 

5000 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

5001 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

5002 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_is_alive, nodes", trb_msg) 

5003 finally: 

5004 var_index += n_nodes 

5005 

5006 # element deletion info 

5007 elif self.header.has_element_deletion_data: 

5008 n_solids = self.header.n_solids 

5009 n_tshells = self.header.n_thick_shells 

5010 n_shells = self.header.n_shells 

5011 n_beams = self.header.n_beams 

5012 # n_elems = n_solids + n_tshells + n_shells + n_beams 

5013 

5014 # SOLIDS 

5015 if n_solids > 0: 

5016 try: 

5017 array_dict[ArrayType.element_solid_is_alive] = state_data[ 

5018 :, var_index : var_index + n_solids 

5019 ].reshape((n_states, n_solids)) 

5020 except Exception: 

5021 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

5022 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

5023 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_is_alive, solids", trb_msg) 

5024 finally: 

5025 var_index += n_solids 

5026 

5027 # TSHELLS 

5028 if n_tshells > 0: 

5029 try: 

5030 array_dict[ArrayType.element_tshell_is_alive] = state_data[ 

5031 :, var_index : var_index + n_tshells 

5032 ].reshape((n_states, n_tshells)) 

5033 except Exception: 

5034 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

5035 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

5036 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_is_alive, solids", trb_msg) 

5037 finally: 

5038 var_index += n_tshells 

5039 

5040 # SHELLS 

5041 if n_shells > 0: 

5042 try: 

5043 array_dict[ArrayType.element_shell_is_alive] = state_data[ 

5044 :, var_index : var_index + n_shells 

5045 ].reshape((n_states, n_shells)) 

5046 except Exception: 

5047 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

5048 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

5049 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_is_alive, shells", trb_msg) 

5050 finally: 

5051 var_index += n_shells 

5052 

5053 # BEAMS 

5054 if n_beams > 0: 

5055 try: 

5056 array_dict[ArrayType.element_beam_is_alive] = state_data[ 

5057 :, var_index : var_index + n_beams 

5058 ].reshape((n_states, n_beams)) 

5059 except Exception: 

5060 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

5061 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

5062 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_is_alive, beams", trb_msg) 

5063 finally: 

5064 var_index += n_beams 

5065 

5066 LOGGER.debug("_read_states_is_alive end at var_index %d", var_index) 

5067 

5068 return var_index 

5069 

5070 def _read_states_sph(self, state_data: np.ndarray, var_index: int, array_dict: dict) -> int: 

5071 """Read the sph state data 

5072 

5073 Parameters 

5074 ---------- 

5075 state_data: np.ndarray 

5076 array with entire state data 

5077 var_index: int 

5078 variable index in the state data array 

5079 array_dict: dict 

5080 dictionary to store the loaded arrays in 

5081 

5082 Returns 

5083 ------- 

5084 var_index: int 

5085 updated variable index after reading the section 

5086 """ 

5087 

5088 if self.header.n_sph_nodes <= 0: 

5089 return var_index 

5090 

5091 LOGGER.debug("_read_states_sph start at var_index %d", var_index) 

5092 

5093 info = self._sph_info 

5094 n_states = state_data.shape[0] 

5095 n_particles = self.header.n_sph_nodes 

5096 n_variables = info.n_sph_vars 

5097 

5098 # extract data 

5099 try: 

5100 sph_data = state_data[:, var_index : var_index + n_particles * n_variables] 

5101 

5102 i_var = 1 

5103 

5104 # deletion 

5105 try: 

5106 array_dict[ArrayType.sph_deletion] = sph_data[:, 0] < 0 

5107 except Exception: 

5108 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

5109 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

5110 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_sph, deletion", trb_msg) 

5111 

5112 # particle radius 

5113 if info.has_influence_radius: 

5114 try: 

5115 array_dict[ArrayType.sph_radius] = sph_data[:, i_var] 

5116 except Exception: 

5117 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

5118 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

5119 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_sph, radius", trb_msg) 

5120 finally: 

5121 i_var += 1 

5122 

5123 # pressure 

5124 if info.has_particle_pressure: 

5125 try: 

5126 array_dict[ArrayType.sph_pressure] = sph_data[:, i_var] 

5127 except Exception: 

5128 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

5129 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

5130 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_sph, pressure", trb_msg) 

5131 finally: 

5132 i_var += 1 

5133 

5134 # stress 

5135 if info.has_stresses: 

5136 try: 

5137 array_dict[ArrayType.sph_stress] = sph_data[ 

5138 :, i_var : i_var + n_particles * 6 

5139 ].reshape((n_states, n_particles, 6)) 

5140 except Exception: 

5141 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

5142 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

5143 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_sph, pressure", trb_msg) 

5144 finally: 

5145 i_var += 6 * n_particles 

5146 

5147 # eff. plastic strain 

5148 if info.has_plastic_strain: 

5149 try: 

5150 array_dict[ArrayType.sph_effective_plastic_strain] = sph_data[:, i_var] 

5151 except Exception: 

5152 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

5153 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

5154 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_sph, eff_plastic_strain", trb_msg) 

5155 finally: 

5156 i_var += 1 

5157 

5158 # density 

5159 if info.has_material_density: 

5160 try: 

5161 array_dict[ArrayType.sph_density] = sph_data[:, i_var] 

5162 except Exception: 

5163 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

5164 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

5165 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_sph, density", trb_msg) 

5166 finally: 

5167 i_var += 1 

5168 

5169 # internal energy 

5170 if info.has_internal_energy: 

5171 try: 

5172 array_dict[ArrayType.sph_internal_energy] = sph_data[:, i_var] 

5173 except Exception: 

5174 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

5175 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

5176 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_sph, internal_energy", trb_msg) 

5177 finally: 

5178 i_var += 1 

5179 

5180 # number of neighbors 

5181 if info.has_n_affecting_neighbors: 

5182 try: 

5183 array_dict[ArrayType.sph_n_neighbors] = sph_data[:, i_var] 

5184 except Exception: 

5185 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

5186 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

5187 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_sph, n_neighbors", trb_msg) 

5188 finally: 

5189 i_var += 1 

5190 

5191 # strain and strainrate 

5192 if info.has_strain_and_strainrate: 

5193 

5194 try: 

5195 array_dict[ArrayType.sph_strain] = sph_data[ 

5196 :, i_var : i_var + n_particles * 6 

5197 ].reshape((n_states, n_particles, 6)) 

5198 except Exception: 

5199 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

5200 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

5201 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_sph, strain", trb_msg) 

5202 finally: 

5203 i_var += 6 * n_particles 

5204 

5205 try: 

5206 array_dict[ArrayType.sph_strainrate] = sph_data[ 

5207 :, i_var : i_var + n_particles * 6 

5208 ].reshape((n_states, n_particles, 6)) 

5209 except Exception: 

5210 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

5211 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

5212 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_sph, strainrate", trb_msg) 

5213 finally: 

5214 i_var += 6 * n_particles 

5215 

5216 # mass 

5217 if info.has_mass: 

5218 try: 

5219 array_dict[ArrayType.sph_mass] = sph_data[:, i_var] 

5220 except Exception: 

5221 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

5222 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

5223 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_sph, pressure", trb_msg) 

5224 finally: 

5225 i_var += 1 

5226 

5227 except Exception: 

5228 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

5229 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

5230 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_sph, sph_data", trb_msg) 

5231 finally: 

5232 var_index += n_particles * n_variables 

5233 

5234 LOGGER.debug("_read_states_sph end at var_index %d", var_index) 

5235 

5236 return var_index 

5237 

5238 def _read_states_airbags(self, state_data: np.ndarray, var_index: int, array_dict: dict) -> int: 

5239 """Read the airbag state data 

5240 

5241 Parameters 

5242 ---------- 

5243 state_data: np.ndarray 

5244 array with entire state data 

5245 var_index: int 

5246 variable index in the state data array 

5247 array_dict: dict 

5248 dictionary to store the loaded arrays in 

5249 

5250 Returns 

5251 ------- 

5252 var_index: int 

5253 updated variable index after reading the section 

5254 """ 

5255 

5256 if self.header.n_airbags <= 0: 

5257 return var_index 

5258 

5259 LOGGER.debug("_read_states_airbags start at var_index %d", var_index) 

5260 

5261 n_states = state_data.shape[0] 

5262 info = self._airbag_info 

5263 n_airbag_geom_vars = info.n_geometric_variables 

5264 n_airbags = info.n_airbags 

5265 n_state_airbag_vars = info.n_airbag_state_variables 

5266 n_particles = info.n_particles 

5267 n_particle_vars = info.n_particle_state_variables 

5268 

5269 # Warning 

5270 # I am not sure if this is right ... 

5271 n_total_vars = n_airbags * n_state_airbag_vars + n_particles * n_particle_vars 

5272 

5273 try: 

5274 # types 

5275 # nlist = ngeom + nvar + nstgeom 

5276 airbag_var_types = self.arrays[ArrayType.airbag_variable_types] 

5277 airbag_var_names = self.arrays[ArrayType.airbag_variable_names] 

5278 # geom_var_types = airbag_var_types[:n_airbag_geom_vars] 

5279 particle_var_types = airbag_var_types[ 

5280 n_airbag_geom_vars : n_airbag_geom_vars + n_particle_vars 

5281 ] 

5282 particle_var_names = airbag_var_names[ 

5283 n_airbag_geom_vars : n_airbag_geom_vars + n_particle_vars 

5284 ] 

5285 

5286 airbag_state_var_types = airbag_var_types[n_airbag_geom_vars + n_particle_vars :] 

5287 airbag_state_var_names = airbag_var_names[n_airbag_geom_vars + n_particle_vars :] 

5288 

5289 # required for dynamic reading 

5290 def get_dtype(type_flag): 

5291 return self._header.itype if type_flag == 1 else self.header.ftype 

5292 

5293 # extract airbag data 

5294 airbag_state_data = state_data[:, var_index : var_index + n_total_vars] 

5295 

5296 # airbag data 

5297 airbag_data = airbag_state_data[:, : n_airbags * n_state_airbag_vars].reshape( 

5298 (n_states, n_airbags, n_state_airbag_vars) 

5299 ) 

5300 airbag_state_offset = n_airbags * n_state_airbag_vars 

5301 

5302 # particle data 

5303 particle_data = airbag_state_data[ 

5304 :, airbag_state_offset : airbag_state_offset + n_particles * n_particle_vars 

5305 ].reshape((n_states, n_particles, n_particle_vars)) 

5306 

5307 # save sh... 

5308 

5309 # airbag state vars 

5310 for i_airbag_state_var in range(n_state_airbag_vars): 

5311 var_name = airbag_state_var_names[i_airbag_state_var].strip() 

5312 var_type = airbag_state_var_types[i_airbag_state_var] 

5313 

5314 if var_name.startswith("Act Gas"): 

5315 try: 

5316 array_dict[ArrayType.airbag_n_active_particles] = airbag_data[ 

5317 :, :, i_airbag_state_var 

5318 ].view(get_dtype(var_type)) 

5319 except Exception: 

5320 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

5321 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

5322 LOGGER.warning( 

5323 msg, "_read_states_airbags, airbag_n_active_particles", trb_msg 

5324 ) 

5325 elif var_name.startswith("Bag Vol"): 

5326 try: 

5327 array_dict[ArrayType.airbag_bag_volume] = airbag_data[ 

5328 :, :, i_airbag_state_var 

5329 ].view(get_dtype(var_type)) 

5330 except Exception: 

5331 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

5332 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

5333 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_airbags, airbag_volume", trb_msg) 

5334 else: 

5335 warn_msg = "Unknown airbag state var: '%s'. Skipping it." 

5336 LOGGER.warning(warn_msg, var_name) 

5337 

5338 # particles yay 

5339 for i_particle_var in range(n_particle_vars): 

5340 var_type = particle_var_types[i_particle_var] 

5341 var_name = particle_var_names[i_particle_var].strip() 

5342 

5343 # particle gas id 

5344 if var_name.startswith("GasC ID"): 

5345 try: 

5346 array_dict[ArrayType.airbag_particle_gas_id] = particle_data[ 

5347 :, :, i_particle_var 

5348 ].view(get_dtype(var_type)) 

5349 except Exception: 

5350 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

5351 msg = "A failure in %s %s was caught:\n%s" 

5352 LOGGER.warning( 

5353 msg, "_read_states_airbags, particle_gas_id", var_name, trb_msg 

5354 ) 

5355 # particle chamber id 

5356 elif var_name.startswith("Cham ID"): 

5357 try: 

5358 array_dict[ArrayType.airbag_particle_chamber_id] = particle_data[ 

5359 :, :, i_particle_var 

5360 ].view(get_dtype(var_type)) 

5361 except Exception: 

5362 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

5363 msg = "A failure in %s %s was caught:\n%s" 

5364 LOGGER.warning( 

5365 msg, "_read_states_airbags, particle_gas_id", var_name, trb_msg 

5366 ) 

5367 # particle leakage 

5368 elif var_name.startswith("Leakage"): 

5369 try: 

5370 array_dict[ArrayType.airbag_particle_leakage] = particle_data[ 

5371 :, :, i_particle_var 

5372 ].view(get_dtype(var_type)) 

5373 except Exception: 

5374 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

5375 msg = "A failure in %s %s was caught:\n%s" 

5376 LOGGER.warning( 

5377 msg, "_read_states_airbags, particle_gas_id", var_name, trb_msg 

5378 ) 

5379 # particle mass 

5380 elif var_name.startswith("Mass"): 

5381 try: 

5382 array_dict[ArrayType.airbag_particle_mass] = particle_data[ 

5383 :, :, i_particle_var 

5384 ].view(get_dtype(var_type)) 

5385 except Exception: 

5386 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

5387 msg = "A failure in %s %s was caught:\n%s" 

5388 LOGGER.warning( 

5389 msg, "_read_states_airbags, particle_gas_id", var_name, trb_msg 

5390 ) 

5391 # particle radius 

5392 try: 

5393 array_dict[ArrayType.airbag_particle_radius] = particle_data[ 

5394 :, :, i_particle_var 

5395 ].view(get_dtype(var_type)) 

5396 except Exception: 

5397 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

5398 msg = "A failure in %s %s was caught:\n%s" 

5399 LOGGER.warning( 

5400 msg, "_read_states_airbags, particle_gas_id", var_name, trb_msg 

5401 ) 

5402 # particle spin energy 

5403 elif var_name.startswith("Spin En"): 

5404 try: 

5405 array_dict[ArrayType.airbag_particle_spin_energy] = particle_data[ 

5406 :, :, i_particle_var 

5407 ].view(get_dtype(var_type)) 

5408 except Exception: 

5409 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

5410 msg = "A failure in %s %s was caught:\n%s" 

5411 LOGGER.warning( 

5412 msg, "_read_states_airbags, particle_gas_id", var_name, trb_msg 

5413 ) 

5414 # particle translational energy 

5415 elif var_name.startswith("Tran En"): 

5416 try: 

5417 array_dict[ArrayType.airbag_particle_translation_energy] = particle_data[ 

5418 :, :, i_particle_var 

5419 ].view(get_dtype(var_type)) 

5420 except Exception: 

5421 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

5422 msg = "A failure in %s %s was caught:\n%s" 

5423 LOGGER.warning( 

5424 msg, "_read_states_airbags, particle_gas_id", var_name, trb_msg 

5425 ) 

5426 # particle segment distance 

5427 elif var_name.startswith("NS dist"): 

5428 try: 

5429 array_dict[ 

5430 ArrayType.airbag_particle_nearest_segment_distance 

5431 ] = particle_data[:, :, i_particle_var].view(get_dtype(var_type)) 

5432 except Exception: 

5433 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

5434 msg = "A failure in %s %s was caught:\n%s" 

5435 LOGGER.warning( 

5436 msg, "_read_states_airbags, particle_gas_id", var_name, trb_msg 

5437 ) 

5438 # particle position 

5439 elif var_name.startswith("Pos x"): 

5440 try: 

5441 particle_var_names_stripped = [ 

5442 entry.strip() for entry in particle_var_names 

5443 ] 

5444 i_particle_var_x = i_particle_var 

5445 i_particle_var_y = particle_var_names_stripped.index("Pos y") 

5446 i_particle_var_z = particle_var_names_stripped.index("Pos z") 

5447 

5448 array_dict[ArrayType.airbag_particle_position] = particle_data[ 

5449 :, :, (i_particle_var_x, i_particle_var_y, i_particle_var_z) 

5450 ].view(get_dtype(var_type)) 

5451 except Exception: 

5452 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

5453 msg = "A failure in %s %s was caught:\n%s" 

5454 LOGGER.warning( 

5455 msg, "_read_states_airbags, particle_gas_id", var_name, trb_msg 

5456 ) 

5457 elif var_name.startswith("Pos y"): 

5458 # handled in Pos x 

5459 pass 

5460 elif var_name.startswith("Pos z"): 

5461 # handled in Pos x 

5462 pass 

5463 # particle velocity 

5464 elif var_name.startswith("Vel x"): 

5465 try: 

5466 particle_var_names_stripped = [ 

5467 entry.strip() for entry in particle_var_names 

5468 ] 

5469 i_particle_var_x = i_particle_var 

5470 i_particle_var_y = particle_var_names_stripped.index("Vel y") 

5471 i_particle_var_z = particle_var_names_stripped.index("Vel z") 

5472 

5473 array_dict[ArrayType.airbag_particle_velocity] = particle_data[ 

5474 :, :, (i_particle_var_x, i_particle_var_y, i_particle_var_z) 

5475 ].view(get_dtype(var_type)) 

5476 except Exception: 

5477 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

5478 msg = "A failure in %s %s was caught:\n%s" 

5479 LOGGER.warning( 

5480 msg, "_read_states_airbags, particle_gas_id", var_name, trb_msg 

5481 ) 

5482 

5483 except Exception:

5485 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

5486 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_airbags, particle_data", trb_msg) 

5487 finally: 

5488 var_index += n_total_vars 

5489 

5490 LOGGER.debug("_read_states_airbags end at var_index %d", var_index) 

5491 

5492 return var_index

5494 def _read_states_road_surfaces( 

5495 self, state_data: np.ndarray, var_index: int, array_dict: dict 

5496 ) -> int: 

5497 """Read the road surfaces state data for whoever wants this ... 

5498 

5499 Parameters 

5500 ---------- 

5501 state_data: np.ndarray 

5502 array with entire state data 

5503 var_index: int 

5504 variable index in the state data array 

5505 array_dict: dict 

5506 dictionary to store the loaded arrays in 

5507 

5508 Returns 

5509 ------- 

5510 var_index: int 

5511 updated variable index after reading the section 

5512 """ 

5513 

5514 if not self.header.has_rigid_road_surface: 

5515 return var_index 

5516 

5517 LOGGER.debug("_read_states_road_surfaces start at var_index %s", var_index) 

5518 

5519 n_states = state_data.shape[0] 

5520 info = self._rigid_road_info 

5521 n_roads = info.n_roads 

5522 

5523 try: 

5524 # read road data 

5525 road_data = state_data[:, var_index : var_index + 6 * n_roads].reshape( 

5526 (n_states, n_roads, 2, 3) 

5527 ) 

5528 

5529 # DISPLACEMENT 

5530 try: 

5531 array_dict[ArrayType.rigid_road_displacement] = road_data[:, :, 0, :] 

5532 except Exception: 

5533 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

5534 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

5535 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_road_surfaces, road_displacement", trb_msg) 

5536 

5537 # VELOCITY 

5538 try: 

5539 array_dict[ArrayType.rigid_road_velocity] = road_data[:, :, 1, :] 

5540 except Exception: 

5541 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

5542 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

5543 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_road_surfaces, road_velocity", trb_msg) 

5544 

5545 except Exception: 

5546 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

5547 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

5548 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_road_surfaces, road_data", trb_msg) 

5549 finally: 

5550 var_index += 6 * n_roads 

5551 

5552 LOGGER.debug("_read_states_road_surfaces end at var_index %d", var_index) 

5553 

5554 return var_index
