5556 def _read_states_rigid_body_motion( 

5557 self, state_data: np.ndarray, var_index: int, array_dict: dict 

5558 ) -> int: 

5559 """Read the road surfaces state data for whoever want this ... 

5560 

5561 Parameters 

5562 ---------- 

5563 state_data: np.ndarray 

5564 array with entire state data 

5565 var_index: int 

5566 variable index in the state data array 

5567 array_dict: dict 

5568 dictionary to store the loaded arrays in 

5569 

5570 Returns 

5571 ------- 

5572 var_index: int 

5573 updated variable index after reading the section 

5574 """ 

5575 

5576 if not self.header.has_rigid_body_data: 

5577 return var_index 

5578 

5579 LOGGER.debug("_read_states_rigid_body_motion start at var_index %d", var_index) 

5580 

5581 info = self._rigid_body_info 

5582 n_states = state_data.shape[0] 

5583 n_rigids = info.n_rigid_bodies 

5584 n_rigid_vars = 12 if self.header.has_reduced_rigid_body_data else 24 

5585 

5586 try: 

5587 # do the thing 

5588 rigid_body_data = state_data[ 

5589 :, var_index : var_index + n_rigids * n_rigid_vars 

5590 ].reshape((n_states, n_rigids, n_rigid_vars)) 

5591 

5592 # let the party begin 

5593 # rigid coordinates 

5594 try: 

5595 array_dict[ArrayType.rigid_body_coordinates] = rigid_body_data[:, :, :3] 

5596 except Exception: 

5597 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

5598 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

5599 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_rigid_body_motion, coordinates", trb_msg) 

5600 finally: 

5601 i_var = 3 

5602 

5603 # rotation matrix 

5604 try: 

5605 array_dict[ArrayType.rigid_body_rotation_matrix] = rigid_body_data[ 

5606 :, :, i_var : i_var + 9 

5607 ] 

5608 except Exception: 

5609 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

5610 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

5611 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_rigid_body_motion, rot_matrix", trb_msg) 

5612 finally: 

5613 i_var += 9 

5614 

5615 if self.header.has_reduced_rigid_body_data: 

5616 return var_index 

5617 

5618 # velocity pewpew 

5619 try: 

5620 array_dict[ArrayType.rigid_body_velocity] = rigid_body_data[:, :, i_var : i_var + 3] 

5621 except Exception: 

5622 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

5623 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

5624 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_rigid_body_motion, velocity", trb_msg) 

5625 finally: 

5626 i_var += 3 

5627 

5628 # rotational velocity 

5629 try: 

5630 array_dict[ArrayType.rigid_body_rot_velocity] = rigid_body_data[ 

5631 :, :, i_var : i_var + 3 

5632 ] 

5633 except Exception: 

5634 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

5635 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

5636 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_rigid_body_motion, rot_velocity", trb_msg) 

5637 finally: 

5638 i_var += 3 

5639 

5640 # acceleration 

5641 try: 

5642 array_dict[ArrayType.rigid_body_acceleration] = rigid_body_data[ 

5643 :, :, i_var : i_var + 3 

5644 ] 

5645 except Exception: 

5646 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

5647 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

5648 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_rigid_body_motion, acceleration", trb_msg) 

5649 finally: 

5650 i_var += 3 

5651 

5652 # rotational acceleration 

5653 try: 

5654 array_dict[ArrayType.rigid_body_rot_acceleration] = rigid_body_data[ 

5655 :, :, i_var : i_var + 3 

5656 ] 

5657 except Exception: 

5658 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

5659 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

5660 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_rigid_body_motion, rot_acceleration", trb_msg) 

5661 finally: 

5662 i_var += 3 

5663 

5664 except Exception: 

5665 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

5666 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

5667 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_read_states_rigid_body_motion, rigid_body_data", trb_msg) 

5668 

5669 finally: 

5670 var_index += n_rigids * n_rigid_vars 

5671 

5672 LOGGER.debug("_read_states_rigid_body_motion end at var_index %d", var_index) 

5673 

5674 return var_index 

5675 

5676 def _collect_file_infos(self, size_per_state: int) -> List[MemoryInfo]: 

5677 """This routine collects the memory and file info for the d3plot files 

5678 

5679 Parameters 

5680 ---------- 

5681 size_per_state: int 

5682 size of every state to be read 

5683 

5684 Returns 

5685 ------- 

5686 memory_infos: List[MemoryInfo] 

5687 memory infos about the states 

5688 

5689 Notes 

5690 ----- 

5691 State data is expected directly behind geometry data 

5692 Unfortunately data is spread across multiple files. 

5693 One file could contain geometry and state data but states 

5694 may also be littered accross several files. This would 

5695 not be an issue, if dyna would not always write in blocks 

5696 of 512 words of memory, leaving zero byte padding blocks 

5697 at the end of files. These need to be removed and/or taken 

5698 care of. 

5699 """ 

5700 

5701 if not self._buffer: 

5702 return [] 

5703 

5704 base_filepath = self.header.filepath 

5705 

5706 # bugfix 

5707 # If you encounter these int casts more often here this is why: 

5708 # Some ints around here are numpy.int32 which can overflow 

5709 # (sometimes there is a warning ... sometimes not ...) 

5710 # we cast to python ints in order to prevent overflow. 

5711 size_per_state = int(size_per_state) 

5712 

5713 # Info: 

5714 # 

5715 # We need to determine here how many states are in every file 

5716 # without really loading the file itself. For big files this is 

5717 # simply filesize // state_size. 

5718 # For files though with a smaller filesize this may cause issues 

5719 # e.g. 

5720 # filesize 2048 bytes (minimum filesize from dyna) 

5721 # geom_size 200 bytes 

5722 # state_size 200 bytes 

5723 # File contains: 

5724 # -> 1 state * state_size + geom_size = 400 bytes 

5725 # Wrong State Estimation: 

5726 # -> (filesize - geom_size) // state_size = 9 states != 1 state 

5727 # 

5728 # To avoid this wrong number of states when reading small files 

5729 # we need to search the end mark (here nonzero byte) from the rear 

5730 # of the file. 

5731 # This though needs the file to be loaded into memory. To make this 

5732 # very light, we simply memorymap a small fraction of the file starting 

5733 # from the rear until we have our nonzero byte. Since the end mark 

5734 # is usually in the first block loaded, there should not be any performance 

5735 # concerns, even with bigger files. 

5736 

5737 # query for state files 

5738 filepaths = D3plot._find_dyna_result_files(base_filepath) 

5739 

5740 # compute state data in first file 

5741 # search therefore the first non-zero byte from the rear 

5742 last_nonzero_byte_index = self._buffer.size 

5743 mview_inv_arr = np.asarray(self._buffer.memoryview[::-1]) 

5744 # pylint: disable = invalid-name 

5745 BLOCK_SIZE = 2048 

5746 for start in range(0, self._buffer.size, BLOCK_SIZE): 

5747 (nz_indexes,) = np.nonzero(mview_inv_arr[start : start + BLOCK_SIZE]) 

5748 if len(nz_indexes): 

5749 last_nonzero_byte_index = self._buffer.size - (start + nz_indexes[0]) 

5750 break 

5751 n_states_beyond_geom = ( 

5752 last_nonzero_byte_index - self.geometry_section_size 

5753 ) // size_per_state 

5754 

5755 # bugfix: if states are too big we can get a negative estimation 

5756 n_states_beyond_geom = max(0, n_states_beyond_geom) 

5757 

5758 # memory required later 

5759 memory_infos = [ 

5760 MemoryInfo( 

5761 start=self.geometry_section_size, # type: ignore 

5762 length=n_states_beyond_geom * size_per_state, # type: ignore 

5763 filepath=base_filepath, 

5764 n_states=n_states_beyond_geom, # type: ignore 

5765 filesize=self._buffer.size, 

5766 use_mmap=True, 

5767 ) 

5768 ] 

5769 

5770 # compute amount of state data in every further file 

5771 for filepath in filepaths: 

5772 filesize = os.path.getsize(filepath) 

5773 last_nonzero_byte_index = -1 

5774 

5775 n_blocks = filesize // mmap.ALLOCATIONGRANULARITY 

5776 rest_size = filesize % mmap.ALLOCATIONGRANULARITY 

5777 block_length = mmap.ALLOCATIONGRANULARITY 

5778 with open(filepath, "rb") as fp: 

5779 

5780 # search last rest block (page-aligned) 

5781 # page-aligned means the start must be 

5782 # a multiple of mmap.ALLOCATIONGRANULARITY 

5783 # otherwise we get an error on linux 

5784 if rest_size: 

5785 start = n_blocks * block_length 

5786 mview = memoryview( 

5787 mmap.mmap( 

5788 fp.fileno(), offset=start, length=rest_size, access=mmap.ACCESS_READ 

5789 ).read() 

5790 ) 

5791 (nz_indexes,) = np.nonzero(mview[::-1]) 

5792 if len(nz_indexes): 

5793 last_nonzero_byte_index = start + rest_size - nz_indexes[0] 

5794 

5795 # search in blocks from the reair 

5796 if last_nonzero_byte_index == -1: 

5797 for i_block in range(n_blocks - 1, -1, -1): 

5798 start = block_length * i_block 

5799 mview = memoryview( 

5800 mmap.mmap( 

5801 fp.fileno(), 

5802 offset=start, 

5803 length=block_length, 

5804 access=mmap.ACCESS_READ, 

5805 ).read() 

5806 ) 

5807 (nz_indexes,) = np.nonzero(mview[::-1]) 

5808 if len(nz_indexes): 

5809 index = block_length - nz_indexes[0] 

5810 last_nonzero_byte_index = start + index 

5811 break 

5812 

5813 if last_nonzero_byte_index == -1: 

5814 msg = "The file {0} seems to be missing it's endmark." 

5815 raise RuntimeError(msg.format(filepath)) 

5816 

5817 # BUGFIX 

5818 # In d3eigv it could be observed that there is not necessarily an end mark. 

5819 # As a consequence the last byte can indeed be zero. We control this by 

5820 # checking if the last nonzero byte was smaller than the state size which 

5821 # makes no sense. 

5822 if ( 

5823 self.header.filetype == D3plotFiletype.D3EIGV 

5824 and last_nonzero_byte_index < size_per_state <= filesize 

5825 ): 

5826 last_nonzero_byte_index = size_per_state 

5827 

5828 n_states_in_file = last_nonzero_byte_index // size_per_state 

5829 memory_infos.append( 

5830 MemoryInfo( 

5831 start=0, 

5832 length=size_per_state * (n_states_in_file), 

5833 filepath=filepath, 

5834 n_states=n_states_in_file, 

5835 filesize=filesize, 

5836 use_mmap=False, 

5837 ) 

5838 ) 

5839 

5840 return memory_infos 

5841 

5842 @staticmethod 

5843 def _read_file_from_memory_info( 

5844 memory_infos: Union[MemoryInfo, List[MemoryInfo]] 

5845 ) -> Tuple[BinaryBuffer, int]: 

5846 """Read files from a single or multiple memory infos 

5847 

5848 Parameters 

5849 ---------- 

5850 memory_infos: MemoryInfo or List[MemoryInfo] 

5851 memory infos for loading a file (see `D3plot._collect_file_infos`) 

5852 

5853 Returns 

5854 ------- 

5855 bb_states: BinaryBuffer 

5856 New binary buffer with all states perfectly linear in memory 

5857 n_states: int 

5858 Number of states to be expected 

5859 

5860 Notes 

5861 ----- 

5862 This routine in contrast to `D3plot._read_state_bytebuffer` is used 

5863 to load only a fraction of files into memory. 

5864 """ 

5865 

5866 # single file case 

5867 if isinstance(memory_infos, MemoryInfo): 

5868 memory_infos = [memory_infos] 

5869 

5870 # allocate memory 

5871 # bugfix: casting to int prevents int32 overflow for large files 

5872 memory_required = 0 

5873 for mem in memory_infos: 

5874 memory_required += int(mem.length) 

5875 mview = memoryview(bytearray(memory_required)) 

5876 

5877 # transfer memory for other files 

5878 n_states = 0 

5879 total_offset = 0 

5880 for minfo in memory_infos: 

5881 LOGGER.debug("opening: %s", minfo.filepath) 

5882 

5883 with open(minfo.filepath, "br") as fp: 

5884 # NOTE 

5885 # mmap is too slow but maybe there are faster 

5886 # ways to use mmap correctly 

5887 # if minfo.use_mmap: 

5888 

5889 # # memory mapping can only be done page aligned 

5890 # mmap_start = (minfo.start // mmap.ALLOCATIONGRANULARITY) * \ 

5891 # mmap.ALLOCATIONGRANULARITY 

5892 # mview_start = minfo.start - mmap_start 

5893 

5894 # end = minfo.start + minfo.length 

5895 # n_end_pages = (end // mmap.ALLOCATIONGRANULARITY + 

5896 # (end % mmap.ALLOCATIONGRANULARITY != 0)) 

5897 # mmap_length = n_end_pages * mmap.ALLOCATIONGRANULARITY - mmap_start 

5898 # if mmap_start + mmap_length > minfo.filesize: 

5899 # mmap_length = minfo.filesize - mmap_start 

5900 

5901 # with mmap.mmap(fp.fileno(), 

5902 # length=mmap_length, 

5903 # offset=mmap_start, 

5904 # access=mmap.ACCESS_READ) as mp: 

5905 # # mp.seek(mview_start) 

5906 # # mview[total_offset:total_offset + 

5907 # # minfo.length] = mp.read(minfo.length) 

5908 

5909 # mview[total_offset:total_offset + 

5910 # minfo.length] = mp[mview_start:mview_start + minfo.length] 

5911 

5912 # else: 

5913 fp.seek(minfo.start) 

5914 fp.readinto(mview[total_offset : total_offset + minfo.length]) # type: ignore 

5915 

5916 total_offset += minfo.length 

5917 n_states += minfo.n_states 

5918 

5919 # save 

5920 bb_states = BinaryBuffer() 

5921 bb_states.memoryview = mview 

5922 

5923 return bb_states, n_states 

5924 

5925 def _read_state_bytebuffer(self, size_per_state: int): 

5926 """This routine reads the data for state information 

5927 

5928 Parameters 

5929 ---------- 

5930 size_per_state: int 

5931 size of every state to be read 

5932 

5933 Returns 

5934 ------- 

5935 bb_states: BinaryBuffer 

5936 New binary buffer with all states perfectly linear in memory 

5937 n_states: int 

5938 Number of states to be expected 

5939 

5940 Notes 

5941 ----- 

5942 State data is expected directly behind geometry data 

5943 Unfortunately data is spread across multiple files. 

5944 One file could contain geometry and state data but states 

5945 may also be littered accross several files. This would 

5946 not be an issue, if dyna would not always write in blocks 

5947 of 512 words of memory, leaving zero byte padding blocks 

5948 at the end of files. These need to be removed and/or taken 

5949 care of. 

5950 """ 

5951 

5952 if not self._buffer: 

5953 return BinaryBuffer(), 0 

5954 

5955 memory_infos = self._collect_file_infos(size_per_state) 

5956 

5957 # allocate memory 

5958 # bugfix: casting to int prevents int32 overflow for large files 

5959 memory_required = 0 

5960 for mem in memory_infos: 

5961 memory_required += int(mem.length) 

5962 mview = memoryview(bytearray(memory_required)) 

5963 

5964 # transfer memory from first file 

5965 n_states = memory_infos[0].n_states 

5966 start = memory_infos[0].start 

5967 length = memory_infos[0].length 

5968 end = start + length 

5969 mview[:length] = self._buffer.memoryview[start:end] 

5970 

5971 # transfer memory for other files 

5972 total_offset = length 

5973 for minfo in memory_infos[1:]: 

5974 with open(minfo.filepath, "br") as fp: 

5975 fp.seek(minfo.start) 

5976 fp.readinto(mview[total_offset : total_offset + length]) # type: ignore 

5977 

5978 total_offset += length 

5979 n_states += minfo.n_states 

5980 

5981 # save 

5982 bb_states = BinaryBuffer() 

5983 bb_states.memoryview = mview 

5984 return bb_states, n_states 

5985 

5986 @staticmethod 

5987 def _find_dyna_result_files(filepath: str): 

5988 """Searches all dyna result files 

5989 

5990 Parameters 

5991 ---------- 

5992 filepath: str 

5993 path to the first basic d3plot file 

5994 

5995 Returns 

5996 ------- 

5997 filepaths: list of str 

5998 path to all dyna files 

5999 

6000 Notes 

6001 ----- 

6002 The dyna files usually follow a scheme to 

6003 simply have the base name and numbers appended 

6004 e.g. (d3plot, d3plot0001, d3plot0002, etc.) 

6005 """ 

6006 

6007 file_dir = os.path.dirname(filepath) 

6008 file_dir = file_dir if len(file_dir) != 0 else "." 

6009 file_basename = os.path.basename(filepath) 

6010 

6011 pattern = f"({file_basename})[0-9]+$" 

6012 reg = re.compile(pattern) 

6013 

6014 filepaths = [ 

6015 os.path.join(file_dir, path) 

6016 for path in os.listdir(file_dir) 

6017 if os.path.isfile(os.path.join(file_dir, path)) and reg.match(path) 

6018 ] 

6019 

6020 # alphasort files to handle d3plots with more than 100 files 

6021 # e.g. d3plot01, d3plot02, ..., d3plot100 

6022 def convert(text): 

6023 return int(text) if text.isdigit() else text.lower() 

6024 

6025 number_pattern = "([0-9]+)" 

6026 

6027 def alphanum_key(key): 

6028 return [convert(c) for c in re.split(number_pattern, key)] 

6029 

6030 return sorted(filepaths, key=alphanum_key) 

6031 

6032 def _determine_wordsize(self): 

6033 """Determine the precision of the file 

6034 

6035 Returns 

6036 ------- 

6037 wordsize: int 

6038 size of each word in bytes 

6039 """ 

6040 

6041 if not self._buffer: 

6042 return 4, np.int32, np.float32 

6043 

6044 # test file type flag (1=d3plot, 5=d3part, 11=d3eigv) 

6045 

6046 # single precision 

6047 value = self._buffer.read_number(44, np.int32) 

6048 if value > 1000: 

6049 value -= 1000 

6050 if value in (1, 5, 11): 

6051 return 4, np.int32, np.float32 

6052 

6053 # double precision 

6054 value = self._buffer.read_number(88, np.int64) 

6055 if value > 1000: 

6056 value -= 1000 

6057 if value in (1, 5, 11): 

6058 return 8, np.int64, np.float64 

6059 

6060 raise RuntimeError(f"Unknown file type '{value}'.") 

6061 

6062 def plot( 

6063 self, 

6064 i_timestep: int = 0, 

6065 field: Union[np.ndarray, None] = None, 

6066 is_element_field: bool = True, 

6067 fringe_limits: Union[Tuple[float, float], None] = None, 

6068 export_filepath: str = "", 

6069 ): 

6070 """Plot the d3plot geometry 

6071 

6072 Parameters 

6073 ---------- 

6074 i_timestep: int 

6075 timestep index to plot 

6076 field: Union[np.ndarray, None] 

6077 Array containing a field value for every element or node 

6078 is_element_field: bool 

6079 if the specified field is for elements or nodes 

6080 fringe_limits: Union[Tuple[float, float], None] 

6081 limits for the fringe bar. Set by default to min and max. 

6082 export_filepath: str 

6083 filepath to export the html to 

6084 

6085 Notes 

6086 ----- 

6087 Currently only shell elements can be plotted, since for 

6088 solids the surface needs extraction. 

6089 

6090 Examples 

6091 -------- 

6092 Plot deformation of last timestep. 

6093 

6094 >>> d3plot = D3plot("path/to/d3plot") 

6095 >>> d3plot.plot(-1) 

6096 >>> # get eff. plastic strain 

6097 >>> pstrain = d3plot.arrays[ArrayType.element_shell_effective_plastic_strain] 

6098 >>> pstrain.shape 

6099 (1, 4696, 3) 

6100 >>> # mean across all 3 integration points 

6101 >>> pstrain = pstrain.mean(axis=2) 

6102 >>> pstrain.shape 

6103 (1, 4696) 

6104 >>> # we only have 1 timestep here but let's take last one in general 

6105 >>> last_timestep = -1 

6106 >>> d3plot.plot(0, field=pstrain[last_timestep]) 

6107 >>> # we don't like the fringe, let's adjust 

6108 >>> d3plot.plot(0, field=pstrain[last_timestep], fringe_limits=(0, 0.3)) 

6109 """ 

6110 

6111 assert i_timestep < self._state_info.n_timesteps 

6112 assert ArrayType.node_displacement in self.arrays 

6113 if fringe_limits: 

6114 assert len(fringe_limits) == 2 

6115 

6116 # shell nodes 

6117 shell_node_indexes = self.arrays[ArrayType.element_shell_node_indexes] 

6118 

6119 # get node displacement 

6120 node_xyz = self.arrays[ArrayType.node_displacement][i_timestep, :, :] 

6121 

6122 # check for correct field size 

6123 if isinstance(field, np.ndarray): 

6124 assert field.ndim == 1 

6125 if is_element_field and len(shell_node_indexes) != len(field): # type: ignore 

6126 msg = "Element indexes and field have different len: {} != {}" 

6127 raise ValueError(msg.format(shell_node_indexes.shape, field.shape)) 

6128 if not is_element_field and len(node_xyz) != len(field): # type: ignore 

6129 msg = "Node field and coords have different len: {} != {}" 

6130 raise ValueError(msg.format(node_xyz.shape, field.shape)) 

6131 

6132 # create plot 

6133 _html = plot_shell_mesh( 

6134 node_coordinates=node_xyz, 

6135 shell_node_indexes=shell_node_indexes, 

6136 field=field, 

6137 is_element_field=is_element_field, 

6138 fringe_limits=fringe_limits, 

6139 ) 

6140 

6141 # store in a temporary file 

6142 tempdir = tempfile.gettempdir() 

6143 tempdir = os.path.join(tempdir, "lasso") 

6144 if not os.path.isdir(tempdir): 

6145 os.mkdir(tempdir) 

6146 

6147 for tmpfile in os.listdir(tempdir): 

6148 tmpfile = os.path.join(tempdir, tmpfile) 

6149 if os.path.isfile(tmpfile): 

6150 os.remove(tmpfile) 

6151 

6152 if export_filepath: 

6153 with open(export_filepath, "w", encoding="utf-8") as fp: 

6154 fp.write(_html) 

6155 else: 

6156 # create new temp file 

6157 with tempfile.NamedTemporaryFile( 

6158 dir=tempdir, suffix=".html", mode="w", delete=False 

6159 ) as fp: 

6160 fp.write(_html) 

6161 webbrowser.open(fp.name) 

6162 

6163 def write_d3plot( 

6164 self, filepath: Union[str, BinaryIO], block_size_bytes: int = 2048, single_file: bool = True 

6165 ): 

6166 """Write a d3plot file again **(pro version only)** 

6167 

6168 Parameters 

6169 ---------- 

6170 filepath: Union[str, BinaryIO] 

6171 filepath of the new d3plot file or an opened file handle 

6172 block_size_bytes: int 

6173 D3plots are originally written in byte-blocks causing zero-padding at the end of 

6174 files. This can be controlled by this parameter. Set to 0 for no padding. 

6175 single_file: bool 

6176 whether to write all states into a single file 

6177 

6178 Examples 

6179 -------- 

6180 Modify an existing d3plot: 

6181 

6182 >>> d3plot = D3plot("path/to/d3plot") 

6183 >>> hvars = d3plot.array[ArrayType.element_shell_history_vars] 

6184 >>> hvars.shape 

6185 (1, 4696, 3, 19) 

6186 >>> new_history_var = np.random.random((1, 4696, 3, 1)) 

6187 >>> new_hvars = np.concatenate([hvars, new_history_var], axis=3) 

6188 >>> d3plot.array[ArrayType.element_shell_history_vars] = new_hvars 

6189 >>> d3plot.write_d3plot("path/to/new/d3plot") 

6190 

6191 Write a new d3plot from scratch: 

6192 

6193 >>> d3plot = D3plot() 

6194 >>> d3plot.arrays[ArrayType.node_coordinates] = np.array([[0, 0, 0], 

6195 ... [1, 0, 0], 

6196 ... [0, 1, 0]]) 

6197 >>> d3plot.arrays[ArrayType.element_shell_node_indexes] = np.array([[0, 2, 1, 1]]) 

6198 >>> d3plot.arrays[ArrayType.element_shell_part_indexes] = np.array([0]) 

6199 >>> d3plot.arrays[ArrayType.node_displacement] = np.array([[[0, 0, 0], 

6200 ... [1, 0, 0], 

6201 ... [0, 1, 0]]]) 

6202 >>> d3plot.write_d3plot("yay.d3plot") 

6203 

6204 Notes 

6205 ----- 

6206 This function is not available in the public version please contact 

6207 LASSO directly in case of further interest. 

6208 """ 

6209 

6210 # if there is a single buffer, write all in 

6211 if not isinstance(filepath, str): 

6212 single_file = True 

6213 

6214 # determine write settings 

6215 write_settings = D3plotWriterSettings(self, block_size_bytes, single_file) 

6216 write_settings.build_header() 

6217 

6218 # remove old files 

6219 if isinstance(filepath, str): 

6220 filepaths = D3plot._find_dyna_result_files(filepath) 

6221 for path in filepaths: 

6222 if os.path.isfile(path): 

6223 os.remove(path) 

6224 

6225 # write geometry file 

6226 with open_file_or_filepath(filepath, "wb") as fp: 

6227 

6228 n_bytes_written = 0 

6229 msg = "wrote {0} after {1}." 

6230 

6231 # header 

6232 n_bytes_written += self._write_header(fp, write_settings) 

6233 LOGGER.debug(msg, n_bytes_written, "_write_header") 

6234 

6235 # material section 

6236 n_bytes_written += self._write_geom_material_section(fp, write_settings) 

6237 LOGGER.debug(msg, n_bytes_written, "_write_geom_material_section") 

6238 

6239 # fluid material data 

6240 n_bytes_written += self._write_geom_fluid_material_header(fp, write_settings) 

6241 LOGGER.debug(msg, n_bytes_written, "_write_geom_fluid_material_header") 

6242 

6243 # SPH element data flags 

6244 n_bytes_written += self._write_geom_sph_element_data_flags(fp, write_settings) 

6245 LOGGER.debug(msg, n_bytes_written, "_write_geom_sph_element_data_flags") 

6246 

6247 # Particle Data 

6248 n_bytes_written += self._write_geom_particle_flags(fp, write_settings) 

6249 LOGGER.debug(msg, n_bytes_written, "_write_geom_particle_flags") 

6250 

6251 # Geometry Data 

6252 n_bytes_written += self._write_geometry(fp, write_settings) 

6253 LOGGER.debug(msg, n_bytes_written, "_write_geometry") 

6254 

6255 # User Material, Node, Blabla IDs 

6256 n_bytes_written += self._write_geom_user_ids(fp, write_settings) 

6257 LOGGER.debug(msg, n_bytes_written, "_write_geom_user_ids") 

6258 

6259 # Rigid Body Description 

6260 n_bytes_written += self._write_geom_rigid_body_description(fp, write_settings) 

6261 LOGGER.debug(msg, n_bytes_written, "_write_geom_rigid_body_description") 

6262 

6263 # Adapted Element Parent List 

6264 # not supported 

6265 

6266 # Smooth Particle Hydrodynamcis Node and Material list 

6267 n_bytes_written += self._write_geom_sph_node_and_materials(fp, write_settings) 

6268 LOGGER.debug(msg, n_bytes_written, "_write_geom_sph_node_and_materials") 

6269 

6270 # Particle Geometry Data 

6271 n_bytes_written += self._write_geom_particle_geometry_data(fp, write_settings) 

6272 LOGGER.debug(msg, n_bytes_written, "_write_geom_particle_geometry_data") 

6273 

6274 # Rigid Road Surface Data 

6275 n_bytes_written += self._write_geom_rigid_road_surface(fp, write_settings) 

6276 LOGGER.debug(msg, n_bytes_written, "_write_geom_rigid_road_surface") 

6277 

6278 # Connectivity for weirdo elements 

6279 # 10 Node Tetra 

6280 # 8 Node Shell 

6281 # 20 Node Solid 

6282 # 27 Node Solid 

6283 n_bytes_written += self._write_geom_extra_node_data(fp, write_settings) 

6284 LOGGER.debug(msg, n_bytes_written, "_write_geom_extra_node_data") 

6285 

6286 # end mark 

6287 n_bytes_written += fp.write(write_settings.pack(-999999.0)) 

6288 LOGGER.debug(msg, n_bytes_written, "_end_mark") 

6289 

6290 # Header Part & Contact Interface Titles 

6291 n_bytes_written_before_titles = n_bytes_written 

6292 n_bytes_written += self._write_header_part_contact_interface_titles(fp, write_settings) 

6293 LOGGER.debug(msg, n_bytes_written, "_write_header_part_contact_interface_titles") 

6294 

6295 if n_bytes_written_before_titles != n_bytes_written: 

6296 

6297 # we seal the file here with an endmark 

6298 n_bytes_written += fp.write(write_settings.pack(-999999.0)) 

6299 LOGGER.debug(msg, n_bytes_written, "_end_mark") 

6300 else: 

6301 pass 

6302 # we already set an end-mark before 

6303 # that is perfectly fine 

6304 

6305 # correct zero padding at the end 

6306 if block_size_bytes > 0: 

6307 zero_bytes = self._get_zero_byte_padding(n_bytes_written, block_size_bytes) 

6308 n_bytes_written += fp.write(zero_bytes) 

6309 LOGGER.debug(msg, n_bytes_written, "_zero_byte_padding") 

6310 

6311 msg = "Wrote {0} bytes to geometry file." 

6312 LOGGER.debug(msg, n_bytes_written) 

6313 

6314 # Extra Data Types (for multi solver output) 

6315 # not supported 

6316 

6317 # write states 

6318 self._write_states(filepath, write_settings) 

6319 

6320 def _write_header(self, fp: typing.IO[Any], settings: D3plotWriterSettings) -> int: 

6321 

6322 wordsize = settings.wordsize 

6323 

6324 header_words = { 

6325 "title": (0 * wordsize, 10 * wordsize), 

6326 "runtime": (10 * wordsize, wordsize), 

6327 "filetype": (11 * wordsize, wordsize), 

6328 "source_version": (12 * wordsize, wordsize), 

6329 "release_version": (13 * wordsize, wordsize), 

6330 "version": (14 * wordsize, wordsize), 

6331 "ndim": (15 * wordsize, wordsize), 

6332 "numnp": (16 * wordsize, wordsize), 

6333 "icode": (17 * wordsize, wordsize), 

6334 "nglbv": (18 * wordsize, wordsize), 

6335 "it": (19 * wordsize, wordsize), 

6336 "iu": (20 * wordsize, wordsize), 

6337 "iv": (21 * wordsize, wordsize), 

6338 "ia": (22 * wordsize, wordsize), 

6339 "nel8": (23 * wordsize, wordsize), 

6340 "nummat8": (24 * wordsize, wordsize), 

6341 "numds": (25 * wordsize, wordsize), 

6342 "numst": (26 * wordsize, wordsize), 

6343 "nv3d": (27 * wordsize, wordsize), 

6344 "nel2": (28 * wordsize, wordsize), 

6345 "nummat2": (29 * wordsize, wordsize), 

6346 "nv1d": (30 * wordsize, wordsize), 

6347 "nel4": (31 * wordsize, wordsize), 

6348 "nummat4": (32 * wordsize, wordsize), 

6349 "nv2d": (33 * wordsize, wordsize), 

6350 "neiph": (34 * wordsize, wordsize), 

6351 "neips": (35 * wordsize, wordsize), 

6352 "maxint": (36 * wordsize, wordsize), 

6353 "nmsph": (37 * wordsize, wordsize), 

6354 "ngpsph": (38 * wordsize, wordsize), 

6355 "narbs": (39 * wordsize, wordsize), 

6356 "nelth": (40 * wordsize, wordsize), 

6357 "nummatt": (41 * wordsize, wordsize), 

6358 "nv3dt": (42 * wordsize, wordsize), 

6359 "ioshl1": (43 * wordsize, wordsize), 

6360 "ioshl2": (44 * wordsize, wordsize), 

6361 "ioshl3": (45 * wordsize, wordsize), 

6362 "ioshl4": (46 * wordsize, wordsize), 

6363 "ialemat": (47 * wordsize, wordsize), 

6364 "ncfdv1": (48 * wordsize, wordsize), 

6365 "ncfdv2": (49 * wordsize, wordsize), 

6366 # "nadapt": (50*wordsize, wordsize), 

6367 "nmmat": (51 * wordsize, wordsize), 

6368 "numfluid": (52 * wordsize, wordsize), 

6369 "inn": (53 * wordsize, wordsize), 

6370 "npefg": (54 * wordsize, wordsize), 

6371 "nel48": (55 * wordsize, wordsize), 

6372 "idtdt": (56 * wordsize, wordsize), 

6373 "extra": (57 * wordsize, wordsize), 

6374 } 

6375 

6376 header_extra_words = { 

6377 "nel20": (64 * wordsize, wordsize), 

6378 "nt3d": (65 * wordsize, wordsize), 

6379 "nel27": (66 * wordsize, wordsize), 

6380 "neipb": (67 * wordsize, wordsize), 

6381 } 

6382 

6383 new_header = settings.header 

6384 

6385 barray = bytearray((64 + new_header["extra"]) * wordsize) 

6386 

6387 for name, (position, size) in header_words.items(): 

6388 barray[position : position + size] = settings.pack(new_header[name], size) 

6389 

6390 if new_header["extra"] > 0: 

6391 for name, (position, size) in header_extra_words.items(): 

6392 barray[position : position + size] = settings.pack(new_header[name], size) 

6393 

6394 n_bytes_written = fp.write(barray) 

6395 

6396 # check 

6397 n_bytes_expected = (64 + new_header["extra"]) * settings.wordsize 

6398 D3plot._compare_n_bytes_checksum(n_bytes_written, n_bytes_expected) 

6399 

6400 return n_bytes_written

6538 def _write_geom_particle_flags(self, fp: typing.IO[Any], settings: D3plotWriterSettings) -> int: 

6539 

6540 npefg = settings.header["npefg"] 

6541 

6542 if npefg <= 0 or npefg > 10000000: 

6543 return 0 

6544 

6545 _check_ndim( 

6546 self, 

6547 { 

6548 ArrayType.airbags_n_particles: ["n_airbags"], 

6549 ArrayType.airbags_n_chambers: ["n_airbags"], 

6550 }, 

6551 ) 

6552 

6553 # n_airbags = npefg % 1000 

6554 subver = npefg // 1000 

6555 

6556 # airbag geometry var count 

6557 ngeom = 5 if ArrayType.airbags_n_chambers in self.arrays else 4 

6558 

6559 # state variable count 

6560 # see later 

6561 nvar = 14 

6562 

6563 # n particles 

6564 n_particles = 0 

6565 if ArrayType.airbags_n_particles in self.arrays: 

6566 n_particles = np.sum(self.arrays[ArrayType.airbags_n_particles]) 

6567 

6568 # airbag state var count 

6569 nstgeom = 2 

6570 

6571 # write 

6572 n_bytes_written = 0 

6573 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(ngeom)) 

6574 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(nvar)) 

6575 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(n_particles)) 

6576 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(nstgeom)) 

6577 if subver == 4: 

6578 # This was never validated 

6579 n_bytes_written += fp.write( 

6580 settings.pack(self.arrays[ArrayType.airbags_n_chambers].sum()) 

6581 ) 

6582 

6583 # check 

6584 n_bytes_expected = (5 if subver == 4 else 4) * settings.wordsize 

6585 D3plot._compare_n_bytes_checksum(n_bytes_written, n_bytes_expected) 

6586 

6587 # typecode for variables 

6588 # pylint: disable = invalid-name 

6589 INT_TC = 1 

6590 # pylint: disable = invalid-name 

6591 FLOAT_TC = 2 

6592 nlist_names_typecodes = [ 

6593 # airbag geometry data (ngeom) 

6594 ["Start N ", INT_TC], 

6595 ["Npart ", INT_TC], 

6596 ["Bag ID ", INT_TC], 

6597 ["NGasC ", INT_TC], 

6598 ["NCham ", INT_TC], 

6599 # state particle data (nvar) 

6600 ["GasC ID ", INT_TC], 

6601 ["Cham ID ", INT_TC], 

6602 ["Leakage ", INT_TC], 

6603 ["Pos x ", FLOAT_TC], 

6604 ["Pos y ", FLOAT_TC], 

6605 ["Pos z ", FLOAT_TC], 

6606 ["Vel x ", FLOAT_TC], 

6607 ["Vel y ", FLOAT_TC], 

6608 ["Vel z ", FLOAT_TC], 

6609 ["Mass ", FLOAT_TC], 

6610 ["Radius ", FLOAT_TC], 

6611 ["Spin En ", FLOAT_TC], 

6612 ["Tran En ", FLOAT_TC], 

6613 ["NS dist ", FLOAT_TC], 

6614 # airbag state vars (nstgeom) 

6615 ["Act Gas ", INT_TC], 

6616 ["Bag Vol ", FLOAT_TC], 

6617 ] 

6618 

6619 # airbag var typecodes 

6620 for _, typecode in nlist_names_typecodes: 

6621 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(typecode)) 

6622 

6623 # airbag var names 

6624 # every word is an ascii char. So, we need to set 

6625 # only the first byte to the ascii char code 

6626 fmt_string = "{0:" + str(settings.wordsize) + "}" 

6627 for name, _ in nlist_names_typecodes: 

6628 name_formatted = fmt_string.format(name).encode("ascii") 

6629 for ch in name_formatted: 

6630 barray = bytearray(settings.wordsize) 

6631 barray[0] = ch 

6632 

6633 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(barray, settings.wordsize)) 

6634 

6635 # check 

6636 n_bytes_expected += len(nlist_names_typecodes) * 9 * settings.wordsize 

6637 D3plot._compare_n_bytes_checksum(n_bytes_written, n_bytes_expected) 

6638 

6639 return n_bytes_written 

6640 

6641 def _write_geometry(self, fp: typing.IO[Any], settings: D3plotWriterSettings) -> int: 

6642 

6643 n_bytes_written = 0 

6644 

6645 # pre-checks 

6646 _check_ndim( 

6647 self, 

6648 { 

6649 ArrayType.node_coordinates: ["n_nodes", "x_y_z"], 

6650 ArrayType.element_solid_node_indexes: ["n_solids", "n_element_nodes"], 

6651 ArrayType.element_solid_part_indexes: ["n_solids"], 

6652 ArrayType.element_solid_extra_nodes: ["n_solids", "n_extra_nodes"], 

6653 ArrayType.element_tshell_node_indexes: ["n_tshells", "n_element_nodes"], 

6654 ArrayType.element_tshell_part_indexes: ["n_tshells"], 

6655 ArrayType.element_beam_node_indexes: ["n_beams", "n_element_nodes"], 

6656 ArrayType.element_beam_part_indexes: ["n_beams"], 

6657 ArrayType.element_shell_node_indexes: ["n_shells", "n_element_nodes"], 

6658 ArrayType.element_shell_part_indexes: ["n_shells"], 

6659 }, 

6660 ) 

6661 self.check_array_dims({ArrayType.node_coordinates: 1}, "x_y_z", 3) 

6662 

6663 array_dims = { 

6664 ArrayType.element_solid_node_indexes: 0, 

6665 ArrayType.element_solid_part_indexes: 0, 

6666 ArrayType.element_solid_extra_nodes: 0, 

6667 } 

6668 n_solids = self.check_array_dims(array_dims, "n_solids") 

6669 self.check_array_dims({ArrayType.element_solid_node_indexes: 1}, "n_element_nodes", 8) 

6670 self.check_array_dims({ArrayType.element_solid_extra_nodes: 1}, "n_extra_nodes", 2) 

6671 array_dims = { 

6672 ArrayType.element_tshell_node_indexes: 0, 

6673 ArrayType.element_tshell_part_indexes: 0, 

6674 } 

6675 self.check_array_dims(array_dims, "n_tshells") 

6676 self.check_array_dims({ArrayType.element_tshell_node_indexes: 1}, "n_element_nodes", 8) 

6677 array_dims = { 

6678 ArrayType.element_beam_node_indexes: 0, 

6679 ArrayType.element_beam_part_indexes: 0, 

6680 } 

6681 self.check_array_dims(array_dims, "n_beams") 

6682 self.check_array_dims({ArrayType.element_beam_node_indexes: 1}, "n_element_nodes", 5) 

6683 array_dims = { 

6684 ArrayType.element_shell_node_indexes: 0, 

6685 ArrayType.element_shell_part_indexes: 0, 

6686 } 

6687 self.check_array_dims(array_dims, "n_shells") 

6688 self.check_array_dims({ArrayType.element_shell_node_indexes: 1}, "n_element_nodes", 4) 

6689 

6690 # NODES 

6691 node_coordinates = ( 

6692 self.arrays[ArrayType.node_coordinates] 

6693 if ArrayType.node_coordinates in self.arrays 

6694 else np.zeros((0, settings.header["ndim"]), dtype=self.header.ftype) 

6695 ) 

6696 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(node_coordinates, dtype_hint=np.floating)) 

6697 

6698 # SOLIDS 

6699 solid_node_indexes = ( 

6700 self.arrays[ArrayType.element_solid_node_indexes] + FORTRAN_OFFSET 

6701 if ArrayType.element_solid_node_indexes in self.arrays 

6702 else np.zeros((0, 8), dtype=self._header.itype) 

6703 ) 

6704 solid_part_indexes = ( 

6705 self.arrays[ArrayType.element_solid_part_indexes] + FORTRAN_OFFSET 

6706 if ArrayType.element_solid_part_indexes in self.arrays 

6707 else np.zeros(0, dtype=self._header.itype) 

6708 ) 

6709 solid_geom_array = np.concatenate( 

6710 (solid_node_indexes, solid_part_indexes.reshape(n_solids, 1)), axis=1 

6711 ) 

6712 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(solid_geom_array, dtype_hint=np.integer)) 

6713 

6714 # SOLID 10 

6715 # the two extra nodes 

6716 if ArrayType.element_solid_extra_nodes in self.arrays: 

6717 array = self.arrays[ArrayType.element_solid_extra_nodes] + FORTRAN_OFFSET 

6718 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(array, dtype_hint=np.integer)) 

6719 

6720 # THICK SHELLS 

6721 tshell_node_indexes = ( 

6722 self.arrays[ArrayType.element_tshell_node_indexes] + FORTRAN_OFFSET 

6723 if ArrayType.element_tshell_node_indexes in self.arrays 

6724 else np.zeros((0, 8), dtype=self._header.itype) 

6725 ) 

6726 tshell_part_indexes = ( 

6727 self.arrays[ArrayType.element_tshell_part_indexes] + FORTRAN_OFFSET 

6728 if ArrayType.element_tshell_part_indexes in self.arrays 

6729 else np.zeros(0, dtype=self._header.itype) 

6730 ) 

6731 tshell_geom_array = np.concatenate( 

6732 (tshell_node_indexes, tshell_part_indexes.reshape(-1, 1)), axis=1 

6733 ) 

6734 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(tshell_geom_array, dtype_hint=np.integer)) 

6735 

6736 # BEAMS 

6737 beam_node_indexes = ( 

6738 self.arrays[ArrayType.element_beam_node_indexes] + FORTRAN_OFFSET 

6739 if ArrayType.element_beam_node_indexes in self.arrays 

6740 else np.zeros((0, 5), dtype=self._header.itype) 

6741 ) 

6742 beam_part_indexes = ( 

6743 self.arrays[ArrayType.element_beam_part_indexes] + FORTRAN_OFFSET 

6744 if ArrayType.element_beam_part_indexes in self.arrays 

6745 else np.zeros(0, dtype=self._header.itype) 

6746 ) 

6747 beam_geom_array = np.concatenate( 

6748 (beam_node_indexes, beam_part_indexes.reshape(-1, 1)), axis=1 

6749 ) 

6750 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(beam_geom_array, dtype_hint=np.integer)) 

6751 

6752 # SHELLS 

6753 shell_node_indexes = ( 

6754 self.arrays[ArrayType.element_shell_node_indexes] + FORTRAN_OFFSET 

6755 if ArrayType.element_shell_node_indexes in self.arrays 

6756 else np.zeros((0, 4), dtype=self._header.itype) 

6757 ) 

6758 shell_part_indexes = ( 

6759 self.arrays[ArrayType.element_shell_part_indexes] + FORTRAN_OFFSET 

6760 if ArrayType.element_shell_part_indexes in self.arrays 

6761 else np.zeros(0, dtype=self._header.itype) 

6762 ) 

6763 shell_geom_array = np.concatenate( 

6764 (shell_node_indexes, shell_part_indexes.reshape(-1, 1)), axis=1 

6765 ) 

6766 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(shell_geom_array, dtype_hint=np.integer)) 

6767 

6768 # check 

6769 n_bytes_expected = ( 

6770 settings.header["numnp"] * 3 

6771 + abs(settings.header["nel8"]) * 9 

6772 + settings.header["nelth"] * 9 

6773 + settings.header["nel2"] * 6 

6774 + settings.header["nel4"] * 5 

6775 ) * settings.wordsize 

6776 if ArrayType.element_solid_extra_nodes in self.arrays: 

6777 n_bytes_expected += 2 * abs(settings.header["nel8"]) 

6778 D3plot._compare_n_bytes_checksum(n_bytes_written, n_bytes_expected) 

6779 

6780 # return the chunks 

6781 return n_bytes_written

6783 def _write_geom_user_ids(self, fp: typing.IO[Any], settings: D3plotWriterSettings) -> int: 

6784 

6785 narbs = settings.header["narbs"] 

6786 if narbs == 0: 

6787 return 0 

6788 

6789 info = self._numbering_info 

6790 

6791 _check_ndim( 

6792 self, 

6793 { 

6794 ArrayType.node_ids: ["n_nodes"], 

6795 ArrayType.element_solid_ids: ["n_solids"], 

6796 ArrayType.element_beam_ids: ["n_beams"], 

6797 ArrayType.element_shell_ids: ["n_shells"], 

6798 ArrayType.element_tshell_ids: ["n_tshells"], 

6799 ArrayType.part_ids: ["n_parts"], 

6800 ArrayType.part_ids_unordered: ["n_parts"], 

6801 ArrayType.part_ids_cross_references: ["n_parts"], 

6802 }, 

6803 ) 

6804 

6805 n_bytes_written = 0 

6806 

6807 # NUMBERING HEADER 

6808 

6809 # nsort seems to be solver internal pointer 

6810 # ... hopefully 

6811 nsort = info.ptr_node_ids 

6812 nsort *= -1 if ArrayType.part_ids in self.arrays else 1 

6813 

6814 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(nsort)) 

6815 

6816 nsrh = abs(nsort) + settings.header["numnp"] 

6817 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(nsrh)) 

6818 

6819 nsrb = nsrh + abs(settings.header["nel8"]) 

6820 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(nsrb)) 

6821 

6822 nsrs = nsrb + settings.header["nel2"] 

6823 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(nsrs)) 

6824 

6825 nsrt = nsrs + settings.header["nel4"] 

6826 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(nsrt)) 

6827 

6828 nsortd = settings.header["numnp"] 

6829 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(nsortd)) 

6830 

6831 nsrhd = abs(settings.header["nel8"]) 

6832 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(nsrhd)) 

6833 

6834 nsrbd = settings.header["nel2"] 

6835 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(nsrbd)) 

6836 

6837 nsrsd = settings.header["nel4"] 

6838 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(nsrsd)) 

6839 

6840 nsrtd = settings.header["nelth"] 

6841 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(nsrtd)) 

6842 

6843 if ArrayType.part_ids in self.arrays: 

6844 # some lsdyna material pointer 

6845 nsrma = info.ptr_material_ids 

6846 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(nsrma)) 

6847 

6848 # some lsdyna material pointer 

6849 nsrmu = info.ptr_material_ids_defined_order 

6850 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(nsrmu)) 

6851 

6852 # some lsdyna material pointer 

6853 nsrmp = info.ptr_material_ids_crossref 

6854 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(nsrmp)) 

6855 

6856 # "Total number of materials (parts)" 

6857 nsrtm = settings.header["nmmat"] 

6858 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(nsrtm)) 

6859 

6860 # Total number of nodal rigid body constraint sets 

6861 numrbs = settings.header["numrbs"] 

6862 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(numrbs)) 

6863 

6864 # Total number of materials 

6865 # ... coz it's fun doing nice things twice 

6866 nmmat = settings.header["nmmat"] 

6867 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(nmmat)) 

6868 

6869 # NODE IDS 

6870 node_ids = ( 

6871 self.arrays[ArrayType.node_ids] 

6872 if ArrayType.node_ids in self.arrays 

6873 else np.arange( 

6874 FORTRAN_OFFSET, settings.header["numnp"] + FORTRAN_OFFSET, dtype=settings.itype 

6875 ) 

6876 ) 

6877 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(node_ids, dtype_hint=np.integer)) 

6878 

6879 # SOLID IDS 

6880 solid_ids = ( 

6881 self.arrays[ArrayType.element_solid_ids] 

6882 if ArrayType.element_solid_ids in self.arrays 

6883 else np.arange( 

6884 FORTRAN_OFFSET, settings.header["nel8"] + FORTRAN_OFFSET, dtype=settings.itype 

6885 ) 

6886 ) 

6887 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(solid_ids, dtype_hint=np.integer)) 

6888 

6889 # BEAM IDS 

6890 beam_ids = ( 

6891 self.arrays[ArrayType.element_beam_ids] 

6892 if ArrayType.element_beam_ids in self.arrays 

6893 else np.arange( 

6894 FORTRAN_OFFSET, settings.header["nel2"] + FORTRAN_OFFSET, dtype=settings.itype 

6895 ) 

6896 ) 

6897 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(beam_ids, dtype_hint=np.integer)) 

6898 

6899 # SHELL IDS 

6900 shell_ids = ( 

6901 self.arrays[ArrayType.element_shell_ids] 

6902 if ArrayType.element_shell_ids in self.arrays 

6903 else np.arange( 

6904 FORTRAN_OFFSET, settings.header["nel4"] + FORTRAN_OFFSET, dtype=settings.itype 

6905 ) 

6906 ) 

6907 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(shell_ids, dtype_hint=np.integer)) 

6908 

6909 # TSHELL IDS 

6910 tshell_ids = ( 

6911 self.arrays[ArrayType.element_tshell_ids] 

6912 if ArrayType.element_tshell_ids in self.arrays 

6913 else np.arange( 

6914 FORTRAN_OFFSET, settings.header["nelth"] + FORTRAN_OFFSET, dtype=settings.itype 

6915 ) 

6916 ) 

6917 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(tshell_ids, dtype_hint=np.integer)) 

6918 

6919 # MATERIALS .... yay 

6920 # 

6921 # lsdyna generates duplicate materials originally 

6922 # thus nmmat in header is larger than the materials used 

6923 # by the elements. Some are related to rigid bodies 

6924 # but some are also generated internally by material models 

6925 # by the following procedure the material array is larger 

6926 # than the actual amount of materials (there may be unused 

6927 # material ids), but it ensures a relatively consistent writing 

6928 

6929 material_ids = np.full(settings.header["nmmat"], -1, dtype=self._header.itype) 

6930 if ArrayType.part_ids in self.arrays: 

6931 part_ids = self.arrays[ArrayType.part_ids] 

6932 material_ids = part_ids 

6933 else: 

6934 material_ids = np.arange(start=0, stop=settings.header["nmmat"], dtype=settings.itype) 

6935 

6936 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(material_ids, dtype_hint=np.integer)) 

6937 

6938 # unordered material ids can be ignored 

6939 data_array = np.zeros(settings.header["nmmat"], dtype=settings.itype) 

6940 if ArrayType.part_ids_unordered in self.arrays: 

6941 array = self.arrays[ArrayType.part_ids_unordered] 

6942 end_index = min(len(array), len(data_array)) 

6943 data_array[:end_index] = array[:end_index] 

6944 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(data_array, dtype_hint=np.integer)) 

6945 

6946 # also cross-reference array for ids 

6947 data_array = np.zeros(settings.header["nmmat"], dtype=settings.itype) 

6948 if ArrayType.part_ids_cross_references in self.arrays: 

6949 array = self.arrays[ArrayType.part_ids_cross_references] 

6950 end_index = min(len(array), len(data_array)) 

6951 data_array[:end_index] = array[:end_index] 

6952 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(data_array, dtype_hint=np.integer)) 

6953 

6954 # check 

6955 n_bytes_expected = settings.header["narbs"] * settings.wordsize 

6956 D3plot._compare_n_bytes_checksum(n_bytes_written, n_bytes_expected) 

6957 

6958 return n_bytes_written 

6959 

6960 def _write_geom_rigid_body_description( 

6961 self, fp: typing.IO[Any], settings: D3plotWriterSettings 

6962 ) -> int: 

6963 

6964 # this type of rigid body descriptions are very rare 

6965 # and thus badly tested 

6966 

6967 if settings.header["ndim"] not in (8, 9): 

6968 return 0 

6969 

6970 _check_ndim( 

6971 self, 

6972 { 

6973 ArrayType.rigid_body_part_indexes: ["n_rigid_bodies"], 

6974 }, 

6975 ) 

6976 array_dims = { 

6977 ArrayType.rigid_body_part_indexes: 0, 

6978 ArrayType.rigid_body_node_indexes_list: 0, 

6979 ArrayType.rigid_body_active_node_indexes_list: 0, 

6980 } 

6981 if not _check_array_occurrence(self, list(array_dims.keys()), list(array_dims.keys())): 

6982 return 0 

6983 

6984 # check length 

6985 # cannot use self._check_array_dims due to some lists 

6986 dim_size = -1 

6987 for typename in array_dims: 

6988 array = self.arrays[typename] 

6989 if dim_size < 0: 

6990 dim_size = len(array) 

6991 else: 

6992 if len(array) != dim_size: 

6993 dimension_size_dict = { 

6994 typename2: len(self.arrays[typename2]) for typename2 in array_dims 

6995 } 

6996 msg = "Inconsistency in array dim '{0}' detected:\n{1}" 

6997 size_list = [ 

6998 f" - name: {typename}, dim: {array_dims[typename]}, size: {size}" 

6999 for typename, size in dimension_size_dict.items() 

7000 ] 

7001 raise ValueError(msg.format("n_rigid_bodies", "\n".join(size_list))) 

7002 

7003 rigid_body_part_indexes = self.arrays[ArrayType.rigid_body_part_indexes] + FORTRAN_OFFSET 

7004 # rigid_body_n_nodes = self.arrays[ArrayType.rigid_body_n_nodes] 

7005 rigid_body_node_indexes_list = self.arrays[ArrayType.rigid_body_node_indexes_list] 

7006 # rigid_body_n_active_nodes = self.arrays[ArrayType.rigid_body_n_active_nodes] 

7007 rigid_body_active_node_indexes_list = self.arrays[ 

7008 ArrayType.rigid_body_active_node_indexes_list 

7009 ] 

7010 

7011 n_bytes_written = 0 

7012 n_bytes_expected = settings.wordsize 

7013 

7014 # NRIGID 

7015 n_rigid_bodies = len(rigid_body_part_indexes) 

7016 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(n_rigid_bodies)) 

7017 

7018 for i_rigid in range(n_rigid_bodies): 

7019 # part index 

7020 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(rigid_body_part_indexes[i_rigid])) 

7021 # node indexes 

7022 array = rigid_body_node_indexes_list[i_rigid] + FORTRAN_OFFSET 

7023 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(len(array))) 

7024 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(array, dtype_hint=np.integer)) 

7025 # active node indexes 

7026 array = rigid_body_active_node_indexes_list[i_rigid] 

7027 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(len(array))) 

7028 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(array, dtype_hint=np.integer)) 

7029 

7030 n_bytes_expected += settings.wordsize * ( 

7031 3 

7032 + len(rigid_body_node_indexes_list[i_rigid]) 

7033 + len(rigid_body_active_node_indexes_list[i_rigid]) 

7034 ) 

7035 

7036 # check 

7037 D3plot._compare_n_bytes_checksum(n_bytes_written, n_bytes_expected) 

7038 

7039 return n_bytes_written

7129 def _write_geom_rigid_road_surface( 

7130 self, fp: typing.IO[Any], settings: D3plotWriterSettings 

7131 ) -> int: 

7132 

7133 if settings.header["ndim"] <= 5: 

7134 return 0 

7135 

7136 _check_ndim( 

7137 self, 

7138 { 

7139 ArrayType.rigid_road_node_ids: ["rigid_road_n_nodes"], 

7140 ArrayType.rigid_road_node_coordinates: ["rigid_road_n_nodes", "x_y_z"], 

7141 ArrayType.rigid_road_segment_node_ids: ["n_segments", "n_nodes"], 

7142 ArrayType.rigid_road_segment_road_id: ["n_segments"], 

7143 }, 

7144 ) 

7145 array_dims = { 

7146 ArrayType.rigid_road_node_ids: 0, 

7147 ArrayType.rigid_road_node_coordinates: 0, 

7148 } 

7149 n_rigid_road_nodes = self.check_array_dims(array_dims, "rigid_road_n_nodes") 

7150 self.check_array_dims({ArrayType.rigid_road_node_coordinates: 1}, "x_y_z", 3) 

7151 array_dims = { 

7152 ArrayType.rigid_road_n_segments: 0, 

7153 ArrayType.rigid_road_segment_node_ids: 0, 

7154 ArrayType.rigid_road_segment_road_id: 0, 

7155 } 

7156 n_rigid_roads = self.check_array_dims(array_dims, "n_rigid_roads") 

7157 n_bytes_written = 0 

7158 

7159 # NODE COUNT 

7160 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(n_rigid_road_nodes)) 

7161 

7162 # SEGMENT COUNT 

7163 # This was never verified 

7164 n_total_segments = np.sum( 

7165 len(segment_ids) for segment_ids in self.arrays[ArrayType.rigid_road_segment_node_ids] 

7166 ) 

7167 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(n_total_segments)) 

7168 

7169 # SURFACE COUNT 

7170 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(n_rigid_roads)) 

7171 

7172 # MOTION FLAG - if motion data is output 

7173 # by default let's just say ... yeah baby 

7174 # This was never verified 

7175 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(1)) 

7176 

7177 # RIGID ROAD NODE IDS 

7178 rigid_road_node_ids = self.arrays[ArrayType.rigid_road_node_ids] 

7179 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(rigid_road_node_ids, dtype_hint=np.integer)) 

7180 

7181 # RIGID ROAD NODE COORDS 

7182 rigid_road_node_coordinates = self.arrays[ArrayType.rigid_road_node_coordinates] 

7183 n_bytes_written += fp.write( 

7184 settings.pack(rigid_road_node_coordinates, dtype_hint=np.floating) 

7185 ) 

7186 

7187 # SURFACE ID 

7188 # SURFACE N_SEGMENTS 

7189 # SURFACE SEGMENTS 

7190 rigid_road_segment_road_id = self.arrays[ArrayType.rigid_road_segment_road_id] 

7191 rigid_road_segment_node_ids = self.arrays[ArrayType.rigid_road_segment_node_ids] 

7192 

7193 for segment_id, node_ids in zip(rigid_road_segment_road_id, rigid_road_segment_node_ids): 

7194 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(segment_id)) 

7195 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(len(node_ids))) 

7196 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(node_ids, dtype_hint=np.integer)) 

7197 

7198 # check 

7199 n_bytes_expected = ( 

7200 4 + 4 * n_rigid_road_nodes + n_rigid_roads * (2 + 4 * n_total_segments) 

7201 ) * settings.wordsize 

7202 D3plot._compare_n_bytes_checksum(n_bytes_written, n_bytes_expected) 

7203 

7204 return n_bytes_written

7206 def _write_geom_extra_node_data( 

7207 self, fp: typing.IO[Any], settings: D3plotWriterSettings 

7208 ) -> int: 

7209 

7210 n_bytes_written = 0 

7211 

7212 # 10 NODE SOLIDS 

7213 if settings.header["nel8"] < 0: 

7214 _check_ndim( 

7215 self, 

7216 { 

7217 ArrayType.element_solid_node10_extra_node_indexes: [ 

7218 "n_solids", 

7219 "2_extra_node_ids", 

7220 ], 

7221 }, 

7222 )

7224 ArrayType.element_solid_node_indexes: 0, 

7225 ArrayType.element_solid_node10_extra_node_indexes: 0, 

7226 }

7229 {ArrayType.element_solid_node10_extra_node_indexes: 1}, "extra_node_ids", 2 

7230 )

7234 ) 

7235

7237 

7238 # 8 NODE SHELLS 

7239 if settings.header["nel48"] > 0: 

7240 _check_ndim( 

7241 self, 

7242 { 

7243 ArrayType.element_shell_node8_element_index: ["n_node8_shells"], 

7244 ArrayType.element_shell_node8_extra_node_indexes: [ 

7245 "n_node8_shells", 

7246 "4_extra_node_ids", 

7247 ], 

7248 }, 

7249 )

7251 ArrayType.element_shell_node8_element_index: 0, 

7252 ArrayType.element_shell_node8_extra_node_indexes: 0, 

7253 } 

7254 self.check_array_dims(array_dims, "n_node8_shells") 

7255 self.check_array_dims( 

7256 {ArrayType.element_shell_node8_extra_node_indexes: 1}, "extra_node_ids", 4 

7257 ) 

7258 

7259 element_indexes = ( 

7260 self.arrays[ArrayType.element_shell_node8_element_index] + FORTRAN_OFFSET 

7261 )
