7263 self.arrays[ArrayType.element_shell_node8_extra_node_indexes] + FORTRAN_OFFSET 

7264 ) 

7265 

7266 geom_data = np.concatenate((element_indexes, extra_nodes), axis=1) 

7267 

7268 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(geom_data, dtype_hint=np.integer)) 

7269 

7270 # 20 NODE SOLIDS 

7271 if settings.header["extra"] > 0 and settings.header["nel20"] > 0: 

7272 _check_ndim( 

7273 self, 

7274 { 

7275 ArrayType.element_solid_node20_element_index: ["n_node20_solids"], 

7276 ArrayType.element_solid_node20_extra_node_indexes: [ 

7277 "n_node20_solids", 

7278 "12_extra_node_ids", 

7279 ], 

7280 }, 

7281 ) 

7282 array_dims = { 

7283 ArrayType.element_solid_node20_element_index: 0, 

7284 ArrayType.element_solid_node20_extra_node_indexes: 0, 

7285 } 

7286 self.check_array_dims(array_dims, "n_node20_solids") 

7287 self.check_array_dims( 

7288 {ArrayType.element_solid_node20_extra_node_indexes: 1}, "extra_node_ids", 12 

7289 ) 

7290 

7291 element_indexes = ( 

7292 self.arrays[ArrayType.element_solid_node20_element_index] + FORTRAN_OFFSET 

7293 ) 

7294 extra_nodes = ( 

7295 self.arrays[ArrayType.element_solid_node20_extra_node_indexes] + FORTRAN_OFFSET 

7296 ) 

7297 

7298 geom_data = np.concatenate((element_indexes, extra_nodes), axis=1) 

7299 

7300 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(geom_data, dtype_hint=np.integer)) 

7301 

7302 # 27 NODE SOLIDS 

7303 if settings.header["extra"] > 0 and settings.header["nel27"] > 0: 

7304 _check_ndim( 

7305 self, 

7306 { 

7307 ArrayType.element_solid_node20_element_index: ["n_node27_solids"], 

7308 ArrayType.element_solid_node20_extra_node_indexes: [ 

7309 "n_node27_solids", 

7310 "19_extra_node_ids", 

7311 ], 

7312 }, 

7313 ) 

7314 array_dims = { 

7315 ArrayType.element_solid_node27_element_index: 0, 

7316 ArrayType.element_solid_node27_extra_node_indexes: 0, 

7317 } 

7318 self.check_array_dims(array_dims, "n_node27_solids") 

7319 self.check_array_dims( 

7320 {ArrayType.element_solid_node27_extra_node_indexes: 1}, "extra_node_ids", 19 

7321 ) 

7322 

7323 element_indexes = ( 

7324 self.arrays[ArrayType.element_solid_node27_element_index] + FORTRAN_OFFSET 

7325 ) 

7326 extra_nodes = ( 

7327 self.arrays[ArrayType.element_solid_node27_extra_node_indexes] + FORTRAN_OFFSET 

7328 ) 

7329 

7330 geom_data = np.concatenate((element_indexes, extra_nodes), axis=1) 

7331 

7332 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(geom_data, dtype_hint=np.integer)) 

7333 

7334 # check 

7335 has_nel10 = settings.header["nel8"] < 0 

7336 n_bytes_expected = ( 

7337 has_nel10 * abs(settings.header["nel8"]) 

7338 + settings.header["nel48"] * 5 

7339 + settings.header["nel20"] * 13 

7340 + settings.header["nel27"] * 20 

7341 ) * settings.wordsize 

7342 D3plot._compare_n_bytes_checksum(n_bytes_written, n_bytes_expected) 

7343 

7344 return n_bytes_written 

7345 

7346 def _write_header_part_contact_interface_titles( 

7347 self, fp: typing.IO[Any], settings: D3plotWriterSettings 

7348 ) -> int: 

7349 

7350 n_bytes_written = 0 

7351 

7352 # PART TITLES 

7353 _check_ndim( 

7354 self, 

7355 { 

7356 # ArrayType.part_titles: ["n_parts", "n_chars"], 

7357 ArrayType.part_titles_ids: ["n_parts"], 

7358 }, 

7359 ) 

7360 array_dimensions = { 

7361 ArrayType.part_titles: 0, 

7362 ArrayType.part_titles_ids: 0, 

7363 } 

7364 if _check_array_occurrence( 

7365 self, list(array_dimensions.keys()), list(array_dimensions.keys()) 

7366 ): 

7367 self.check_array_dims(array_dimensions, "n_parts") 

7368 

7369 ntype = 90001 

7370 

7371 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(ntype)) 

7372 

7373 part_titles_ids = self.arrays[ArrayType.part_titles_ids] 

7374 part_titles = self.arrays[ArrayType.part_titles] 

7375 

7376 n_entries = len(part_titles) 

7377 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(n_entries)) 

7378 

7379 # title words always have 4 byte size 

7380 title_wordsize = 4 

7381 max_len = 18 * title_wordsize 

7382 fmt_name = "{0:" + str(max_len) + "}" 

7383 for pid, title in zip(part_titles_ids, part_titles): 

7384 title = title.decode("ascii") 

7385 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(pid)) 

7386 

7387 formatted_title = fmt_name.format(title[:max_len]) 

7388 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(formatted_title, max_len)) 

7389 

7390 # TITLE2 

7391 # yet another title, coz double is always more fun 

7392 if "title2" in self.header.title2: 

7393 ntype = 90000 

7394 

7395 # title words always have 4 bytes 

7396 title_wordsize = 4 

7397 title_size_words = 18 

7398 

7399 fmt_title2 = "{0:" + str(title_wordsize * title_size_words) + "}" 

7400 title2 = fmt_title2.format(self.header.title2[: settings.wordsize * title_size_words]) 

7401 

7402 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(ntype)) 

7403 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(title2, settings.wordsize * title_size_words)) 

7404 

7405 # CONTACT TITLES 

7406 array_dimensions = { 

7407 ArrayType.contact_titles: 0, 

7408 ArrayType.contact_title_ids: 0, 

7409 } 

7410 if _check_array_occurrence( 

7411 self, list(array_dimensions.keys()), list(array_dimensions.keys()) 

7412 ): 

7413 self.check_array_dims(array_dimensions, "n_parts") 

7414 

7415 ntype = 90002 

7416 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(ntype)) 

7417 

7418 titles_ids = self.arrays[ArrayType.contact_title_ids] 

7419 titles = self.arrays[ArrayType.contact_titles] 

7420 

7421 n_entries = len(titles) 

7422 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(n_entries)) 

7423 

7424 max_len = 18 * self.header.wordsize 

7425 fmt_name = "{0:" + str(max_len) + "}" 

7426 for pid, title in zip(titles_ids, titles): 

7427 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(pid)) 

7428 

7429 formatted_title = fmt_name.format(title[:max_len]) 

7430 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(formatted_title)) 

7431 

7432 return n_bytes_written 

7433 

7434 def _write_states( 

7435 self, filepath: Union[str, typing.BinaryIO], settings: D3plotWriterSettings 

7436 ) -> int: 

7437 

7438 # did we store any states? 

7439 n_timesteps_written = 0 

7440 

7441 # if timestep array is missing check for any state arrays 

7442 if ArrayType.global_timesteps not in self.arrays: 

7443 # if any state array is present simply make up a timestep array 

7444 if any(array_name in self.arrays for array_name in ArrayType.get_state_array_names()): 

7445 array_dims = {array_name: 0 for array_name in ArrayType.get_state_array_names()} 

7446 n_timesteps = self.check_array_dims( 

7447 array_dimensions=array_dims, dimension_name="n_timesteps" 

7448 ) 

7449 self._state_info.n_timesteps = n_timesteps 

7450 self.arrays[ArrayType.global_timesteps] = np.arange( 

7451 0, n_timesteps, dtype=settings.ftype 

7452 ) 

7453 # no state data so we call it a day 

7454 else: 

7455 return n_timesteps_written 

7456 

7457 # formatter for state files 

7458 timesteps = self.arrays[ArrayType.global_timesteps] 

7459 n_timesteps = len(timesteps) 

7460 fmt_state_file_counter = "{0:02d}" 

7461 

7462 # single file or multiple file handling 

7463 state_fp: Union[None, typing.BinaryIO] = None 

7464 file_to_close: Union[None, typing.BinaryIO] = None 

7465 if isinstance(filepath, str): 

7466 if settings.single_file: 

7467 # pylint: disable = consider-using-with 

7468 state_fp = file_to_close = open(filepath + fmt_state_file_counter.format(1), "ab") 

7469 else: 

7470 # create a new file per timestep 

7471 # see time loop 

7472 pass 

7473 else: 

7474 state_fp = filepath 

7475 

7476 try: 

7477 # time looping ... wheeeeeeeee 

7478 for i_timestep, _ in enumerate(timesteps): 

7479 

7480 # open new state file ... or not 

7481 state_filepath_or_file = ( 

7482 filepath + fmt_state_file_counter.format(i_timestep + 1) 

7483 if isinstance(filepath, str) and state_fp is None 

7484 else state_fp 

7485 ) 

7486 

7487 n_bytes_written = 0 

7488 

7489 with open_file_or_filepath(state_filepath_or_file, "ab") as fp: 

7490 

7491 # GLOBALS 

7492 n_bytes_written += self._write_states_globals(fp, i_timestep, settings) 

7493 

7494 # NODE DATA 

7495 n_bytes_written += self._write_states_nodes(fp, i_timestep, settings) 

7496 

7497 # SOLID THERMAL DATA 

7498 n_bytes_written += self._write_states_solid_thermal_data( 

7499 fp, i_timestep, settings 

7500 ) 

7501 

7502 # CFDDATA 

7503 # not supported 

7504 

7505 # SOLIDS 

7506 n_bytes_written += self._write_states_solids(fp, i_timestep, settings) 

7507 

7508 # THICK SHELLS 

7509 n_bytes_written += self._write_states_tshells(fp, i_timestep, settings) 

7510 

7511 # spocky ... BEAM me up 

7512 n_bytes_written += self._write_states_beams(fp, i_timestep, settings) 

7513 

7514 # SHELLS 

7515 n_bytes_written += self._write_states_shells(fp, i_timestep, settings) 

7516 

7517 # DELETION INFO 

7518 n_bytes_written += self._write_states_deletion_info(fp, i_timestep, settings) 

7519 

7520 # SPH 

7521 n_bytes_written += self._write_states_sph(fp, i_timestep, settings) 

7522 

7523 # AIRBAG 

7524 n_bytes_written += self._write_states_airbags(fp, i_timestep, settings) 

7525 

7526 # RIGID ROAD 

7527 n_bytes_written += self._write_states_rigid_road(fp, i_timestep, settings) 

7528 

7529 # RIGID BODY 

7530 n_bytes_written += self._write_states_rigid_bodies(fp, i_timestep, settings) 

7531 

7532 # EXTRA DATA 

7533 # not supported 

7534 

7535 # end mark 

7536 # at the end for single file buffer 

7537 # or behind each state file 

7538 if not settings.single_file or i_timestep == n_timesteps - 1: 

7539 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(-999999.0)) 

7540 

7541 if settings.block_size_bytes > 0: 

7542 zero_bytes = self._get_zero_byte_padding( 

7543 n_bytes_written, settings.block_size_bytes 

7544 ) 

7545 n_bytes_written += fp.write(zero_bytes) 

7546 

7547 # log 

7548 msg = "_write_states wrote %d bytes" 

7549 LOGGER.debug(msg, n_bytes_written) 

7550 n_timesteps_written += 1 

7551 

7552 finally: 

7553 # close file if required 

7554 if file_to_close is not None: 

7555 file_to_close.close() 

7556 

7557 return n_timesteps_written 

7558 

7559 def _write_states_globals( 

7560 self, fp: typing.IO[Any], i_timestep: int, settings: D3plotWriterSettings 

7561 ) -> int: 

7562 

7563 _check_ndim( 

7564 self, 

7565 { 

7566 ArrayType.global_kinetic_energy: ["n_timesteps"], 

7567 ArrayType.global_internal_energy: ["n_timesteps"], 

7568 ArrayType.global_total_energy: ["n_timesteps"], 

7569 ArrayType.global_velocity: ["n_timesteps", "vx_vy_vz"], 

7570 }, 

7571 ) 

7572 array_dims = { 

7573 ArrayType.global_timesteps: 0, 

7574 ArrayType.global_kinetic_energy: 0, 

7575 ArrayType.global_internal_energy: 0, 

7576 ArrayType.global_total_energy: 0, 

7577 ArrayType.global_velocity: 0, 

7578 } 

7579 self.check_array_dims(array_dims, "n_timesteps") 

7580 

7581 byte_checksum = 0 

7582 

7583 n_global_vars = settings.header["nglbv"] 

7584 

7585 # TIME 

7586 timesteps = self.arrays[ArrayType.global_timesteps] 

7587 byte_checksum += fp.write(settings.pack(timesteps[i_timestep])) 

7588 

7589 # GLOBAL KINETIC ENERGY 

7590 if n_global_vars >= 1: 

7591 array_type = ArrayType.global_kinetic_energy 

7592 value = ( 

7593 self.arrays[array_type][i_timestep] 

7594 if array_type in self.arrays 

7595 else self.header.ftype(0.0) 

7596 ) 

7597 byte_checksum += fp.write(settings.pack(value, dtype_hint=np.floating)) 

7598 

7599 # GLOBAL INTERNAL ENERGY 

7600 if n_global_vars >= 2: 

7601 array_type = ArrayType.global_internal_energy 

7602 value = ( 

7603 self.arrays[array_type][i_timestep] 

7604 if array_type in self.arrays 

7605 else self.header.ftype(0.0) 

7606 ) 

7607 byte_checksum += fp.write(settings.pack(value, dtype_hint=np.floating)) 

7608 

7609 # GLOBAL TOTAL ENERGY 

7610 if n_global_vars >= 3: 

7611 array_type = ArrayType.global_total_energy 

7612 value = ( 

7613 self.arrays[array_type][i_timestep] 

7614 if array_type in self.arrays 

7615 else self.header.ftype(0.0) 

7616 ) 

7617 byte_checksum += fp.write(settings.pack(value, dtype_hint=np.floating)) 

7618 

7619 # GLOBAL VELOCITY 

7620 if n_global_vars >= 6: 

7621 self.check_array_dims({ArrayType.global_velocity: 1}, "vx_vy_vz", 3) 

7622 array_type = ArrayType.global_velocity 

7623 array = ( 

7624 self.arrays[array_type][i_timestep] 

7625 if array_type in self.arrays 

7626 else np.zeros(3, self.header.ftype) 

7627 ) 

7628 byte_checksum += fp.write(settings.pack(array, dtype_hint=np.floating)) 

7629 

7630 # PARTS 

7631 # 

7632 # Parts always need special love since dyna 

7633 # writes many dummy parts 

7634 _check_ndim( 

7635 self, 

7636 { 

7637 ArrayType.part_internal_energy: ["n_timesteps", "n_parts"], 

7638 ArrayType.part_kinetic_energy: ["n_timesteps", "n_parts"], 

7639 ArrayType.part_velocity: ["n_timesteps", "n_parts", "vx_vy_vz"], 

7640 ArrayType.part_mass: ["n_timesteps", "n_parts"], 

7641 ArrayType.part_hourglass_energy: ["n_timesteps", "n_parts"], 

7642 }, 

7643 ) 

7644 array_dims = { 

7645 ArrayType.global_timesteps: 0, 

7646 ArrayType.part_internal_energy: 0, 

7647 ArrayType.part_kinetic_energy: 0, 

7648 ArrayType.part_velocity: 0, 

7649 ArrayType.part_mass: 0, 

7650 ArrayType.part_hourglass_energy: 0, 

7651 } 

7652 self.check_array_dims(array_dims, "n_timesteps") 

7653 

7654 self.check_array_dims({ArrayType.part_velocity: 2}, "vx_vy_vz", 3) 

7655 

7656 n_parts = settings.header["nmmat"] 

7657 

7658 def _write_part_field(array_type: str, default_shape: Union[int, Tuple], dtype: np.dtype): 

7659 array = ( 

7660 self.arrays[array_type][i_timestep] 

7661 if array_type in self.arrays 

7662 else np.zeros(default_shape, self.header.ftype) 

7663 ) 

7664 

7665 if len(array): 

7666 dummy_array = array 

7667 return fp.write(settings.pack(dummy_array, dtype_hint=np.floating)) 

7668 

7669 return 0 

7670 

7671 # PART INTERNAL ENERGY 

7672 if n_global_vars >= 6 + n_parts: 

7673 byte_checksum += _write_part_field( 

7674 ArrayType.part_internal_energy, n_parts, settings.ftype 

7675 ) 

7676 

7677 # PART KINETIC ENERGY 

7678 if n_global_vars >= 6 + 2 * n_parts: 

7679 byte_checksum += _write_part_field( 

7680 ArrayType.part_kinetic_energy, n_parts, settings.ftype 

7681 ) 

7682 

7683 # PART VELOCITY 

7684 if n_global_vars >= 6 + 5 * n_parts: 

7685 byte_checksum += _write_part_field( 

7686 ArrayType.part_velocity, (n_parts, 3), settings.ftype 

7687 ) 

7688 

7689 # PART MASS 

7690 if n_global_vars >= 6 + 6 * n_parts: 

7691 byte_checksum += _write_part_field(ArrayType.part_mass, n_parts, settings.ftype) 

7692 

7693 # PART HOURGLASS ENERGY 

7694 if n_global_vars >= 6 + 7 * n_parts: 

7695 byte_checksum += _write_part_field( 

7696 ArrayType.part_hourglass_energy, n_parts, settings.ftype 

7697 ) 

7698 

7699 # RIGID WALL 

7700 array_dims = { 

7701 ArrayType.global_timesteps: 0, 

7702 ArrayType.rigid_wall_force: 0, 

7703 ArrayType.rigid_wall_position: 0, 

7704 } 

7705 self.check_array_dims(array_dims, "n_timesteps") 

7706 array_dims = { 

7707 ArrayType.rigid_wall_force: 1, 

7708 ArrayType.rigid_wall_position: 1, 

7709 } 

7710 self.check_array_dims(array_dims, "n_rigid_walls") 

7711 self.check_array_dims({ArrayType.rigid_wall_position: 2}, "x_y_z", 3) 

7712 

7713 n_rigid_wall_vars = settings.header["n_rigid_wall_vars"] 

7714 n_rigid_walls = settings.header["n_rigid_walls"] 

7715 if n_global_vars >= 6 + 7 * n_parts + n_rigid_wall_vars * n_rigid_walls: 

7716 if n_rigid_wall_vars >= 1: 

7717 array = self.arrays[ArrayType.rigid_wall_force][i_timestep] 

7718 byte_checksum += fp.write(settings.pack(array, dtype_hint=np.floating)) 

7719 if n_rigid_wall_vars >= 4: 

7720 array = self.arrays[ArrayType.rigid_wall_position][i_timestep] 

7721 byte_checksum += fp.write(settings.pack(array, dtype_hint=np.floating)) 

7722 

7723 # check byte checksum 

7724 # pylint: disable = invalid-name 

7725 TIME_WORDSIZE = 1 

7726 byte_checksum_target = (TIME_WORDSIZE + settings.header["nglbv"]) * settings.wordsize 

7727 if byte_checksum != byte_checksum_target: 

7728 msg = ( 

7729 "byte checksum wrong: " 

7730 f"{byte_checksum_target} (header) != {byte_checksum} (checksum)" 

7731 ) 

7732 raise RuntimeError(msg) 

7733 

7734 # log 

7735 msg = "%s wrote %d bytes." 

7736 LOGGER.debug(msg, "_write_states_globals", byte_checksum) 

7737 

7738 return byte_checksum 

7739 

7740 def _write_states_nodes( 

7741 self, fp: typing.IO[Any], i_timestep: int, settings: D3plotWriterSettings 

7742 ) -> int: 

7743 

7744 n_nodes = settings.header["numnp"] 

7745 if n_nodes <= 0: 

7746 return 0 

7747 

7748 _check_ndim( 

7749 self, 

7750 { 

7751 ArrayType.node_displacement: ["n_timesteps", "n_nodes", "x_y_z"], 

7752 ArrayType.node_velocity: ["n_timesteps", "n_nodes", "vx_vy_vz"], 

7753 ArrayType.node_acceleration: ["n_timesteps", "n_nodes", "ax_ay_az"], 

7754 ArrayType.node_heat_flux: ["n_timesteps", "n_nodes", "hx_hy_hz"], 

7755 # INFO: cannot check since it may have 1 or 3 values per node 

7756 # ArrayType.node_temperature: ["n_timesteps","n_nodes"], 

7757 ArrayType.node_mass_scaling: ["n_timesteps", "n_nodes"], 

7758 ArrayType.node_temperature_gradient: ["n_timesteps", "n_nodes"], 

7759 ArrayType.node_residual_forces: ["n_timesteps", "n_nodes", "fx_fy_fz"], 

7760 ArrayType.node_residual_moments: ["n_timesteps", "n_nodes", "mx_my_mz"], 

7761 }, 

7762 ) 

7763 array_dims = { 

7764 ArrayType.global_timesteps: 0, 

7765 ArrayType.node_displacement: 0, 

7766 ArrayType.node_velocity: 0, 

7767 ArrayType.node_acceleration: 0, 

7768 ArrayType.node_heat_flux: 0, 

7769 ArrayType.node_temperature: 0, 

7770 ArrayType.node_mass_scaling: 0, 

7771 ArrayType.node_temperature_gradient: 0, 

7772 ArrayType.node_residual_forces: 0, 

7773 ArrayType.node_residual_moments: 0, 

7774 } 

7775 self.check_array_dims(array_dims, "n_timesteps") 

7776 array_dims = { 

7777 ArrayType.node_coordinates: 0, 

7778 ArrayType.node_displacement: 1, 

7779 ArrayType.node_velocity: 1, 

7780 ArrayType.node_acceleration: 1, 

7781 ArrayType.node_heat_flux: 1, 

7782 ArrayType.node_temperature: 1, 

7783 ArrayType.node_mass_scaling: 1, 

7784 ArrayType.node_temperature_gradient: 1, 

7785 ArrayType.node_residual_forces: 1, 

7786 ArrayType.node_residual_moments: 1, 

7787 } 

7788 self.check_array_dims(array_dims, "n_nodes") 

7789 self.check_array_dims({ArrayType.node_heat_flux: 2}, "x_y_z", 3) 

7790 self.check_array_dims({ArrayType.node_displacement: 2}, "dx_dy_dz", 3) 

7791 self.check_array_dims({ArrayType.node_velocity: 2}, "vx_vy_vz", 3) 

7792 self.check_array_dims({ArrayType.node_acceleration: 2}, "ax_ay_az", 3) 

7793 self.check_array_dims({ArrayType.node_residual_forces: 2}, "fx_fy_fz", 3) 

7794 self.check_array_dims({ArrayType.node_residual_moments: 2}, "mx_my_mz", 3) 

7795 

7796 byte_checksum = 0 

7797 

7798 it = settings.header["it"] 

7799 has_mass_scaling = False 

7800 if it >= 10: 

7801 it -= 10 

7802 has_mass_scaling = True 

7803 

7804 n_nodes = settings.header["numnp"] 

7805 

7806 # NODE DISPLACEMENT 

7807 if settings.header["iu"]: 

7808 array = self.arrays[ArrayType.node_displacement][i_timestep] 

7809 byte_checksum += fp.write(settings.pack(array, dtype_hint=np.floating)) 

7810 

7811 if it != 0: 

7812 

7813 # NODE TEMPERATURES 

7814 array_type = ArrayType.node_temperature 

7815 array = ( 

7816 self.arrays[array_type][i_timestep] 

7817 if array_type in self.arrays 

7818 else np.zeros(n_nodes, dtype=settings.ftype) 

7819 ) 

7820 

7821 # just 1 temperature per node 

7822 if it < 3: 

7823 byte_checksum += fp.write(settings.pack(array, dtype_hint=np.floating)) 

7824 # 3 temperatures per node 

7825 else: 

7826 self.check_array_dims({ArrayType.node_temperature: 2}, "node_layer", 3) 

7827 byte_checksum += fp.write(settings.pack(array, dtype_hint=np.floating)) 

7828 

7829 # NODE HEAT FLUX 

7830 if it >= 2: 

7831 array = self.arrays[ArrayType.node_heat_flux][i_timestep] 

7832 byte_checksum += fp.write(settings.pack(array, dtype_hint=np.floating)) 

7833 

7834 # NODE MASS SCALING 

7835 if has_mass_scaling: 

7836 array = self.arrays[ArrayType.node_mass_scaling][i_timestep] 

7837 byte_checksum += fp.write(settings.pack(array, dtype_hint=np.floating)) 

7838 

7839 # NODE TEMPERATURE GRADIENT 

7840 if settings.has_node_temperature_gradient: 

7841 array = self.arrays[ArrayType.node_temperature_gradient][i_timestep] 

7842 byte_checksum += fp.write(settings.pack(array, dtype_hint=np.floating)) 

7843 

7844 # NODE RESIDUAL FORCES 

7845 if settings.has_node_residual_forces: 

7846 array = ( 

7847 self.arrays[ArrayType.node_residual_forces][i_timestep] 

7848 if ArrayType.node_residual_forces in self.arrays 

7849 else np.zeros((n_nodes, 3), dtype=settings.ftype) 

7850 ) 

7851 byte_checksum += fp.write(settings.pack(array, dtype_hint=np.floating)) 

7852 

7853 # NODE RESIDUAL MOMENTS 

7854 if settings.has_node_residual_moments: 

7855 array = ( 

7856 self.arrays[ArrayType.node_residual_moments][i_timestep] 

7857 if ArrayType.node_residual_forces in self.arrays 

7858 else np.zeros((n_nodes, 3), dtype=settings.ftype) 

7859 ) 

7860 byte_checksum += fp.write(settings.pack(array, dtype_hint=np.floating)) 

7861 

7862 # NODE VELOCITY 

7863 if settings.header["iv"]: 

7864 array = self.arrays[ArrayType.node_velocity][i_timestep] 

7865 byte_checksum += fp.write(settings.pack(array, dtype_hint=np.floating)) 

7866 

7867 # NODE ACCELERATION 

7868 if settings.header["ia"]: 

7869 array = self.arrays[ArrayType.node_acceleration][i_timestep] 

7870 byte_checksum += fp.write(settings.pack(array, dtype_hint=np.floating)) 

7871 

7872 # check the checksum 

7873 n_thermal_vars = 0 

7874 if settings.header["it"] % 10 == 1: 

7875 n_thermal_vars = 1 

7876 elif settings.header["it"] % 10 == 2: 

7877 n_thermal_vars = 4 

7878 elif settings.header["it"] % 10 == 3: 

7879 n_thermal_vars = 6 

7880 

7881 if settings.header["it"] // 10 == 1: 

7882 n_thermal_vars += 1 

7883 

7884 n_temp_gradient_vars = settings.has_node_temperature_gradient 

7885 n_residual_forces_vars = settings.has_node_residual_forces * 3 

7886 n_residual_moments_vars = settings.has_node_residual_moments * 3 

7887 

7888 # pylint: disable = invalid-name 

7889 NDIM = 3 

7890 byte_checksum_target = ( 

7891 ( 

7892 (settings.header["iu"] + settings.header["iv"] + settings.header["ia"]) * NDIM 

7893 + n_thermal_vars 

7894 + n_temp_gradient_vars 

7895 + n_residual_forces_vars 

7896 + n_residual_moments_vars 

7897 ) 

7898 * settings.wordsize 

7899 * settings.header["numnp"] 

7900 ) 

7901 if byte_checksum != byte_checksum_target: 

7902 msg = ( 

7903 "byte checksum wrong: " 

7904 "{byte_checksum_target} (header) != {byte_checksum} (checksum)" 

7905 ) 

7906 raise RuntimeError(msg) 

7907 

7908 # log 

7909 msg = "%s wrote %d bytes." 

7910 LOGGER.debug(msg, "_write_states_nodes", byte_checksum) 

7911 

7912 return byte_checksum 

7913 

7914 def _write_states_solid_thermal_data( 

7915 self, fp: typing.IO[Any], i_timestep: int, settings: D3plotWriterSettings 

7916 ) -> int: 

7917 

7918 if settings.header["nt3d"] <= 0: 

7919 return 0 

7920 

7921 _check_ndim( 

7922 self, 

7923 { 

7924 ArrayType.element_solid_thermal_data: [ 

7925 "n_timesteps", 

7926 "n_solids", 

7927 "n_solids_thermal_vars", 

7928 ] 

7929 }, 

7930 ) 

7931 

7932 array_dims = { 

7933 ArrayType.global_timesteps: 0, 

7934 ArrayType.element_solid_thermal_data: 0, 

7935 } 

7936 self.check_array_dims(array_dims, "n_timesteps") 

7937 

7938 array_dims = { 

7939 ArrayType.element_solid_node_indexes: 0, 

7940 ArrayType.element_solid_thermal_data: 1, 

7941 } 

7942 self.check_array_dims(array_dims, "n_solids") 

7943 

7944 array = self.arrays[ArrayType.element_solid_thermal_data][i_timestep] 

7945 n_bytes_written = fp.write(settings.pack(array, dtype_hint=np.floating)) 

7946 

7947 # check bytes 

7948 n_bytes_expected = ( 

7949 settings.header["nt3d"] * abs(settings.header["nel8"]) * settings.wordsize 

7950 ) 

7951 if n_bytes_expected != n_bytes_written: 

7952 msg = ( 

7953 "byte checksum wrong: " 

7954 f"{n_bytes_expected} (header) != {n_bytes_written} (checksum)" 

7955 ) 

7956 raise RuntimeError(msg) 

7957 

7958 # log 

7959 msg = "%s wrote %d bytes." 

7960 LOGGER.debug(msg, "_write_states_thermal_data", n_bytes_written) 

7961 

7962 return n_bytes_written 

7963 

7964 def _write_states_solids( 

7965 self, fp: typing.IO[Any], i_timestep: int, settings: D3plotWriterSettings 

7966 ) -> int: 

7967 

7968 n_solids = abs(settings.header["nel8"]) 

7969 n_solid_vars = settings.header["nv3d"] 

7970 n_solid_layers = settings.n_solid_layers 

7971 

7972 if n_solids == 0 or n_solid_vars <= 0: 

7973 return 0 

7974 

7975 _check_ndim( 

7976 self, 

7977 { 

7978 ArrayType.element_solid_stress: [ 

7979 "n_timesteps", 

7980 "n_solids", 

7981 "n_solid_layers", 

7982 "σx_σy_σz_σxy_σyz_σxz", 

7983 ], 

7984 ArrayType.element_solid_effective_plastic_strain: [ 

7985 "n_timesteps", 

7986 "n_solid_layers", 

7987 "n_solids", 

7988 ], 

7989 ArrayType.element_solid_history_variables: [ 

7990 "n_timesteps", 

7991 "n_solids", 

7992 "n_solid_layers", 

7993 "n_solid_history_vars", 

7994 ], 

7995 ArrayType.element_solid_strain: [ 

7996 "n_timesteps", 

7997 "n_solids", 

7998 "n_solid_layers", 

7999 "εx_εy_εz_εxy_εyz_εxz", 

8000 ], 

8001 ArrayType.element_solid_plastic_strain_tensor: [ 

8002 "n_timesteps", 

8003 "n_solids", 

8004 "n_solid_layers", 

8005 "εx_εy_εz_εxy_εyz_εxz", 

8006 ], 

8007 ArrayType.element_solid_thermal_strain_tensor: [ 

8008 "n_timesteps", 

8009 "n_solids", 

8010 "n_solid_layers", 

8011 "εx_εy_εz_εxy_εyz_εxz", 

8012 ], 

8013 }, 

8014 ) 

8015 

8016 array_dims = { 

8017 ArrayType.global_timesteps: 0, 

8018 ArrayType.element_solid_stress: 0, 

8019 ArrayType.element_solid_effective_plastic_strain: 0, 

8020 ArrayType.element_solid_history_variables: 0, 

8021 ArrayType.element_solid_strain: 0, 

8022 ArrayType.element_solid_plastic_strain_tensor: 0, 

8023 ArrayType.element_solid_thermal_strain_tensor: 0, 

8024 } 

8025 self.check_array_dims(array_dims, "n_timesteps") 

8026 

8027 array_dims = { 

8028 ArrayType.element_solid_node_indexes: 0, 

8029 ArrayType.element_solid_stress: 1, 

8030 ArrayType.element_solid_effective_plastic_strain: 1, 

8031 ArrayType.element_solid_history_variables: 1, 

8032 ArrayType.element_solid_strain: 1, 

8033 ArrayType.element_solid_plastic_strain_tensor: 1, 

8034 ArrayType.element_solid_thermal_strain_tensor: 1, 

8035 } 

8036 self.check_array_dims(array_dims, "n_solids") 

8037 

8038 array_dims = { 

8039 ArrayType.element_solid_stress: 2, 

8040 ArrayType.element_solid_effective_plastic_strain: 2, 

8041 ArrayType.element_solid_history_variables: 2, 

8042 ArrayType.element_solid_strain: 2, 

8043 ArrayType.element_solid_plastic_strain_tensor: 2, 

8044 ArrayType.element_solid_thermal_strain_tensor: 2, 

8045 } 

8046 self.check_array_dims(array_dims, "n_solid_layers") 

8047 

8048 self.check_array_dims({ArrayType.element_solid_stress: 3}, "σx_σy_σz_σxy_σyz_σxz", 6) 

8049 

8050 self.check_array_dims({ArrayType.element_solid_strain: 3}, "εx_εy_εz_εxy_εyz_εxz", 6) 

8051 

8052 self.check_array_dims( 

8053 {ArrayType.element_solid_plastic_strain_tensor: 3}, "εx_εy_εz_εxy_εyz_εxz", 6 

8054 ) 

8055 

8056 self.check_array_dims( 

8057 {ArrayType.element_solid_thermal_strain_tensor: 3}, "εx_εy_εz_εxy_εyz_εxz", 6 

8058 ) 

8059 

8060 # allocate array 

8061 solid_data = np.zeros( 

8062 (n_solids, n_solid_layers, n_solid_vars // n_solid_layers), dtype=settings.ftype 

8063 ) 

8064 

8065 # SOLID STRESS 

8066 if ArrayType.element_solid_stress in self.arrays: 

8067 try: 

8068 array = self.arrays[ArrayType.element_solid_stress][i_timestep] 

8069 solid_data[:, :, 0:6] = array 

8070 except Exception: 

8071 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

8072 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

8073 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_write_states_solids, element_solid_stress", trb_msg) 

8074 

8075 # SOLID EFFECTIVE PSTRAIN 

8076 if ArrayType.element_solid_effective_plastic_strain in self.arrays: 

8077 try: 

8078 array = self.arrays[ArrayType.element_solid_effective_plastic_strain][i_timestep] 

8079 solid_data[:, :, 6] = array 

8080 except Exception: 

8081 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

8082 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

8083 LOGGER.warning( 

8084 msg, "_write_states_solids, element_solid_effective_plastic_strain", trb_msg 

8085 ) 

8086 

8087 # SOLID HISTORY VARIABLES 

8088 # (strains, pstrain tensor and thermal tensor are excluded here) 

8089 has_strain = settings.header["istrn"] 

8090 n_solid_history_variables = ( 

8091 settings.header["neiph"] 

8092 - 6 * has_strain 

8093 - 6 * settings.has_plastic_strain_tensor 

8094 - 6 * settings.has_thermal_strain_tensor 

8095 ) 

8096 

8097 if n_solid_history_variables: 

8098 try: 

8099 array = self.arrays[ArrayType.element_solid_history_variables][i_timestep] 

8100 solid_data[:, :, 7 : 7 + n_solid_history_variables] = array 

8101 except Exception: 

8102 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

8103 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

8104 LOGGER.warning( 

8105 msg, "_write_states_solids, element_solid_history_variables", trb_msg 

8106 ) 

8107 

8108 # SOLID STRAIN 

8109 if has_strain and ArrayType.element_solid_strain in self.arrays: 

8110 try: 

8111 array = self.arrays[ArrayType.element_solid_strain][i_timestep] 

8112 offset = 7 + n_solid_history_variables 

8113 solid_data[:, :, offset : offset + 6] = array 

8114 except Exception: 

8115 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

8116 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

8117 LOGGER.warning(msg, "_write_states_solids, element_solid_strain", trb_msg) 

8118 

8119 # PLASTIC STRAIN TENSOR 

8120 if ( 

8121 settings.has_plastic_strain_tensor 

8122 and ArrayType.element_solid_plastic_strain_tensor in self.arrays 

8123 ): 

8124 try: 

8125 array = self.arrays[ArrayType.element_solid_plastic_strain_tensor][i_timestep] 

8126 offset = 7 + n_solid_history_variables + 6 * has_strain 

8127 solid_data[:, :, offset : offset + 6] = array 

8128 except Exception: 

8129 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

8130 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

8131 LOGGER.warning( 

8132 msg, "_write_states_solids, element_solid_plastic_strain_tensor", trb_msg 

8133 ) 

8134 

8135 # THERMAL STRAIN TENSOR 

8136 if ( 

8137 settings.has_thermal_strain_tensor 

8138 and ArrayType.element_solid_thermal_strain_tensor in self.arrays 

8139 ): 

8140 try: 

8141 array = self.arrays[ArrayType.element_solid_thermal_strain_tensor][i_timestep] 

8142 offset = ( 

8143 7 

8144 + n_solid_history_variables 

8145 + 6 * has_strain 

8146 + 6 * settings.has_plastic_strain_tensor 

8147 ) 

8148 solid_data[:, :, offset : offset + 6] = array 

8149 except Exception: 

8150 trb_msg = traceback.format_exc() 

8151 msg = "A failure in %s was caught:\n%s" 

8152 LOGGER.warning( 

8153 msg, "_write_states_solids, element_solid_thermal_strain_tensor", trb_msg 

8154 ) 

8155 

8156 n_bytes_written = fp.write(settings.pack(solid_data, dtype_hint=np.floating)) 

8157 

8158 # check bytes 

8159 n_bytes_expected = ( 

8160 settings.header["nv3d"] * abs(settings.header["nel8"]) * settings.wordsize 

8161 ) 

8162 if n_bytes_expected != n_bytes_written: 

8163 msg = ( 

8164 "byte checksum wrong: " 

8165 f"{n_bytes_expected} (header) != {n_bytes_written} (checksum)" 

8166 ) 

8167 raise RuntimeError(msg) 

8168 

8169 # log 

8170 msg = "%s wrote %d bytes." 

8171 LOGGER.debug(msg, "_write_states_solids", n_bytes_written) 

8172 

8173 return n_bytes_written 

8174 

8175 def _write_states_tshells( 

8176 self, fp: typing.IO[Any], i_timestep: int, settings: D3plotWriterSettings 

8177 ) -> int: 

8178 

8179 n_tshells = settings.header["nelth"] 

8180 n_tshell_vars = settings.header["nv3dt"] 

8181 if n_tshells <= 0 or n_tshell_vars <= 0: 

8182 return 0 

8183 

8184 _check_ndim( 

8185 self, 

8186 { 

8187 ArrayType.element_tshell_stress: [ 

8188 "n_timesteps", 

8189 "n_tshells", 

8190 "n_shell_layers", 

8191 "σx_σy_σz_σxy_σyz_σxz", 

8192 ], 

8193 ArrayType.element_tshell_strain: [ 

8194 "n_timesteps", 

8195 "n_tshells", 

8196 "upper_lower", 

8197 "εx_εy_εz_εxy_εyz_εxz", 

8198 ], 

8199 ArrayType.element_tshell_effective_plastic_strain: [ 

8200 "n_timesteps", 

8201 "n_tshells", 

8202 "n_shell_layers", 

8203 ], 

8204 ArrayType.element_tshell_history_variables: [ 

8205 "n_timesteps", 

8206 "n_tshells", 

8207 "n_shell_layers", 

8208 "n_tshell_history_vars", 

8209 ], 

8210 }, 

8211 ) 

8212 

8213 array_dims = { 

8214 ArrayType.global_timesteps: 0, 

8215 ArrayType.element_tshell_stress: 0, 

8216 ArrayType.element_tshell_strain: 0, 

8217 ArrayType.element_tshell_effective_plastic_strain: 0, 

8218 ArrayType.element_tshell_history_variables: 0, 

8219 } 

8220 self.check_array_dims(array_dims, "n_timesteps") 

8221 

8222 array_dims = { 

8223 ArrayType.element_tshell_node_indexes: 0, 

8224 ArrayType.element_tshell_stress: 1, 

8225 ArrayType.element_tshell_strain: 1, 

8226 ArrayType.element_tshell_effective_plastic_strain: 1, 

8227 ArrayType.element_tshell_history_variables: 1, 

8228 } 

8229 self.check_array_dims(array_dims, "n_tshells") 

8230 

8231 self.check_array_dims({ArrayType.element_tshell_stress: 3}, "σx_σy_σz_σxy_σyz_σxz", 6) 

8232 

8233 self.check_array_dims({ArrayType.element_tshell_strain: 2}, "upper_lower", 2) 

8234 

8235 self.check_array_dims({ArrayType.element_tshell_strain: 3}, "εx_εy_εz_εxy_εyz_εxz", 6) 

8236 

8237 has_stress = settings.header["ioshl1"] == 1000 

8238 has_pstrain = settings.header["ioshl2"] == 1000 

8239 n_history_vars = settings.header["neips"] 

8240 n_layer_vars = settings.n_shell_layers * (6 * has_stress + has_pstrain + n_history_vars) 

8241 

8242 tshell_data = np.zeros((n_tshells, n_tshell_vars), settings.ftype) 

8243 tshell_layer_data = tshell_data[:, :n_layer_vars].reshape( 

8244 (n_tshells, settings.n_shell_layers, -1) 

8245 ) 

8246 tshell_nonlayer_data = tshell_data[:, n_layer_vars:] 

8247 

8248 # TSHELL STRESS 

8249 if has_stress: 

8250 if ArrayType.element_tshell_stress in self.arrays: 

8251 array = self.arrays[ArrayType.element_tshell_stress][i_timestep] 

8252 tshell_layer_data[:, :, 0:6] = array 

8253 

8254 # TSHELL EFF. PLASTIC STRAIN 

8255 if has_pstrain: 

8256 if ArrayType.element_tshell_effective_plastic_strain in self.arrays: 

8257 array = self.arrays[ArrayType.element_tshell_effective_plastic_strain][i_timestep] 

8258 start_index = 6 * has_stress 

8259 tshell_layer_data[:, :, start_index] = array 

8260 

8261 # TSHELL HISTORY VARS 

8262 if n_history_vars != 0: 

8263 if ArrayType.element_tshell_history_variables in self.arrays: 

8264 array = self.arrays[ArrayType.element_tshell_history_variables][i_timestep] 

8265 start_index = 6 * has_stress + has_pstrain 

8266 end_index = start_index + array.shape[2] 

8267 tshell_layer_data[:, :, start_index:end_index] = array 

8268 

8269 # TSHELL STRAIN 

8270 if settings.header["istrn"]: 

8271 if ArrayType.element_tshell_strain in self.arrays: 

8272 array = self.arrays[ArrayType.element_tshell_strain][i_timestep] 

8273 start_index = 6 * has_stress + has_pstrain + n_history_vars 

8274 tshell_nonlayer_data[:, :] = array.reshape(n_tshells, 12) 

8275 

8276 n_bytes_written = fp.write(settings.pack(tshell_data, dtype_hint=np.floating)) 

8277 

8278 # check bytes 

8279 n_bytes_expected = ( 

8280 settings.header["nv3dt"] * abs(settings.header["nelth"]) * settings.wordsize 

8281 ) 

8282 if n_bytes_expected != n_bytes_written: 

8283 msg = ( 

8284 "byte checksum wrong: " 

8285 f"{n_bytes_expected} (header) != {n_bytes_written} (checksum)" 

8286 ) 

8287 raise RuntimeError(msg) 

8288 

8289 # log 

8290 msg = "%s wrote %d bytes." 

8291 LOGGER.debug(msg, "_write_states_tshells", n_bytes_written) 

8292 

8293 return n_bytes_written 

8294 

8295 def _write_states_beams( 

8296 self, fp: typing.IO[Any], i_timestep: int, settings: D3plotWriterSettings 

8297 ) -> int: 

8298 

8299 n_beams = settings.header["nel2"] 

8300 n_beam_vars = settings.header["nv1d"] 

8301 if n_beams <= 0 or n_beam_vars <= 0: 

8302 return 0 

8303 

8304 n_beam_layers = settings.header["beamip"] 

8305 n_beam_history_vars = settings.header["neipb"] 

8306 

8307 _check_ndim( 

8308 self, 

8309 { 

8310 ArrayType.element_beam_axial_force: ["n_timesteps", "n_beams"], 

8311 ArrayType.element_beam_shear_force: ["n_timesteps", "n_beams", "fs_ft"], 

8312 ArrayType.element_beam_bending_moment: ["n_timesteps", "n_beams", "ms_mt"], 

8313 ArrayType.element_beam_torsion_moment: ["n_timesteps", "n_beams"], 

8314 ArrayType.element_beam_shear_stress: [ 

8315 "n_timesteps", 

8316 "n_beams", 

8317 "n_beam_layers", 

8318 "σrs_σtr", 

8319 ], 

8320 ArrayType.element_beam_axial_stress: ["n_timesteps", "n_beams", "n_beam_layers"], 

8321 ArrayType.element_beam_plastic_strain: ["n_timesteps", "n_beams", "n_beam_layers"], 

8322 ArrayType.element_beam_axial_strain: ["n_timesteps", "n_beams", "n_beam_layers"], 

8323 ArrayType.element_beam_history_vars: [ 

8324 "n_timesteps", 

8325 "n_beams", 

8326 "n_beam_layers+3", 

8327 "n_beam_history_vars", 

8328 ], 

8329 }, 

8330 ) 

8331 

8332 array_dims = { 

8333 ArrayType.global_timesteps: 0, 

8334 ArrayType.element_beam_axial_force: 0, 

8335 ArrayType.element_beam_shear_force: 0, 

8336 ArrayType.element_beam_bending_moment: 0, 

8337 ArrayType.element_beam_torsion_moment: 0, 

8338 ArrayType.element_beam_shear_stress: 0, 

8339 ArrayType.element_beam_axial_stress: 0, 

8340 ArrayType.element_beam_plastic_strain: 0, 

8341 ArrayType.element_beam_axial_strain: 0, 

8342 ArrayType.element_beam_history_vars: 0, 

8343 } 

8344 self.check_array_dims(array_dims, "n_timesteps") 

8345 array_dims = { 

8346 ArrayType.element_beam_axial_force: 1, 

8347 ArrayType.element_beam_shear_force: 1, 

8348 ArrayType.element_beam_bending_moment: 1, 

8349 ArrayType.element_beam_torsion_moment: 1, 

8350 ArrayType.element_beam_shear_stress: 1, 

8351 ArrayType.element_beam_axial_stress: 1, 

8352 ArrayType.element_beam_plastic_strain: 1, 

8353 ArrayType.element_beam_axial_strain: 1, 

8354 ArrayType.element_beam_history_vars: 1, 

8355 } 

8356 self.check_array_dims(array_dims, "n_beams") 

8357 self.check_array_dims({ArrayType.element_beam_shear_force: 2}, "fs_ft", 2) 

8358 self.check_array_dims({ArrayType.element_beam_bending_moment: 2}, "ms_mt", 2) 

8359 array_dims = { 

8360 ArrayType.element_beam_shear_stress: 2, 

8361 ArrayType.element_beam_axial_stress: 2, 

8362 ArrayType.element_beam_plastic_strain: 2, 

8363 ArrayType.element_beam_axial_strain: 2, 

8364 ArrayType.element_beam_history_vars: 2, 

8365 } 

8366 n_beam_layers = self.check_array_dims(array_dims, "n_beam_layers") 

8367 self.check_array_dims({ArrayType.element_beam_shear_stress: 3}, "σrs_σtr", 2) 

8368 self.check_array_dims( 

8369 {ArrayType.element_beam_history_vars: 2}, "n_modes", n_beam_layers + 3 

8370 ) 

8371 

8372 # allocate buffer 

8373 beam_data = np.zeros((n_beams, n_beam_vars), dtype=settings.ftype) 

8374 n_layer_vars_total = 5 * n_beam_layers 

8375 beam_layer_data = beam_data[:, 6 : 6 + n_layer_vars_total].reshape( 

8376 (n_beams, n_beam_layers, 5) 

8377 ) 

8378 beam_history_vars = beam_data[:, 6 + n_layer_vars_total :].reshape( 

8379 (n_beams, 3 + n_beam_layers, n_beam_history_vars) 

8380 ) 

8381 

8382 # BEAM AXIAL FORCE 

8383 if ArrayType.element_beam_axial_force in self.arrays: 

8384 array = self.arrays[ArrayType.element_beam_axial_force][i_timestep] 

8385 beam_data[:, 0] = array 

8386 

8387 # BEAM SHEAR FORCE 

8388 if ArrayType.element_beam_shear_force in self.arrays: 

8389 array = self.arrays[ArrayType.element_beam_shear_force][i_timestep] 

8390 beam_data[:, 1:3] = array 

8391 

8392 # BEAM BENDING MOMENTUM 

8393 if ArrayType.element_beam_bending_moment in self.arrays: 

8394 array = self.arrays[ArrayType.element_beam_bending_moment][i_timestep] 

8395 beam_data[:, 3:5] = array 

8396 

8397 # BEAM TORSION MOMENTUM 

8398 if ArrayType.element_beam_torsion_moment in self.arrays: 

8399 array = self.arrays[ArrayType.element_beam_torsion_moment][i_timestep] 

8400 beam_data[:, 5] = array 

8401 

8402 if n_beam_layers: 

8403 array = ( 

8404 self.arrays[ArrayType.element_beam_axial_stress][i_timestep] 

8405 if ArrayType.element_beam_axial_stress in self.arrays 

8406 else np.zeros((n_beams, n_beam_layers), dtype=settings.ftype) 

8407 ) 

8408 beam_layer_data[:, :, 0] = array 

8409 

8410 array = ( 

8411 self.arrays[ArrayType.element_beam_shear_stress][i_timestep] 

8412 if ArrayType.element_beam_shear_stress in self.arrays 

8413 else np.zeros((n_beams, n_beam_layers, 2), dtype=settings.ftype) 

8414 ) 

8415 beam_layer_data[:, :, 1:3] = array 

8416 

8417 array = ( 

8418 self.arrays[ArrayType.element_beam_plastic_strain][i_timestep] 

8419 if ArrayType.element_beam_plastic_strain in self.arrays 

8420 else np.zeros((n_beams, n_beam_layers), dtype=settings.ftype) 

8421 ) 

8422 beam_layer_data[:, :, 3] = array 

8423 

8424 array = ( 

8425 self.arrays[ArrayType.element_beam_axial_strain][i_timestep] 

8426 if ArrayType.element_beam_axial_strain in self.arrays 

8427 else np.zeros((n_beams, n_beam_layers), dtype=settings.ftype) 

8428 ) 

8429 beam_layer_data[:, :, 4] = array 

8430 

8431 # BEAM HISTORY VARIABLES 

8432 if n_beam_history_vars: 

8433 array = ( 

8434 self.arrays[ArrayType.element_beam_history_vars][i_timestep] 

8435 if ArrayType.element_beam_history_vars in self.arrays 

8436 else np.zeros( 

8437 (n_beams, n_beam_layers + 3, n_beam_history_vars), dtype=settings.ftype 

8438 ) 

8439 ) 

8440 beam_history_vars[:, :, :] = array 

8441 

8442 n_bytes_written = fp.write(settings.pack(beam_data, dtype_hint=np.floating)) 

8443 

8444 # check bytes 

8445 n_bytes_expected = settings.header["nv1d"] * settings.header["nel2"] * settings.wordsize 

8446 if n_bytes_expected != n_bytes_written: 

8447 msg = ( 

8448 "byte checksum wrong: " 

8449 f"{n_bytes_expected} (header) != {n_bytes_written} (checksum)" 

8450 ) 

8451 raise RuntimeError(msg) 

8452 

8453 # log 

8454 msg = "%s wrote %d bytes." 

8455 LOGGER.debug(msg, "_write_states_tshells", n_bytes_written) 

8456 

8457 return n_bytes_written 

8458 

8459 def _write_states_shells( 

8460 self, fp: typing.IO[Any], i_timestep: int, settings: D3plotWriterSettings 

8461 ) -> int: 

8462 

8463 n_shells = settings.header["nel4"] 

8464 n_shell_vars = settings.header["nv2d"] 

8465 n_rigid_shells = settings.n_rigid_shells 

8466 is_d3part = self.header.filetype == D3plotFiletype.D3PART 

8467 # d3part writes results also for rigid shells 

8468 n_reduced_shells = n_shells if is_d3part else n_shells - n_rigid_shells 

8469 

8470 if n_reduced_shells <= 0 or n_shell_vars <= 0: 

8471 return 0 

8472 

8473 has_stress = settings.header["ioshl1"] == 1000 

8474 has_pstrain = settings.header["ioshl2"] == 1000 

8475 has_forces = settings.header["ioshl3"] == 1000 

8476 has_else = settings.header["ioshl4"] == 1000 

8477 has_strain = settings.header["istrn"] != 0 

8478 n_shell_history_vars = settings.header["neips"] 

8479 

8480 _check_ndim( 

8481 self, 

8482 { 

8483 ArrayType.element_shell_stress: [ 

8484 "n_timesteps", 

8485 "n_shells", 

8486 "n_shell_layers", 

8487 "σx_σy_σz_σxy_σyz_σxz", 

8488 ], 

8489 ArrayType.element_shell_effective_plastic_strain: [ 

8490 "n_timesteps", 

8491 "n_shells", 

8492 "n_shell_layers", 

8493 ], 

8494 ArrayType.element_shell_history_vars: [ 

8495 "n_timesteps", 

8496 "n_shells", 

8497 "n_shell_layers", 

8498 "n_shell_history_vars", 

8499 ], 

8500 ArrayType.element_shell_bending_moment: ["n_timesteps", "n_shells", "mx_my_mxy"], 

8501 ArrayType.element_shell_shear_force: ["n_timesteps", "n_shells", "qx_qy"], 

8502 ArrayType.element_shell_normal_force: ["n_timesteps", "n_shells", "nx_ny_nxy"], 

8503 ArrayType.element_shell_thickness: ["n_timesteps", "n_shells"], 

8504 ArrayType.element_shell_unknown_variables: [ 

8505 "n_timesteps", 

8506 "n_shells", 

8507 "n_extra_vars", 

8508 ], 

8509 ArrayType.element_shell_internal_energy: ["n_timesteps", "n_shells"], 

8510 ArrayType.element_shell_strain: [ 

8511 "n_timesteps", 

8512 "n_shells", 

8513 "upper_lower", 

8514 "εx_εy_εz_εxy_εyz_εxz", 

8515 ], 

8516 }, 

8517 ) 

8518 

8519 array_dims = { 

8520 ArrayType.global_timesteps: 0, 

8521 ArrayType.element_shell_stress: 0, 

8522 ArrayType.element_shell_effective_plastic_strain: 0, 

8523 ArrayType.element_shell_history_vars: 0, 

8524 ArrayType.element_shell_bending_moment: 0, 

8525 ArrayType.element_shell_shear_force: 0, 

8526 ArrayType.element_shell_normal_force: 0, 

8527 ArrayType.element_shell_thickness: 0, 

8528 ArrayType.element_shell_unknown_variables: 0, 

8529 ArrayType.element_shell_internal_energy: 0, 

8530 ArrayType.element_shell_strain: 0, 

8531 } 

8532 self.check_array_dims(array_dims, "n_timesteps") 

8533 

8534 array_dims = { 

8535 ArrayType.element_shell_stress: 1, 

8536 ArrayType.element_shell_effective_plastic_strain: 1, 

8537 ArrayType.element_shell_history_vars: 1, 

8538 ArrayType.element_shell_bending_moment: 1, 

8539 ArrayType.element_shell_shear_force: 1, 

8540 ArrayType.element_shell_normal_force: 1, 

8541 ArrayType.element_shell_thickness: 1, 

8542 ArrayType.element_shell_unknown_variables: 1, 

8543 ArrayType.element_shell_internal_energy: 1, 

8544 ArrayType.element_shell_strain: 1, 

8545 } 

8546 n_reduced_shells = self.check_array_dims(array_dims, "n_shells") 

8547 if not is_d3part and n_reduced_shells != n_shells - n_rigid_shells: 

8548 msg = ( 

8549 "Parts with mattyp 20 (rigid material) were specified." 

8550 " For these parts no state data is output in dyna." 

8551 " The state arrays are thus expected output data for only" 

8552 f" {n_shells - n_rigid_shells} shells and not {n_reduced_shells}." 

8553 ) 

8554 raise ValueError(msg) 

8555 

8556 array_dims = { 

8557 ArrayType.element_shell_stress: 2, 

8558 ArrayType.element_shell_effective_plastic_strain: 2, 

8559 ArrayType.element_shell_history_vars: 2, 

8560 } 

8561 n_shell_layers = self.check_array_dims(array_dims, "n_shell_layers") 

8562 

8563 self.check_array_dims({ArrayType.element_shell_stress: 3}, "σx_σy_σz_σxy_σyz_σxz", 6) 

8564 self.check_array_dims({ArrayType.element_shell_bending_moment: 2}, "mx_my_mxy", 3) 

8565 self.check_array_dims({ArrayType.element_shell_shear_force: 2}, "qx_qy") 

8566 self.check_array_dims({ArrayType.element_shell_strain: 2}, "upper_lower", 2) 

8567 self.check_array_dims({ArrayType.element_shell_strain: 3}, "εx_εy_εz_εxy_εyz_εxz", 6) 

8568 

8569 # allocate buffer 

8570 shell_data = np.zeros((n_reduced_shells, n_shell_vars), dtype=settings.ftype) 

8571 n_layer_vars = has_stress * 6 + has_pstrain + n_shell_history_vars 

8572 n_layer_vars_total = n_layer_vars * n_shell_layers 

8573 

8574 shell_layer_data = shell_data[:, :n_layer_vars_total].reshape( 

8575 (n_reduced_shells, n_shell_layers, n_layer_vars) 

8576 ) 

8577 shell_nonlayer_data = shell_data[:, n_layer_vars_total:] 

8578 

8579 start_layer_index = 0 

8580 end_layer_index = 0 

8581 

8582 # SHELL STRESS 

8583 if has_stress: 

8584 start_layer_index = 0 

8585 end_layer_index = 6 

8586 if ArrayType.element_shell_stress in self.arrays: 

8587 array = self.arrays[ArrayType.element_shell_stress][i_timestep] 

8588 shell_layer_data[:, :, start_layer_index:end_layer_index] = array 

8589 

8590 # EFF PSTRAIN 

8591 if has_pstrain: 

8592 start_layer_index = end_layer_index 

8593 end_layer_index = start_layer_index + has_pstrain 

8594 if ArrayType.element_shell_effective_plastic_strain in self.arrays: 

8595 array = self.arrays[ArrayType.element_shell_effective_plastic_strain][i_timestep] 

8596 shell_layer_data[:, :, start_layer_index:end_layer_index] = array.reshape( 

8597 (n_reduced_shells, n_shell_layers, 1) 

8598 ) 

8599 

8600 # SHELL HISTORY VARS 

8601 if n_shell_history_vars: 

8602 start_layer_index = end_layer_index 

8603 end_layer_index = start_layer_index + n_shell_history_vars 

8604 if ArrayType.element_shell_history_vars in self.arrays: 

8605 array = self.arrays[ArrayType.element_shell_history_vars][i_timestep] 

8606 n_hist_vars_arr = array.shape[2] 

8607 end_layer_index2 = start_layer_index + min(n_hist_vars_arr, n_shell_history_vars) 

8608 shell_layer_data[:, :, start_layer_index:end_layer_index2] = array 

8609 

8610 start_index = 0 

8611 end_index = 0 

8612 

8613 # SHELL FORCES 

8614 if has_forces: 

8615 start_index = end_index 

8616 end_index = start_index + 8 

8617 

8618 # MOMENTUM 

8619 if ArrayType.element_shell_bending_moment in self.arrays: 

8620 start_index2 = start_index 

8621 end_index2 = start_index + 3 

8622 array = self.arrays[ArrayType.element_shell_bending_moment][i_timestep] 

8623 shell_nonlayer_data[:, start_index2:end_index2] = array 

8624 

8625 # SHEAR 

8626 if ArrayType.element_shell_shear_force in self.arrays: 

8627 start_index2 = start_index + 3 

8628 end_index2 = start_index + 5 

8629 array = self.arrays[ArrayType.element_shell_shear_force][i_timestep] 

8630 shell_nonlayer_data[:, start_index2:end_index2] = array 

8631 

8632 # NORMAL 

8633 if ArrayType.element_shell_normal_force in self.arrays: 

8634 start_index2 = start_index + 5 

8635 end_index2 = start_index + 8 

8636 array = self.arrays[ArrayType.element_shell_normal_force][i_timestep] 

8637 shell_nonlayer_data[:, start_index2:end_index2] = array 

8638 

8639 if has_else: 

8640 start_index = end_index 

8641 end_index = start_index + 3 

8642 

8643 # THICKNESS 

8644 if ArrayType.element_shell_thickness in self.arrays: 

8645 start_index2 = start_index 

8646 end_index2 = start_index + 1 

8647 array = self.arrays[ArrayType.element_shell_thickness][i_timestep] 

8648 shell_nonlayer_data[:, start_index2:end_index2] = array.reshape( 

8649 (n_reduced_shells, 1) 

8650 ) 

8651 

8652 # ELEMENT SPECIFIC VARS 

8653 if ArrayType.element_shell_unknown_variables in self.arrays: 

8654 start_index2 = start_index + 1 

8655 end_index2 = start_index + 3 

8656 array = self.arrays[ArrayType.element_shell_unknown_variables][i_timestep] 

8657 shell_nonlayer_data[:, start_index2:end_index2] = array 

8658 

8659 # SHELL STRAIN 

8660 # 

8661 # Strain is squeezed between the 3rd and 4th var of the else block 

8662 if has_strain: 

8663 start_index = end_index 

8664 end_index = start_index + 12 

8665 

8666 if ArrayType.element_shell_strain in self.arrays: 

8667 array = self.arrays[ArrayType.element_shell_strain][i_timestep] 

8668 shell_nonlayer_data[:, start_index:end_index] = array.reshape( 

8669 (n_reduced_shells, 12) 

8670 ) 

8671 

8672 # INTERNAL ENERGY 

8673 if has_else: 

8674 start_index = end_index 

8675 end_index = start_index + 1 

8676 

8677 if ArrayType.element_shell_internal_energy in self.arrays: 

8678 array = self.arrays[ArrayType.element_shell_internal_energy][i_timestep] 

8679 shell_nonlayer_data[:, start_index:end_index] = array.reshape((n_reduced_shells, 1)) 

8680 

8681 # THERMAL STRAIN TENSOR 

8682 if settings.has_plastic_strain_tensor: 

8683 start_index = end_index 

8684 end_index = start_index + n_shell_layers * 6 

8685 

8686 if ArrayType.element_shell_plastic_strain_tensor in self.arrays: 

8687 array = self.arrays[ArrayType.element_shell_plastic_strain_tensor][i_timestep] 

8688 shell_nonlayer_data[:, start_index:end_index] = array.reshape( 

8689 (n_reduced_shells, n_shell_layers * 6) 

8690 ) 

8691 

8692 # PLASTIC THERMAL TENSOR 

8693 if settings.has_thermal_strain_tensor: 

8694 start_index = end_index 

8695 end_index = start_index + 6 

8696 

8697 if ArrayType.element_shell_thermal_strain_tensor in self.arrays: 

8698 array = self.arrays[ArrayType.element_shell_thermal_strain_tensor][i_timestep] 

8699 shell_nonlayer_data[:, start_index:end_index] = array.reshape((n_reduced_shells, 6)) 

8700 

8701 n_bytes_written = fp.write(settings.pack(shell_data, dtype_hint=np.floating)) 

8702 

8703 # check bytes 

8704 # *(settings.header["nel4"]-settings.n_rigid_shells)\ 

8705 n_bytes_expected = settings.header["nv2d"] * n_reduced_shells * settings.wordsize 

8706 if n_bytes_expected != n_bytes_written: 

8707 msg = ( 

8708 "byte checksum wrong: " 

8709 f"{n_bytes_expected} (header) != {n_bytes_written} (checksum)" 

8710 ) 

8711 raise RuntimeError(msg) 

8712 

8713 # log 

8714 msg = "%s wrote %d bytes." 

8715 LOGGER.debug(msg, "_write_states_shells", n_bytes_written) 

8716 

8717 return n_bytes_written 

8718 

8719 def _write_states_deletion_info( 

8720 self, fp: typing.IO[Any], i_timestep: int, settings: D3plotWriterSettings 

8721 ) -> int: 

8722 

8723 if settings.mdlopt <= 0: 

8724 return 0 

8725 

8726 n_bytes_written = 0 

8727 n_bytes_expected = 0 

8728 

8729 # NODE DELETION 

8730 if settings.mdlopt == 1: 

8731 

8732 _check_ndim(self, {ArrayType.node_is_alive: ["n_timesteps", "n_nodes"]}) 

8733 

8734 array_dims = { 

8735 ArrayType.global_timesteps: 0, 

8736 ArrayType.node_is_alive: 0, 

8737 } 

8738 self.check_array_dims(array_dims, "n_timesteps") 

8739 

8740 array_dims = { 

8741 ArrayType.node_coordinates: 0, 

8742 ArrayType.node_is_alive: 1, 

8743 } 

8744 self.check_array_dims(array_dims, "n_nodes") 

8745 

8746 n_nodes = settings.header["numnp"] 

8747 

8748 array = ( 

8749 self.arrays[ArrayType.node_is_alive] 

8750 if ArrayType.node_is_alive in self.arrays 

8751 else np.zeros(n_nodes, dtype=settings.ftype) 

8752 ) 

8753 

8754 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(array, dtype_hint=np.floating)) 

8755 

8756 # check 

8757 n_bytes_expected = settings.header["numnp"] * settings.wordsize 

8758 

8759 # ELEMENT DELETION 

8760 elif settings.mdlopt == 2: 

8761 

8762 _check_ndim( 

8763 self, 

8764 { 

8765 ArrayType.element_solid_is_alive: ["n_timesteps", "n_solids"], 

8766 ArrayType.element_shell_is_alive: ["n_timesteps", "n_shells"], 

8767 ArrayType.element_beam_is_alive: ["n_timesteps", "n_beams"], 

8768 ArrayType.element_tshell_is_alive: ["n_timesteps", "n_tshells"], 

8769 }, 

8770 ) 

8771 

8772 array_dims = { 

8773 ArrayType.global_timesteps: 0, 

8774 ArrayType.element_solid_is_alive: 0, 

8775 ArrayType.element_shell_is_alive: 0, 

8776 ArrayType.element_beam_is_alive: 0, 

8777 ArrayType.element_tshell_is_alive: 0, 

8778 } 

8779 self.check_array_dims(array_dims, "n_timesteps") 

8780 

8781 array_dims = { 

8782 ArrayType.element_solid_node_indexes: 0, 

8783 ArrayType.element_solid_is_alive: 1, 

8784 } 

8785 self.check_array_dims(array_dims, "n_solids") 

8786 

8787 array_dims = { 

8788 ArrayType.element_beam_node_indexes: 0, 

8789 ArrayType.element_beam_is_alive: 1, 

8790 } 

8791 self.check_array_dims(array_dims, "n_beams") 

8792 

8793 array_dims = { 

8794 ArrayType.element_shell_node_indexes: 0, 

8795 ArrayType.element_shell_is_alive: 1, 

8796 } 

8797 self.check_array_dims(array_dims, "n_shells") 

8798 

8799 array_dims = { 

8800 ArrayType.element_tshell_node_indexes: 0, 

8801 ArrayType.element_tshell_is_alive: 1, 

8802 } 

8803 self.check_array_dims(array_dims, "n_tshells") 

8804 

8805 n_solids = settings.header["nel8"] 

8806 n_tshells = settings.header["nelth"] 

8807 n_shells = settings.header["nel4"] 

8808 n_beams = settings.header["nel2"] 

8809 

8810 # SOLID DELETION 

8811 array = ( 

8812 self.arrays[ArrayType.element_solid_is_alive][i_timestep] 

8813 if ArrayType.element_solid_is_alive in self.arrays 

8814 else np.ones(n_solids, dtype=settings.ftype) 

8815 ) 

8816 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(array, dtype_hint=np.floating)) 

8817 

8818 # THICK SHELL DELETION 

8819 array = ( 

8820 self.arrays[ArrayType.element_tshell_is_alive][i_timestep] 

8821 if ArrayType.element_tshell_is_alive in self.arrays 

8822 else np.ones(n_tshells, dtype=settings.ftype) 

8823 ) 

8824 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(array, dtype_hint=np.floating)) 

8825 

8826 # SHELL DELETION 

8827 array = ( 

8828 self.arrays[ArrayType.element_shell_is_alive][i_timestep] 

8829 if ArrayType.element_shell_is_alive in self.arrays 

8830 else np.ones(n_shells, dtype=settings.ftype) 

8831 ) 

8832 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(array, dtype_hint=np.floating)) 

8833 

8834 # BEAM DELETION 

8835 array = ( 

8836 self.arrays[ArrayType.element_beam_is_alive][i_timestep] 

8837 if ArrayType.element_beam_is_alive in self.arrays 

8838 else np.ones(n_beams, dtype=settings.ftype) 

8839 ) 

8840 n_bytes_written += fp.write(settings.pack(array, dtype_hint=np.floating)) 

8841 

8842 # check 

8843 n_bytes_expected = ( 

8844 settings.header["nel2"] 

8845 + settings.header["nel4"] 

8846 + abs(settings.header["nel8"]) 

8847 + settings.header["nelth"] 

8848 ) * settings.wordsize 

8849 

8850 else: 

8851 msg = f"Invalid mdlopt flag during write process: {settings.mdlopt}" 

8852 raise RuntimeError(msg) 

8853 

8854 # check bytes 

8855 if n_bytes_expected != n_bytes_written: 

8856 msg = ( 

8857 "byte checksum wrong: " 

8858 f"{n_bytes_expected} (header) != {n_bytes_written} (checksum)" 

8859 ) 

8860 raise RuntimeError(msg) 

8861 

8862 # log 

8863 msg = "%s wrote %d bytes." 

8864 LOGGER.debug(msg, "_write_states_deletion_info", n_bytes_written) 

8865 

8866 return n_bytes_written 

8867 

8868 def _write_states_sph( 

8869 self, fp: typing.IO[Any], i_timestep: int, settings: D3plotWriterSettings 

8870 ) -> int: 

8871 

8872 if settings.header["nmsph"] <= 0: 

8873 return 0 

8874 

8875 _check_ndim( 

8876 self, 

8877 { 

8878 ArrayType.sph_deletion: ["n_timesteps", "n_particles"], 

8879 ArrayType.sph_radius: ["n_timesteps", "n_particles"], 

8880 ArrayType.sph_pressure: ["n_timesteps", "n_particles"], 

8881 ArrayType.sph_stress: ["n_timesteps", "n_particles", "σx_σy_σz_σxy_σyz_σxz"], 

8882 ArrayType.sph_effective_plastic_strain: ["n_timesteps", "n_particles"], 

8883 ArrayType.sph_density: ["n_timesteps", "n_particles"], 

8884 ArrayType.sph_internal_energy: ["n_timesteps", "n_particles"], 

8885 ArrayType.sph_n_neighbors: ["n_timesteps", "n_particles"], 

8886 ArrayType.sph_strain: ["n_timesteps", "n_particles", "εx_εy_εz_εxy_εyz_εxz"], 

8887 ArrayType.sph_mass: ["n_timesteps", "n_particles"], 

8888 }, 

8889 ) 

8890 

8891 array_dims = { 

8892 ArrayType.global_timesteps: 0, 

8893 ArrayType.sph_deletion: 0, 

8894 ArrayType.sph_radius: 0, 

8895 ArrayType.sph_pressure: 0, 

8896 ArrayType.sph_stress: 0, 

8897 ArrayType.sph_effective_plastic_strain: 0, 

8898 ArrayType.sph_density: 0, 

8899 ArrayType.sph_internal_energy: 0, 

8900 ArrayType.sph_n_neighbors: 0, 

8901 ArrayType.sph_strain: 0, 

8902 ArrayType.sph_mass: 0, 

8903 } 

8904 self.check_array_dims(array_dims, "n_timesteps") 

8905 

8906 array_dims = { 

8907 ArrayType.sph_node_indexes: 0, 

8908 ArrayType.sph_deletion: 1, 

8909 ArrayType.sph_radius: 1, 

8910 ArrayType.sph_pressure: 1, 

8911 ArrayType.sph_stress: 1, 

8912 ArrayType.sph_effective_plastic_strain: 1, 

8913 ArrayType.sph_density: 1, 

8914 ArrayType.sph_internal_energy: 1, 

8915 ArrayType.sph_n_neighbors: 1, 

8916 ArrayType.sph_strain: 1, 

8917 ArrayType.sph_mass: 1, 

8918 } 

8919 n_particles = self.check_array_dims(array_dims, "n_particles") 

8920 self.check_array_dims({ArrayType.sph_stress: 2}, "σx_σy_σz_σxy_σyz_σxz", 6) 

8921 self.check_array_dims({ArrayType.sph_strain: 2}, "εx_εy_εz_εxy_εyz_εxz", 6) 

8922 

8923 n_sph_variables = settings.header["numsph"] 

8924 

8925 sph_data = np.zeros((n_particles, n_sph_variables)) 

8926 

8927 start_index = 0 

8928 end_index = 0 

8929 

8930 # SPH MATERIAL AND DELETION 

8931 start_index = 0 

8932 end_index = 1 

8933 array = ( 

8934 self.arrays[ArrayType.sph_deletion][i_timestep] 

8935 if ArrayType.sph_deletion in self.arrays 

8936 else np.ones(n_particles) 

8937 ) 

8938 sph_data[:, start_index:end_index] = array 

8939 

8940 # INFLUENCE RADIUS 

8941 if settings.header["isphfg2"]: 

8942 start_index = end_index 

8943 end_index = start_index + n_particles 

8944 if ArrayType.sph_radius in self.arrays: 

8945 array = self.arrays[ArrayType.sph_radius][i_timestep] 

8946 sph_data[:, start_index:end_index] = array 

8947 

8948 # PRESSURE 

8949 if settings.header["isphfg3"]: 

8950 start_index = end_index 

8951 end_index = start_index + n_particles 

8952 if ArrayType.sph_pressure in self.arrays: 

8953 array = self.arrays[ArrayType.sph_pressure][i_timestep] 

8954 sph_data[:, start_index:end_index] = array 

8955 

8956 # STRESS 

8957 if settings.header["isphfg4"]: 

8958 start_index = end_index 

8959 end_index = start_index + 6 * n_particles 

8960 if ArrayType.sph_stress in self.arrays: 

8961 array = self.arrays[ArrayType.sph_stress][i_timestep] 

8962 sph_data[:, start_index:end_index] = array 

8963 

8964 # PSTRAIN 

8965 if settings.header["isphfg5"]: 

8966 start_index = end_index 

8967 end_index = start_index + n_particles 

8968 if ArrayType.sph_effective_plastic_strain in self.arrays: 

8969 array = self.arrays[ArrayType.sph_effective_plastic_strain][i_timestep] 

8970 sph_data[:, start_index:end_index] = array 

8971 

8972 # DENSITY 

8973 if settings.header["isphfg6"]: 

8974 start_index = end_index 

8975 end_index = start_index + n_particles 

8976 if ArrayType.sph_density in self.arrays: 

8977 array = self.arrays[ArrayType.sph_density][i_timestep] 

8978 sph_data[:, start_index:end_index] = array 

8979 

8980 # INTERNAL ENERGY 

8981 if settings.header["isphfg7"]: 

8982 start_index = end_index 

8983 end_index = start_index + n_particles 

8984 if ArrayType.sph_internal_energy in self.arrays: 

8985 array = self.arrays[ArrayType.sph_internal_energy][i_timestep] 

8986 sph_data[:, start_index:end_index] = array 

8987 

8988 # INTERNAL ENERGY 

8989 if settings.header["isphfg8"]: 

8990 start_index = end_index 

8991 end_index = start_index + n_particles 

8992 if ArrayType.sph_n_neighbors in self.arrays: 

8993 array = self.arrays[ArrayType.sph_n_neighbors][i_timestep] 

8994 sph_data[:, start_index:end_index] = array 

8995 

8996 # STRAIN 

8997 if settings.header["isphfg9"]: 

8998 start_index = end_index 

8999 end_index = start_index + n_particles * 6 

9000 if ArrayType.sph_strain in self.arrays: 

9001 array = self.arrays[ArrayType.sph_strain][i_timestep] 

9002 sph_data[:, start_index:end_index] = array 

9003 

9004 # MASS 

9005 if settings.header["isphfg10"]: 

9006 start_index = end_index 

9007 end_index = start_index + n_particles 

9008 if ArrayType.sph_mass in self.arrays: 

9009 array = self.arrays[ArrayType.sph_mass][i_timestep] 

9010 sph_data[:, start_index:end_index] = array 

9011 

9012 n_bytes_written = fp.write(settings.pack(sph_data, dtype_hint=np.floating)) 

9013 

9014 # check bytes 

9015 n_bytes_expected = ( 

9016 settings.header["nv2d"] 

9017 * (settings.header["nel4"] - settings.header["numrbe"]) 

9018 * settings.wordsize 

9019 ) 

9020 if n_bytes_expected != n_bytes_written: 

9021 msg = ( 

9022 "byte checksum wrong: " 

9023 f"{n_bytes_expected} (header) != {n_bytes_written} (checksum)" 

9024 ) 

9025 raise RuntimeError(msg) 

9026 

9027 # log 

9028 msg = "%s wrote %d bytes." 

9029 LOGGER.debug(msg, "_write_states_sph", n_bytes_written) 

9030 

9031 return n_bytes_written

9431 

9432 def check_array_dims( 

9433 self, array_dimensions: Dict[str, int], dimension_name: str, dimension_size: int = -1 

9434 ): 

9435 """This function checks if multiple arrays share an array dimensions 

9436 with the same size. 

9437 

9438 Parameters 

9439 ---------- 

9440 array_dimensions: Dict[str, int] 

9441 Array name and expected number of dimensions as dict 

9442 dimension_name: str 

9443 Name of the array dimension for error messages 

9444 dimension_size: int 

9445 Optional expected size. If not set then all entries must equal 

9446 the first value collected. 

9447 

9448 Raises 

9449 ------ 

9450 ValueError 

9451 If dimensions do not match in any kind of way. 

9452 """ 

9453 

9454 dimension_size_dict = {} 

9455 

9456 # collect all dimensions 

9457 for typename, dimension_index in array_dimensions.items(): 

9458 if typename not in self.arrays: 

9459 continue 

9460 

9461 array = self.arrays[typename] 

9462 

9463 if dimension_index >= array.ndim: 

9464 msg = ( 

9465 f"Array '{typename}' requires at least " 

9466 f"{dimension_index} dimensions ({dimension_name})" 

9467 ) 

9468 raise ValueError(msg) 

9469 

9470 dimension_size_dict[typename] = array.shape[dimension_index] 

9471 

9472 # static dimension 

9473 if dimension_size >= 0: 

9474 arrays_with_wrong_dims = { 

9475 typename: size 

9476 for typename, size in dimension_size_dict.items() 

9477 if size != dimension_size 

9478 } 

9479 

9480 if arrays_with_wrong_dims: 

9481 msg = "The dimension %s of the following arrays is expected to have size %d:\n%s" 

9482 msg_arrays = [ 

9483 f" - name: {typename} dim: {array_dimensions[typename]} size: {size}" 

9484 for typename, size in arrays_with_wrong_dims.items() 

9485 ] 

9486 raise ValueError(msg, dimension_name, dimension_size, "\n".join(msg_arrays)) 

9487 

9488 # dynamic dimensions 

9489 else: 

9490 if dimension_size_dict: 

9491 unique_sizes = np.unique(list(dimension_size_dict.values())) 

9492 if len(unique_sizes) > 1: 

9493 msg = "Inconsistency in array dim '%d' detected:\n%s" 

9494 size_list = [ 

9495 f" - name: {typename}, dim: {array_dimensions[typename]}, size: {size}" 

9496 for typename, size in dimension_size_dict.items() 

9497 ] 

9498 raise ValueError(msg, dimension_name, "\n".join(size_list)) 

9499 if len(unique_sizes) == 1: 

9500 dimension_size = unique_sizes[0] 

9501 

9502 if dimension_size < 0: 

9503 return 0 

9504 

9505 return dimension_size 

9506 

9507 @staticmethod 

9508 def _compare_n_bytes_checksum(n_bytes_written: int, n_bytes_expected: int): 

9509 """Throw if the byte checksum was not ok 

9510 

9511 Parameters 

9512 ---------- 

9513 n_bytes_written: int 

9514 bytes written to the file 

9515 n_bytes_expected: int 

9516 bytes expected from the header computation 

9517 

9518 Raises 

9519 ------ 

9520 RuntimeError 

9521 If the byte count doesn't match. 

9522 """ 

9523 if n_bytes_expected != n_bytes_written: 

9524 msg = ( 

9525 "byte checksum wrong: " 

9526 f"{n_bytes_expected} (header) != {n_bytes_written} (checksum)" 

9527 ) 

9528 raise RuntimeError(msg) 

9529 

9530 def _get_zero_byte_padding(self, n_bytes_written: int, block_size_bytes: int): 

9531 """Compute the zero byte-padding at the end of files 

9532 

9533 Parameters 

9534 ---------- 

9535 n_bytes_written: int 

9536 number of bytes already written to file 

9537 block_size_bytes: int 

9538 byte block size of the file 

9539 

9540 Returns 

9541 ------- 

9542 zero_bytes: bytes 

9543 zero-byte padding ready to be written to the file 

9544 """ 

9545 

9546 if block_size_bytes > 0: 

9547 remaining_bytes = n_bytes_written % block_size_bytes 

9548 n_bytes_to_fill = block_size_bytes - remaining_bytes if remaining_bytes != 0 else 0 

9549 return b"\x00" * n_bytes_to_fill 

9550 

9551 return b"" 

9552 

9553 def compare(self, d3plot2, array_eps: Union[float, None] = None): 

9554 """Compare two d3plots and print the info 

9555 

9556 Parameters 

9557 ---------- 

9558 d3plot2: D3plot 

9559 second d3plot 

9560 array_eps: float or None 

9561 tolerance for arrays 

9562 

9563 Returns 

9564 ------- 

9565 hdr_differences: dict 

9566 differences in the header 

9567 array_differences: dict 

9568 difference between arrays as message 

9569 

9570 Examples 

9571 -------- 

9572 Comparison of a femzipped file and an uncompressed file. Femzip 

9573 is a lossy compression, thus precision is traded for memory. 

9574 

9575 >>> d3plot1 = D3plot("path/to/d3plot") 

9576 >>> d3plot2 = D3plot("path/to/d3plot.fz") 

9577 >>> hdr_diff, array_diff = d3plot1.compare(d3plot2) 

9578 >>> for arraytype, msg in array_diff.items(): 

9579 >>> print(name, msg) 

9580 node_coordinates Δmax = 0.050048828125 

9581 node_displacement Δmax = 0.050048828125 

9582 node_velocity Δmax = 0.050048828125 

9583 node_acceleration Δmax = 49998984.0 

9584 element_beam_axial_force Δmax = 6.103515625e-05 

9585 element_shell_stress Δmax = 0.0005035400390625 

9586 element_shell_thickness Δmax = 9.999999717180685e-10 

9587 element_shell_unknown_variables Δmax = 0.0005000010132789612 

9588 element_shell_internal_energy Δmax = 188.41957092285156 

9589 

9590 """ 

9591 

9592 # pylint: disable = too-many-nested-blocks 

9593 

9594 assert isinstance(d3plot2, D3plot) 

9595 d3plot1 = self 

9596 

9597 hdr_differences = d3plot1.header.compare(d3plot2.header) 

9598 

9599 # ARRAY COMPARISON 

9600 array_differences = {} 

9601 

9602 array_names = list(d3plot1.arrays.keys()) + list(d3plot2.arrays.keys()) 

9603 

9604 for name in array_names: 

9605 

9606 array1 = ( 

9607 d3plot1.arrays[name] if name in d3plot1.arrays else "Array is missing in original" 

9608 ) 

9609 

9610 array2 = d3plot2.arrays[name] if name in d3plot2.arrays else "Array is missing in other" 

9611 

9612 # d3parts write results for rigid shells. 

9613 # when rewriting as d3plot we simply 

9614 # don't write the part_material_types 

9615 # array which is the same as having no 

9616 # rigid shells. 

9617 d3plot1_is_d3part = d3plot1.header.filetype == D3plotFiletype.D3PART 

9618 d3plot2_is_d3part = d3plot2.header.filetype == D3plotFiletype.D3PART 

9619 if name == "part_material_type" and (d3plot1_is_d3part or d3plot2_is_d3part): 

9620 continue 

9621 

9622 # we have an array to compare 

9623 if isinstance(array1, str): 

9624 array_differences[name] = array1 

9625 elif isinstance(array2, str): 

9626 array_differences[name] = array2 

9627 elif isinstance(array2, np.ndarray): 

9628 comparison = False 

9629 

9630 # compare arrays 

9631 if isinstance(array1, np.ndarray): 

9632 if array1.shape != array2.shape: 

9633 comparison = f"shape mismatch {array1.shape} != {array2.shape}" 

9634 else: 

9635 if np.issubdtype(array1.dtype, np.number) and np.issubdtype( 

9636 array2.dtype, np.number 

9637 ): 

9638 diff = np.abs(array1 - array2) 

9639 if diff.size: 

9640 if array_eps is not None: 

9641 diff2 = diff[diff > array_eps] 

9642 if diff2.size: 

9643 diff2_max = diff2.max() 

9644 if diff2_max: 

9645 comparison = f"Δmax = {diff2_max}" 

9646 else: 

9647 diff_max = diff.max() 

9648 if diff_max: 

9649 comparison = f"Δmax = {diff_max}" 

9650 else: 

9651 n_mismatches = (array1 != array2).sum() 

9652 if n_mismatches: 

9653 comparison = f"Mismatches: {n_mismatches}" 

9654 

9655 else: 

9656 comparison = "Arrays don't match" 

9657 

9658 # print 

9659 if comparison: 

9660 array_differences[name] = comparison 

9661 

9662 return hdr_differences, array_differences 

9663 

9664 def get_part_filter( 

9665 self, filter_type: FilterType, part_ids: Iterable[int], for_state_array: bool = True 

9666 ) -> np.ndarray: 

9667 """Get a part filter for different entities 

9668 

9669 Parameters 

9670 ---------- 

9671 filter_type: lasso.dyna.FilterType 

9672 the array type to filter for (beam, shell, solid, tshell, node) 

9673 part_ids: Iterable[int] 

9674 part ids to filter out 

9675 for_state_array: bool 

9676 if the filter is meant for a state array. Makes a difference 

9677 for shells if rigid bodies are in the model (mattyp == 20) 

9678 

9679 Returns 

9680 ------- 

9681 mask: np.ndarray 

9682 mask usable on arrays to filter results 

9683 

9684 Examples 

9685 -------- 

9686 >>> from lasso.dyna import D3plot, ArrayType, FilterType 

9687 >>> d3plot = D3plot("path/to/d3plot") 

9688 >>> part_ids = [13, 14] 

9689 >>> mask = d3plot.get_part_filter(FilterType.shell) 

9690 >>> shell_stress = d3plot.arrays[ArrayType.element_shell_stress] 

9691 >>> shell_stress.shape 

9692 (34, 7463, 3, 6) 

9693 >>> # select only parts from part_ids 

9694 >>> shell_stress_parts = shell_stress[:, mask] 

9695 """ 

9696 

9697 # nodes are treated separately 

9698 if filter_type == FilterType.NODE: 

9699 node_index_arrays = [] 

9700 

9701 if ArrayType.element_shell_node_indexes in self.arrays: 

9702 shell_filter = self.get_part_filter( 

9703 FilterType.SHELL, part_ids, for_state_array=False 

9704 ) 

9705 shell_node_indexes = self.arrays[ArrayType.element_shell_node_indexes] 

9706 node_index_arrays.append(shell_node_indexes[shell_filter].flatten()) 

9707 

9708 if ArrayType.element_solid_node_indexes in self.arrays: 

9709 solid_filter = self.get_part_filter( 

9710 FilterType.SOLID, part_ids, for_state_array=False 

9711 ) 

9712 solid_node_indexes = self.arrays[ArrayType.element_solid_node_indexes] 

9713 node_index_arrays.append(solid_node_indexes[solid_filter].flatten()) 

9714 

9715 if ArrayType.element_tshell_node_indexes in self.arrays: 

9716 tshell_filter = self.get_part_filter( 

9717 FilterType.TSHELL, part_ids, for_state_array=False 

9718 ) 

9719 tshell_node_indexes = self.arrays[ArrayType.element_tshell_node_indexes] 

9720 node_index_arrays.append(tshell_node_indexes[tshell_filter].flatten()) 

9721 

9722 return np.unique(np.concatenate(node_index_arrays)) 

9723 

9724 # we need part ids first 

9725 if ArrayType.part_ids in self.arrays: 

9726 d3plot_part_ids = self.arrays[ArrayType.part_ids] 

9727 elif ArrayType.part_titles_ids in self.arrays: 

9728 d3plot_part_ids = self.arrays[ArrayType.part_titles_ids] 

9729 else: 

9730 msg = "D3plot does neither contain '%s' nor '%s'" 

9731 raise RuntimeError(msg, ArrayType.part_ids, ArrayType.part_titles_ids) 

9732 

9733 # if we filter parts we can stop here 

9734 if filter_type == FilterType.PART: 

9735 return np.isin(d3plot_part_ids, part_ids) 

9736 

9737 # get part indexes from part ids 

9738 part_indexes = np.argwhere(np.isin(d3plot_part_ids, part_ids)).flatten() 

9739 

9740 # associate part indexes with entities 

9741 if filter_type == FilterType.BEAM: 

9742 entity_part_indexes = self.arrays[ArrayType.element_beam_part_indexes] 

9743 elif filter_type == FilterType.SHELL: 

9744 entity_part_indexes = self.arrays[ArrayType.element_shell_part_indexes] 

9745 

9746 # shells may contain "rigid body shell elements" 

9747 # for these shells no state data is output and thus 

9748 # the state arrays have a reduced element count 

9749 if for_state_array and self._material_section_info.n_rigid_shells != 0: 

9750 mat_types = self.arrays[ArrayType.part_material_type] 

9751 mat_type_filter = mat_types[entity_part_indexes] != 20 

9752 entity_part_indexes = entity_part_indexes[mat_type_filter] 

9753 

9754 elif filter_type == FilterType.TSHELL: 

9755 entity_part_indexes = self.arrays[ArrayType.element_tshell_part_indexes] 

9756 elif filter_type == FilterType.SOLID: 

9757 entity_part_indexes = self.arrays[ArrayType.element_solid_part_indexes] 

9758 else: 

9759 msg = "Invalid filter_type '%s'. Use lasso.dyna.FilterType." 

9760 raise ValueError(msg, filter_type) 

9761 

9762 mask = np.isin(entity_part_indexes, part_indexes) 

9763 return mask 

9764 

9765 @staticmethod 

9766 def enable_logger(enable: bool): 

9767 """Enable the logger for this class 

9768 

9769 Parameters 

9770 ---------- 

9771 enable: bool 

9772 whether to enable logging for this class 

9773 """ 

9774 

9775 if enable: 

9776 LOGGER.setLevel(logging.DEBUG) 

9777 else: 

9778 LOGGER.setLevel(logging.NOTSET)
